1
00:03:20,301 --> 00:03:22,341
"Time is not a straight line.

2
00:03:22,621 --> 00:03:25,101
The past, the future,
and the present coexist.

3
00:03:25,421 --> 00:03:27,140
Humans live through several ages

4
00:03:27,141 --> 00:03:30,661
and several lifetimes,
separated only by time." - Hermann Hesse.

5
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:34,940
"Across every age and every lifetime,

6
00:03:34,941 --> 00:03:38,661
our fate remains the same:
to be royally screwed." - Shaji Paappan

7
00:03:44,301 --> 00:03:45,461
War...

8
00:03:46,021 --> 00:03:49,261
A battle for freedom that has raged
for aeons across the world.

9
00:03:52,741 --> 00:03:54,301
A single enemy for everyone.

10
00:03:54,941 --> 00:03:56,261
The Organisation.

11
00:03:57,181 --> 00:04:00,101
A colossal private entity
that rules the whole world.

12
00:04:03,021 --> 00:04:07,061
They overthrew every government
and every democratic institution.

13
00:04:09,901 --> 00:04:11,540
Some of them were bought.

14
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:12,941
Anyone who resisted was eliminated.

15
00:04:14,021 --> 00:04:17,981
Only a few people like us
continue to fight without stopping.

16
00:04:19,141 --> 00:04:20,180
What I'm about to tell you now...

17
00:04:20,181 --> 00:04:23,380
I've wanted to tell you this
for a very long time.

18
00:04:23,381 --> 00:04:25,541
And today, the right moment
has finally arrived.

19
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:41,021
How did this Organisation
conquer the whole world?

20
00:04:42,381 --> 00:04:43,341
Do you have any idea?

21
00:04:43,821 --> 00:04:44,860
No.

22
00:04:44,861 --> 00:04:46,101
I have the answer.

23
00:04:47,061 --> 00:04:48,261
They time travelled.

24
00:04:50,901 --> 00:04:53,421
First, they gained mastery
over time and its eras.

25
00:04:54,141 --> 00:04:55,141
How?

26
00:04:57,661 --> 00:04:59,301
All because of this.

27
00:05:08,781 --> 00:05:09,940
Star Dust.

28
00:05:09,941 --> 00:05:11,621
A rare and mysterious relic.

29
00:05:12,141 --> 00:05:16,941
They became capable of controlling
timelines by harvesting its energy.

30
00:05:19,221 --> 00:05:20,181
Now what, Baba?

31
00:05:20,381 --> 00:05:21,861
That is a profound question!

32
00:05:22,301 --> 00:05:24,900
No one can defeat them
with weapons alone.

33
00:05:24,901 --> 00:05:26,781
I've been saying that for ages.

34
00:05:27,781 --> 00:05:29,741
The timelines must be corrected.

35
00:05:29,941 --> 00:05:32,541
For that to happen, the Star Dust
must return to the righteous.

36
00:05:33,341 --> 00:05:35,180
Right now it is in the hands of people

37
00:05:35,181 --> 00:05:38,421
whom we would normally
never see or interact with.

38
00:05:39,421 --> 00:05:40,741
Total strangers.

39
00:05:41,181 --> 00:05:43,181
Their decisions will determine

40
00:05:44,021 --> 00:05:46,541
the fate of the entire world.

41
00:06:00,341 --> 00:06:01,780
Baba, these strangers...

42
00:06:01,781 --> 00:06:03,101
Are these people heroes?

43
00:06:03,261 --> 00:06:04,621
Heroes...?
Yes.

44
00:06:04,981 --> 00:06:08,181
But they are also
a bunch of idiots.

45
00:06:13,061 --> 00:06:14,461
[It's me,
Shaji Paappan]

46
00:06:14,581 --> 00:06:16,421
As always,
I'll kick this off myself.

47
00:06:16,781 --> 00:06:18,501
I am Arakkal Abu.

48
00:06:19,061 --> 00:06:20,781
Since it's been a while
since we last met,

49
00:06:20,981 --> 00:06:22,181
let me catch you up.

50
00:06:23,061 --> 00:06:26,141
Moonga's family packed him off
to Saudi for a forced detox.

51
00:06:26,421 --> 00:06:28,500
To fill his spot, his younger brother
Moosa showed up!

52
00:06:28,501 --> 00:06:29,500
God knows why!

53
00:06:29,501 --> 00:06:30,500
That's not enough!

54
00:06:30,501 --> 00:06:33,181
If it were you, only a village
would roast you!

55
00:06:33,341 --> 00:06:34,940
But honestly, we never knew

56
00:06:34,941 --> 00:06:37,821
your brother goes around
getting roasted all across Kerala!

57
00:06:38,301 --> 00:06:41,661
♪ The cutest little goat ♪

58
00:06:41,941 --> 00:06:45,421
♪ The sugary sweet goat ♪

59
00:06:48,421 --> 00:06:49,380
Mom!

60
00:06:49,381 --> 00:06:51,940
If the court case ends soon,
won't Paappan get the gold trophy?

61
00:06:51,941 --> 00:06:53,901
Once he sells it,
won't Paappan become rich?

62
00:06:54,021 --> 00:06:55,540
Then he can buy
our house back, right?

63
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:56,540
Oh, yeah?

64
00:06:56,541 --> 00:07:00,341
Our house deed is still pledged to that
loan shark 'Iron' Abdullah, isn't it?

65
00:07:00,541 --> 00:07:02,780
We used to live in our own house,
now we're stuck in a rented one.

66
00:07:02,781 --> 00:07:05,821
I won't let that crook Paappan
set foot in this house!

67
00:07:06,141 --> 00:07:08,421
As always, Ammachi refuses
to let Paappan in the house.

68
00:07:08,541 --> 00:07:09,541
Hey, Paappan...

69
00:07:09,781 --> 00:07:10,941
Ammachi isn't budging.

70
00:07:11,101 --> 00:07:12,420
Better stay away for now.

71
00:07:12,421 --> 00:07:13,621
What else am I supposed to do?

72
00:07:14,101 --> 00:07:16,541
Only this time,
he's banned from the rented house too.

73
00:07:17,741 --> 00:07:20,821
We were so punctual with the rent
on the first of every month that

74
00:07:21,101 --> 00:07:23,581
the old club owner kicked us out.

75
00:07:24,181 --> 00:07:25,981
We've moved
to a new club headquarters now.

76
00:07:26,221 --> 00:07:28,341
New place, same old unpaid rent.

77
00:07:30,301 --> 00:07:32,180
Cleetus is still the same old Cleetus.

78
00:07:32,181 --> 00:07:33,860
♪ Captain Cleetus ♪

79
00:07:33,861 --> 00:07:34,900
A total nuisance!

80
00:07:34,901 --> 00:07:36,621
♪ Everyone else is a worker ♪

81
00:07:36,741 --> 00:07:38,580
♪ But Cleetus is the Big Boss
of the world ♪

82
00:07:38,581 --> 00:07:39,580
Cut! Cut! Cut!

83
00:07:39,581 --> 00:07:40,740
- Shucks!
- What's the issue?

84
00:07:40,741 --> 00:07:42,900
When you say "money money,"
laugh with a nice bright ring to it!

85
00:07:42,901 --> 00:07:44,140
Give me that filthy rich vibe!

86
00:07:44,141 --> 00:07:45,661
- Get another bundle of notes now.
- Okay.

87
00:07:46,181 --> 00:07:47,820
Ugh, I can't stand
looking at Lolan's face!

88
00:07:47,821 --> 00:07:49,061
Looks like a chopped yam!

89
00:07:49,181 --> 00:07:51,420
Dude!
You mock me if I grow a beard!

90
00:07:51,421 --> 00:07:52,740
You mock me even
if I shave it off!

91
00:07:52,741 --> 00:07:54,021
What next,
should I chop my head off?

92
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:55,420
Action!

93
00:07:55,421 --> 00:07:56,941
What the hell are
you doing, Cleetus?

94
00:07:57,461 --> 00:07:58,820
Those are dollars!
If Paappan finds out...

95
00:07:58,821 --> 00:07:59,740
Pick it all up!

96
00:07:59,741 --> 00:08:00,740
Yes.

97
00:08:00,741 --> 00:08:02,260
Paappan is making
one last desperate attempt.

98
00:08:02,261 --> 00:08:05,780
He's trying to take the ten lakh dollars
we got from the fake healers

99
00:08:05,781 --> 00:08:07,700
all the way to America
to exchange it into Indian rupees

100
00:08:07,701 --> 00:08:08,981
and finally make it in life.

101
00:08:09,661 --> 00:08:10,821
And we're in on it too.

102
00:08:11,181 --> 00:08:12,421
Though it's taking some time,

103
00:08:12,741 --> 00:08:16,301
Paappan says everyone's travel papers
are getting cleared.

104
00:08:16,901 --> 00:08:18,740
Cleetus, however, can't go.

105
00:08:18,741 --> 00:08:19,620
Why, dude?

106
00:08:19,621 --> 00:08:22,420
You don't have a certificate showing
you failed 10th grade like we do, right?

107
00:08:22,421 --> 00:08:22,940
Yeah!

108
00:08:22,941 --> 00:08:25,341
Didn't you drop out in third grade
once they stopped the free breakfast?

109
00:08:25,981 --> 00:08:27,061
So,

110
00:08:27,181 --> 00:08:28,501
you won't get a passport...

111
00:08:29,101 --> 00:08:30,100
because...

112
00:08:30,101 --> 00:08:32,501
you don't even have
the documents required to apply.

113
00:08:33,421 --> 00:08:34,741
Go on, cry your heart out.

114
00:08:35,421 --> 00:08:37,301
Cleetus may be sad and jealous,

115
00:08:37,741 --> 00:08:38,941
but we don't care.

116
00:08:39,301 --> 00:08:43,621
Because those dollars are our last shot
at becoming winners in life.

117
00:08:50,061 --> 00:08:52,101
Why are you sitting alone, Captain?
Where is Paappan?

118
00:08:52,821 --> 00:08:54,500
They must have gone to America.

119
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:56,061
To America?
For what?

120
00:08:56,581 --> 00:08:57,820
And then, for no reason at all,

121
00:08:57,821 --> 00:09:01,261
Rachel decided to strike up
a conversation with the Captain.

122
00:09:01,861 --> 00:09:02,860
Well, Captain...

123
00:09:02,861 --> 00:09:04,340
The American President, Trump...

124
00:09:04,341 --> 00:09:07,541
is attending a youth meeting
at the Coimbatore stadium.

125
00:09:08,181 --> 00:09:10,740
You should go and meet Trump
with those Dollars, Captain.

126
00:09:10,741 --> 00:09:11,821
Then you should tell Trump,

127
00:09:11,941 --> 00:09:13,820
"This is your Dollar.
Give me Indian money."

128
00:09:13,821 --> 00:09:17,180
He will personally hand you
mint-fresh Gandhi notes right away.

129
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:18,180
- Simple!
- Is it?

130
00:09:18,181 --> 00:09:19,701
If you have any doubt,

131
00:09:19,861 --> 00:09:21,461
just say, "I'm a tourist,
I'm a tourist."

132
00:09:21,821 --> 00:09:23,181
She was only kidding.

133
00:09:23,461 --> 00:09:25,141
But of course,
Cleetus took it seriously.

134
00:09:26,501 --> 00:09:27,621
Paappan!!!

135
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:29,621
♪ Captain Cleetus ♪

136
00:09:29,821 --> 00:09:31,021
Wait and watch!

137
00:09:34,581 --> 00:09:36,861
[Winners Club - Pothumukku]

138
00:09:46,501 --> 00:09:47,821
Krishnan!

139
00:09:48,181 --> 00:09:49,621
What's wrong?
Did a snake get in? Huh?

140
00:09:50,781 --> 00:09:51,861
What is it?

141
00:09:52,181 --> 00:09:53,901
- Yikes!
- Jesus! Where did the dollars go?

142
00:09:55,981 --> 00:09:57,140
What is this?
Konkani?

143
00:09:57,141 --> 00:09:58,581
To deerest Peppan,

144
00:09:59,101 --> 00:10:00,780
I'm leaving with the door.

145
00:10:00,781 --> 00:10:02,300
I'll return as a rick guy.

146
00:10:02,301 --> 00:10:04,900
Why take the door there?
Why not call the rick guy here?

147
00:10:04,901 --> 00:10:07,181
- But the door is right here.
- That's right! Read the rest.

148
00:10:07,501 --> 00:10:09,941
Drum is combing Koya bathroom.

149
00:10:10,461 --> 00:10:11,940
I'll comb back after mating him.

150
00:10:11,941 --> 00:10:13,941
- What's he going to comb?
- Read the rest.

151
00:10:14,221 --> 00:10:16,061
If I say I will comb,
I will comb!

152
00:10:16,461 --> 00:10:17,821
I swear on Madam!

153
00:10:18,221 --> 00:10:20,661
Yours sin-seer-lee,
Cleerus the Claw.

154
00:10:21,901 --> 00:10:23,580
Who on earth swears on a Madam?

155
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:24,781
With him,
anything is possible.

156
00:10:25,221 --> 00:10:26,700
You're reading it all wrong!

157
00:10:26,701 --> 00:10:27,941
To dearest Paappan,

158
00:10:28,181 --> 00:10:29,621
I'm leaving with the dollars.

159
00:10:29,741 --> 00:10:30,901
I'll return as a rich guy.

160
00:10:31,021 --> 00:10:32,340
Trump is visiting Coimbatore.

161
00:10:32,341 --> 00:10:33,540
I'll come back
after meeting him.

162
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:35,100
If I say I will come,
I will come!

163
00:10:35,101 --> 00:10:36,260
I swear on Mother Mary!

164
00:10:36,261 --> 00:10:38,021
Yours sincerely,
Cleetus. Signed.

165
00:10:38,301 --> 00:10:39,380
So it wasn't 'The Claw'?

166
00:10:39,381 --> 00:10:40,660
How did you even read this?

167
00:10:40,661 --> 00:10:42,140
I'm the one who wrote it
for Captain!

168
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:43,221
Oh!

169
00:10:43,701 --> 00:10:45,580
- What are you doing?
- Uploading it as my status update!

170
00:10:45,581 --> 00:10:46,901
- Oh!
- Leave that.

171
00:10:47,101 --> 00:10:48,340
What will I tell Paappan?

172
00:10:48,341 --> 00:10:49,821
What will I tell the travel agent?

173
00:10:50,101 --> 00:10:51,100
Hey, where's our vehicle?

174
00:10:51,101 --> 00:10:53,221
Let's grab him in Coimbatore
before he does something stupid.

175
00:10:54,541 --> 00:10:57,140
Here at the Venkatachalam Stadium
Coimbatore,

176
00:10:57,141 --> 00:11:00,340
the final media rehearsals
and mock sessions are going on.

177
00:11:00,341 --> 00:11:02,861
As you can see,
the security is already beefed up,

178
00:11:03,061 --> 00:11:04,661
since the threats have
always been there.

179
00:11:05,541 --> 00:11:07,181
♪ Captain Cleetus ♪

180
00:11:07,341 --> 00:11:08,981
♪ Captain Cleetus ♪

181
00:11:09,141 --> 00:11:10,741
Trump, my man!
Here I come!

182
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:14,101
At least today, I'll prove
to Paappan that I'm smart.

183
00:11:14,261 --> 00:11:16,221
All this police security
just to receive me?

184
00:11:16,381 --> 00:11:17,860
Anyway, I'll deal
only with the big man.

185
00:11:17,861 --> 00:11:19,061
- Hey, stop!
- Huh?

186
00:11:19,261 --> 00:11:20,221
[In Hindi] Who are you?

187
00:11:20,541 --> 00:11:21,501
What do you want?

188
00:11:22,101 --> 00:11:26,261
[in broken Hindi] This... from the bag...
inside... uh... from Trump... dollars...

189
00:11:26,941 --> 00:11:28,101
Give Indian money.

190
00:11:28,301 --> 00:11:29,740
[In Hindi] What nonsense
is this idiot saying?

191
00:11:29,741 --> 00:11:31,500
How do I explain
this to him?

192
00:11:31,501 --> 00:11:32,460
What?

193
00:11:32,461 --> 00:11:34,141
[in broken Hindi]
I talk you... talk you.

194
00:11:34,381 --> 00:11:35,260
Huh!

195
00:11:35,261 --> 00:11:36,701
These are all dollars.

196
00:11:39,141 --> 00:11:40,421
Is Trump done
with his tea break?

197
00:11:41,101 --> 00:11:42,461
- What's going on?
- Sir...

198
00:11:42,741 --> 00:11:44,300
[In Hindi] He wants
to exchange dollars.

199
00:11:44,301 --> 00:11:45,381
- Give it to me.
- Okay, sir.

200
00:11:47,461 --> 00:11:48,741
- This is fake currency.
- Fake?

201
00:11:48,901 --> 00:11:49,900
It's fake, man.

202
00:11:49,901 --> 00:11:51,620
- Yeah, yeah.
- Are you crazy?

203
00:11:51,621 --> 00:11:53,861
Didn't Rachel teach me something?!

204
00:11:54,301 --> 00:11:56,341
- Yes! I am a terrorist!
- What?

205
00:11:57,221 --> 00:11:58,820
Put the guns away!
No need for that!

206
00:11:58,821 --> 00:12:00,181
I'm telling the truth.

207
00:12:00,741 --> 00:12:02,900
If you don't believe me,
call Paappan and check.

208
00:12:02,901 --> 00:12:04,341
You rascal!
You're pulling a gun out?

209
00:12:07,501 --> 00:12:10,261
As soon as Lasar got his hands on
the money-mint, he burst out laughing.

210
00:12:10,381 --> 00:12:11,501
So did we!

211
00:12:14,741 --> 00:12:16,860
Whenever we ask where
he got the dollars from,

212
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:19,461
he's been feeding us this same load
of crap for four days straight.

213
00:12:19,981 --> 00:12:22,661
The guy looks
mentally unstable.

214
00:12:23,141 --> 00:12:25,181
I've got his address and details.
We'll see.

215
00:12:25,901 --> 00:12:29,021
How can you be so sure
my dollars are fake?

216
00:12:29,301 --> 00:12:30,421
Tell me.

217
00:12:30,581 --> 00:12:32,061
This is a real American dollar note.

218
00:12:32,581 --> 00:12:34,180
And this here
is Benjamin Franklin.

219
00:12:34,181 --> 00:12:36,300
He never wore glasses
in his life.

220
00:12:36,301 --> 00:12:37,300
Really?

221
00:12:37,301 --> 00:12:39,940
But on your notes,
Franklin is wearing glasses.

222
00:12:39,941 --> 00:12:41,060
How come?

223
00:12:41,061 --> 00:12:42,181
Let me see that.

224
00:12:43,261 --> 00:12:44,421
Huh!

225
00:12:45,061 --> 00:12:46,821
You sneaky little devil!

226
00:12:47,421 --> 00:12:50,300
You stole Gandhi's glasses,
took a photo wearing them,

227
00:12:50,301 --> 00:12:52,301
and printed it
on your currency notes, huh?

228
00:12:52,821 --> 00:12:55,901
Sir, you must charge him
under every law in the book!

229
00:12:59,581 --> 00:13:00,701
You saw that, right?

230
00:13:01,221 --> 00:13:02,500
He's trapped!

231
00:13:02,501 --> 00:13:03,901
If we don't step in now,

232
00:13:04,061 --> 00:13:05,661
Cleetus will rot in jail forever.

233
00:13:06,581 --> 00:13:07,860
So,

234
00:13:07,861 --> 00:13:09,741
we decided to put our
brains to work.

235
00:13:11,901 --> 00:13:14,020
No one usually
blocks our vehicle,

236
00:13:14,021 --> 00:13:15,580
but sometimes,
we block theirs.

237
00:13:15,581 --> 00:13:16,820
[In Tamil] Why are you slowing down?

238
00:13:16,821 --> 00:13:18,501
There's a vehicle
crossing the road, sir.

239
00:13:24,941 --> 00:13:26,261
And when we block them,

240
00:13:26,581 --> 00:13:29,621
you guys should already have taken
positions on both sides of the road

241
00:13:29,981 --> 00:13:31,901
without drawing any suspicion.

242
00:13:32,301 --> 00:13:34,020
You remember everything
we planned, right?

243
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:35,300
As soon as Abu fires,

244
00:13:35,301 --> 00:13:36,300
blast it immediately!

245
00:13:36,301 --> 00:13:37,420
Copy that!

246
00:13:37,421 --> 00:13:39,300
- Who is that?
- Hey! Who is that?

247
00:13:39,301 --> 00:13:40,981
Hey! You're
deafening me!

248
00:13:41,461 --> 00:13:42,460
Go there and ask him.

249
00:13:42,461 --> 00:13:43,781
- Okay, sir.
- Just go ask him.

250
00:13:44,421 --> 00:13:45,981
Hey! Who are you?

251
00:13:46,341 --> 00:13:48,061
Why have you parked across the road?

252
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:50,461
Sir, I've got a flat tire.

253
00:13:50,701 --> 00:13:51,980
I don't have any tools with me.

254
00:13:51,981 --> 00:13:53,580
The mechanic is on his way
with the tools.

255
00:13:53,581 --> 00:13:55,700
Now all he needs is a parrot
and some tarot cards.

256
00:13:55,701 --> 00:13:57,580
By the way,
where are you headed, sir?

257
00:13:57,581 --> 00:13:59,381
Hey! You're asking us
where we're going!?

258
00:13:59,661 --> 00:14:02,021
Call the mechanic!
Are you just making up stories?

259
00:14:17,701 --> 00:14:19,980
♪ Abu is terror untold,
A devil ruthless and bold ♪

260
00:14:19,981 --> 00:14:22,340
♪ Wingman to the Lord of Doom
Blood is his sweet perfume ♪

261
00:14:22,341 --> 00:14:26,901
♪ With a machete he combs his hair,
Chopping heads is his hobby... beware! ♪

262
00:14:27,501 --> 00:14:28,901
Character change!

263
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:30,941
Minus the rage!

264
00:14:31,461 --> 00:14:33,820
♪ Wingman to the Lord of Doom
Blood is his sweet perfume ♪

265
00:14:33,821 --> 00:14:36,820
♪ With a machete he combs his hair,
Chopping heads is his hobby... beware! ♪

266
00:14:36,821 --> 00:14:37,901
Here he comes, sir.

267
00:14:48,741 --> 00:14:50,541
Hurry up, you rascal!

268
00:14:51,941 --> 00:14:53,340
He is a superb mechanic.

269
00:14:53,341 --> 00:14:55,101
He'll probably mess up
the vehicle even more.

270
00:14:56,421 --> 00:14:58,101
- Hurry up!
- Sir, just two minutes.

271
00:14:58,341 --> 00:14:59,620
He is a lazy ox, sir.

272
00:14:59,621 --> 00:15:01,021
He's always like this!
Crazy guy!

273
00:15:01,301 --> 00:15:02,741
What are you staring at?
Want a slap?

274
00:15:03,021 --> 00:15:04,541
Try it.
I'll teach you a lesson!

275
00:15:08,661 --> 00:15:09,660
Ready?

276
00:15:09,661 --> 00:15:12,100
♪ Chapathi chapathi
chapathi chapathi ♪

277
00:15:12,101 --> 00:15:13,260
♪ Parotta Sambar ♪

278
00:15:13,261 --> 00:15:14,060
Sir...

279
00:15:14,061 --> 00:15:16,541
It's a bicycle pump. How can they
inflate a van tire with that?

280
00:15:17,621 --> 00:15:19,020
- Am I the one doing it?
- No, sir.

281
00:15:19,021 --> 00:15:20,500
You idiot! Go ask him!

282
00:15:20,501 --> 00:15:23,180
♪ Chapathi chapathi ♪

283
00:15:23,181 --> 00:15:24,220
Hey!

284
00:15:24,221 --> 00:15:26,940
Are you trying to be funny
inflating it with a bicycle pump?

285
00:15:26,941 --> 00:15:28,020
Get your vehicle off the road!

286
00:15:28,021 --> 00:15:29,340
This is how we do it
back home, sir.

287
00:15:29,341 --> 00:15:30,381
Just five minutes, sir.

288
00:15:31,581 --> 00:15:33,421
Right when the fight
is about to break out,

289
00:15:35,861 --> 00:15:38,021
that's when Paappan
makes his grand entrance!

290
00:15:38,301 --> 00:15:39,821
SHAJIYETTAA!

291
00:15:41,461 --> 00:15:42,701
♪ Paappan, Paappan ♪

292
00:15:43,141 --> 00:15:44,621
♪ O Paappan, Paappan ♪

293
00:15:45,061 --> 00:15:46,301
♪ O Paappan, Paappan ♪

294
00:15:46,781 --> 00:15:48,181
♪ O Paappan, Paappan ♪

295
00:15:48,741 --> 00:15:52,420
♪ Even Haji Mastan would salute the man,
The brave and mighty Shaji Paappan ♪

296
00:15:52,421 --> 00:15:55,740
♪ Even an atom bomb would surely fizzle,
Before Shaji Paappan's lethal sizzle ♪

297
00:15:55,741 --> 00:15:59,060
♪ Even Haji Mastan would salute the man,
The brave and mighty Shaji Paappan ♪

298
00:15:59,061 --> 00:16:02,341
♪ Even an atom bomb would surely fizzle,
Before Shaji Paappan's lethal sizzle ♪

299
00:16:02,661 --> 00:16:03,740
Explosive!

300
00:16:03,741 --> 00:16:04,820
A barrage of fireworks!

301
00:16:04,821 --> 00:16:05,981
A festival indeed!

302
00:16:06,301 --> 00:16:17,261
♪ O precious Paappan,
O priceless Paappan ♪

303
00:16:26,981 --> 00:16:28,101
Hey! Who the hell are you?

304
00:16:28,901 --> 00:16:29,941
Paappan!

305
00:16:30,461 --> 00:16:31,661
Shaji Paappan!

306
00:16:33,261 --> 00:16:34,700
Release my boy right now!

307
00:16:34,701 --> 00:16:36,821
Hey! What the hell have you
guys been doing for so long?

308
00:16:37,101 --> 00:16:38,061
It's nothing, sir.

309
00:16:38,461 --> 00:16:39,421
Hey!

310
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:40,900
This is your final warning.

311
00:16:40,901 --> 00:16:42,301
Move your vehicle and leave.

312
00:16:42,581 --> 00:16:44,300
Or else, I'll bury you
right where you stand!

313
00:16:44,301 --> 00:16:45,501
Son of a b****!

314
00:16:45,941 --> 00:16:46,901
Huh!

315
00:17:00,061 --> 00:17:02,181
Use that language with your father.
Try it with Paappan,

316
00:17:03,181 --> 00:17:05,340
and that head of yours
won't stay on your neck!

317
00:17:05,341 --> 00:17:07,060
- Destroy him, Paappan!
- Oh, yeah!

318
00:17:07,061 --> 00:17:08,901
No sentiments,
no compromise!

319
00:17:09,141 --> 00:17:10,101
Hey! Zip it!

320
00:17:10,421 --> 00:17:11,980
Why are you still standing there
talking to him?

321
00:17:11,981 --> 00:17:12,981
Shoot him!

322
00:17:16,301 --> 00:17:17,420
Now that's what
I'm talking about!

323
00:17:17,421 --> 00:17:18,501
Blast!

324
00:17:22,221 --> 00:17:23,221
Oh no!

325
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:28,260
♪ The festival bursts with joy in the air,
Cheers and euphoria everywhere ♪

326
00:17:28,261 --> 00:17:31,020
♪ Rope in hand for the tug-of-war,
Here comes the little army with a roar ♪

327
00:17:31,021 --> 00:17:36,420
♪ Drums roll loud, storm-clouds proclaim,
Sirens and war-cries hail their fame ♪

328
00:17:36,421 --> 00:17:39,260
♪ The world shall bow
to their blazing palms ♪

329
00:17:39,261 --> 00:17:42,100
♪ Like pearls that fall
from shattered dreams ♪

330
00:17:42,101 --> 00:17:47,701
♪ Like lightning racing for the sky,
Their daring hearts find paths to try ♪

331
00:17:48,861 --> 00:17:49,901
Cleetus!

332
00:17:50,381 --> 00:17:51,541
Come get in the vehicle!

333
00:17:52,221 --> 00:17:53,980
Why should I get in that vehicle?

334
00:17:53,981 --> 00:17:55,380
You should get in
this one instead, Paappan.

335
00:17:55,381 --> 00:17:57,421
Then we'd have two junk
vehicles of our own!

336
00:17:58,141 --> 00:17:59,101
Cleetus...

337
00:17:59,981 --> 00:18:02,381
I'm not even going to ask
how you pull this off!

338
00:18:03,021 --> 00:18:05,061
But how did your father
even pull this off?

339
00:18:05,421 --> 00:18:06,621
Get out here, you swamp-rat!

340
00:18:07,701 --> 00:18:13,180
♪ Where firework rebels gather bold,
Defy the sun that burns the road ♪

341
00:18:13,181 --> 00:18:18,780
♪ O fearless legends brave and free,
Swimming across the roaring, raging sea ♪

342
00:18:18,781 --> 00:18:21,380
♪ With burning embers in their veins,
With fiery wings that break their chains ♪

343
00:18:21,381 --> 00:18:24,180
♪ War-drums roar across the land,
The world now trembles at their stand ♪

344
00:18:24,181 --> 00:18:26,900
♪ Crouching panthers shiver in dread,
Their pride bows down its head ♪

345
00:18:26,901 --> 00:18:30,221
♪ All who stand before their might,
Soon call it quits and quit the fight ♪

346
00:18:31,541 --> 00:18:32,580
Hey, Shukkoor...

347
00:18:32,581 --> 00:18:33,580
Yeah...

348
00:18:33,581 --> 00:18:35,220
I didn't even have to fire the gun.

349
00:18:35,221 --> 00:18:36,581
The cops did it
themselves!

350
00:18:37,021 --> 00:18:38,780
- That was so stupid, Cleetus!
- Why?

351
00:18:38,781 --> 00:18:40,300
Didn't you see how much
money we just blew?

352
00:18:40,301 --> 00:18:42,340
- Plus we had to use our brains!
- Exactly!

353
00:18:42,341 --> 00:18:44,221
So what? Isn't it a good thing
I got caught?

354
00:18:44,421 --> 00:18:46,500
Instead, if you had taken
those fake notes to America,

355
00:18:46,501 --> 00:18:48,540
and their cops caught you,
would you ever get out?

356
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:50,461
You should be thanking me!

357
00:18:51,341 --> 00:18:52,500
Cleetus, thank you!

358
00:18:52,501 --> 00:18:53,701
Thank you! Welcome!

359
00:18:54,661 --> 00:18:56,021
Why can't you thank me?

360
00:18:56,461 --> 00:18:57,621
Thank you!

361
00:19:23,101 --> 00:19:24,701
Why is Paappan wobbling like that?

362
00:19:25,301 --> 00:19:26,941
Have you ever seen
Paappan ride straight?

363
00:19:28,701 --> 00:19:30,420
- Oh no! Look! Shajiyettan!
- Shajiyettan!

364
00:19:30,421 --> 00:19:31,260
Oh no!

365
00:19:31,261 --> 00:19:32,740
- Paappan!
- Shajiyettan!

366
00:19:32,741 --> 00:19:34,220
- Oh no!
- Shajiyettan!

367
00:19:34,221 --> 00:19:35,460
Hit the brakes, Abu!

368
00:19:35,461 --> 00:19:37,180
- Over there!
- Get out of the van!

369
00:19:37,181 --> 00:19:38,141
Stop the van, fast!

370
00:19:38,421 --> 00:19:40,340
- Paappan!
- Pull over, Abu!

371
00:19:40,341 --> 00:19:41,661
Seems like Paappan is done for!

372
00:19:59,221 --> 00:20:00,701
Abu, hold me gently!

373
00:20:01,181 --> 00:20:02,621
My eyes suddenly went dark.

374
00:20:02,821 --> 00:20:06,181
Funny… for crooks like you,
you look just like cops.

375
00:20:07,061 --> 00:20:08,260
Who's that?

376
00:20:08,261 --> 00:20:09,421
Paappan!

377
00:20:09,701 --> 00:20:12,421
Everyone bolted the moment
the cops showed up.

378
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:14,140
But I stayed back
and surrendered.

379
00:20:14,141 --> 00:20:16,980
The ones who ran won't have
their photos in tomorrow's papers.

380
00:20:16,981 --> 00:20:20,341
But you and I will be in
tomorrow's papers, Paappan.

381
00:20:21,301 --> 00:20:22,381
How's my brain?

382
00:20:23,541 --> 00:20:26,020
Your brain works overtime
just to stay stupid, Cleetus.

383
00:20:26,021 --> 00:20:27,540
♪ Captain Cleetus ♪

384
00:20:27,541 --> 00:20:28,620
Sir...

385
00:20:28,621 --> 00:20:29,860
So what's the plan now?

386
00:20:29,861 --> 00:20:31,741
Are we going to the hospital first

387
00:20:31,941 --> 00:20:33,781
or straight to the police station?

388
00:20:37,381 --> 00:20:38,541
Phew!

389
00:20:39,181 --> 00:20:40,621
[In Tamil] This charge sheet says

390
00:20:40,781 --> 00:20:42,620
Cleetus printed
counterfeit American dollars

391
00:20:42,621 --> 00:20:45,460
and tried to exchange
them with Donald Trump

392
00:20:45,461 --> 00:20:48,021
during his visit to Coimbatore.

393
00:20:48,181 --> 00:20:50,940
- That's all.
- So, isn't he the prime accused?

394
00:20:50,941 --> 00:20:52,141
Yes, Your Honour.

395
00:20:52,341 --> 00:20:53,980
Usually, Paappan is always
the prime accused.

396
00:20:53,981 --> 00:20:55,741
I'm the prime accused this time?
Thank you!

397
00:20:55,981 --> 00:20:57,741
Is this really the place to brag?

398
00:20:58,421 --> 00:21:00,140
Let them know
it's not only the lawyers,

399
00:21:00,141 --> 00:21:01,181
we've got enough cases too.

400
00:21:01,421 --> 00:21:04,101
While prime accused Cleetus
was being brought to court,

401
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:09,141
Shaji Paappan was arrested for throwing
a crude bomb to help him escape.

402
00:21:09,301 --> 00:21:10,620
He is the second accused.

403
00:21:10,621 --> 00:21:11,941
- Correct?
- Yes, Your Honour.

404
00:21:12,141 --> 00:21:13,261
Yours truly!

405
00:21:14,941 --> 00:21:17,100
Is there no one here
to represent them?

406
00:21:17,101 --> 00:21:18,941
- That--
- I'll argue our case, Your Honour!

407
00:21:19,181 --> 00:21:20,180
Let the arguments begin!

408
00:21:20,181 --> 00:21:22,021
We're ready! Are you?
[TV game show style]

409
00:21:22,141 --> 00:21:23,700
I'll treat you
to parotta and gravy.

410
00:21:23,701 --> 00:21:25,101
Just don't get us
the death penalty!

411
00:21:25,581 --> 00:21:27,101
Relax.
This is a walk in the park!

412
00:21:27,301 --> 00:21:28,661
Hey! What's going on?

413
00:21:29,061 --> 00:21:33,021
Sir, our intelligence team ran
a background check in their hometown.

414
00:21:33,341 --> 00:21:35,500
The locals say these guys
are complete lunatics,

415
00:21:35,501 --> 00:21:38,940
and we'd be even bigger lunatics
for trying to arrest them!

416
00:21:38,941 --> 00:21:40,660
That's why we haven't
arrested anyone.

417
00:21:40,661 --> 00:21:41,861
Sigh!

418
00:21:41,981 --> 00:21:43,261
Hey officer! Come over here!

419
00:21:43,421 --> 00:21:46,340
See? They got scared
as soon as I said I'd argue.

420
00:21:46,341 --> 00:21:47,861
Yeah, I was a bit scared too.

421
00:21:49,861 --> 00:21:52,821
Hey, I suspect this is Kerala
trying to mess with us!

422
00:21:53,021 --> 00:21:55,580
Should we throw these guys
in jail, feed them,

423
00:21:55,581 --> 00:21:57,421
and waste our tax money?

424
00:21:57,541 --> 00:22:01,061
Let the people of Kerala deal
with the mess these guys caused.

425
00:22:01,221 --> 00:22:03,541
Why should we be the ones
to suffer for it?

426
00:22:03,901 --> 00:22:06,660
These guys must pay compensation
for the damage they've caused.

427
00:22:06,661 --> 00:22:08,140
- Got it?
- Sir, but--

428
00:22:08,141 --> 00:22:09,581
No! Don't say a word!

429
00:22:10,341 --> 00:22:11,821
- Shaji Paappan!
- Yes!

430
00:22:12,221 --> 00:22:13,381
Do you know Tamil?

431
00:22:13,501 --> 00:22:15,061
I can't speak it,

432
00:22:15,301 --> 00:22:16,460
but I can't understand it either.

433
00:22:16,461 --> 00:22:17,421
Yes.

434
00:22:17,821 --> 00:22:19,381
Your Honour,
we're starving here.

435
00:22:20,261 --> 00:22:21,461
What do you do for a living?

436
00:22:21,741 --> 00:22:22,820
[in Malayalam]
What is your job?

437
00:22:22,821 --> 00:22:23,941
Tug-of-war!

438
00:22:24,101 --> 00:22:25,141
And I am his tugger!

439
00:22:25,901 --> 00:22:27,021
You call that a job?

440
00:22:28,461 --> 00:22:30,581
Why do I always get
these ridiculous cases?

441
00:22:30,861 --> 00:22:32,061
Just my luck!

442
00:22:32,581 --> 00:22:33,861
I am closing this case.

443
00:22:34,501 --> 00:22:36,061
What about my defence
and legal arguments?

444
00:22:36,461 --> 00:22:37,740
Zip it, you moron!

445
00:22:37,741 --> 00:22:39,780
There are plenty of other states.
You'll get your chance soon.

446
00:22:39,781 --> 00:22:41,061
Much obliged, Your Honour!

447
00:22:41,461 --> 00:22:42,700
- Let's get out of here.
- Paappan! Paappan!

448
00:22:42,701 --> 00:22:43,860
- Wait! Wait!
- Don't go.

449
00:22:43,861 --> 00:22:44,780
Calling from behind?
Bad omen!

450
00:22:44,781 --> 00:22:49,100
[In Tamil] This court orders you
to pay ₹4 lakhs as compensation

451
00:22:49,101 --> 00:22:50,660
for the damages caused by you

452
00:22:50,661 --> 00:22:53,140
to the Police Department
and the Jail Department.

453
00:22:53,141 --> 00:22:54,100
Ah!

454
00:22:54,101 --> 00:22:55,701
That's a fair ruling. Good.

455
00:22:55,941 --> 00:22:57,821
I can contribute
maybe ₹500 myself.

456
00:22:58,061 --> 00:22:59,061
Happy now?

457
00:22:59,221 --> 00:23:00,701
You owe me ₹300, Cleetus.

458
00:23:00,901 --> 00:23:01,861
Oh no!

459
00:23:02,301 --> 00:23:03,500
Silence! Silence!

460
00:23:03,501 --> 00:23:05,900
Everyone here appreciates
your generosity, Paappan!

461
00:23:05,901 --> 00:23:09,020
Sigh! Tell them not to build
a temple for me!

462
00:23:09,021 --> 00:23:10,261
- Paappan!
- My Lord!

463
00:23:10,461 --> 00:23:14,100
People like you would not have existed,
not in this world...

464
00:23:14,101 --> 00:23:16,020
not in any other world
or timeline.

465
00:23:16,021 --> 00:23:18,221
Oh, that's just your
misconception, Your Honour!

466
00:23:18,421 --> 00:23:22,140
I bet there were bigger hustlers
than us back in the old days.

467
00:23:22,141 --> 00:23:23,181
I swear!

468
00:23:23,541 --> 00:23:24,621
Alright then,
see you soon!

469
00:23:36,701 --> 00:23:37,980
Ah, Michael Sir!

470
00:23:37,981 --> 00:23:39,381
Your research
isn't finished yet?

471
00:23:39,781 --> 00:23:41,701
Not yet.
The pre-synopsis is next week.

472
00:23:41,941 --> 00:23:43,421
I'm just adding
the final touches.

473
00:23:50,741 --> 00:23:51,901
Damn it!

474
00:24:31,301 --> 00:24:33,581
The "Royal Tusker's Pearl"
we've chased for ages

475
00:24:33,861 --> 00:24:35,981
finally falls into our hands today.

476
00:24:36,901 --> 00:24:39,101
But how will we trick

477
00:24:39,541 --> 00:24:40,980
the "Ghost of the High Range"

478
00:24:40,981 --> 00:24:42,541
with an empty briefcase?

479
00:24:45,781 --> 00:24:47,021
Come with me.

480
00:24:47,661 --> 00:24:51,581
The moment I got this location,
I deployed a hundred of our men.

481
00:24:52,141 --> 00:24:54,541
And he will be done
and dusted forever!

482
00:25:09,741 --> 00:25:11,181
We've brought the payment
as agreed.

483
00:25:12,461 --> 00:25:13,621
Can we see the stuff?

484
00:25:14,901 --> 00:25:16,061
Finally!

485
00:25:16,461 --> 00:25:19,221
So pleased to meet you, Mr. Ghost.

486
00:25:20,181 --> 00:25:21,941
What's your real name, man?

487
00:25:46,541 --> 00:25:49,180
♪ The burning fire,
The burning fire ♪

488
00:25:49,181 --> 00:25:50,660
Oh my GOD!

489
00:25:50,661 --> 00:25:53,461
♪ The burning fire,
The burning fire ♪

490
00:25:53,741 --> 00:25:57,340
♪ The High Range's highly dangerous
underworld kingpin renowned ♪

491
00:25:57,341 --> 00:26:00,581
♪ Striking like high-voltage
lightning crashing to the ground ♪

492
00:26:00,701 --> 00:26:06,221
♪ Satan Xavier ♪

493
00:26:07,821 --> 00:26:09,700
♪ Satan Xavier ♪

494
00:26:09,701 --> 00:26:12,141
Satan Xavier!

495
00:26:13,741 --> 00:26:14,941
You are damn right.

496
00:26:15,301 --> 00:26:16,261
That's the name.

497
00:26:17,261 --> 00:26:18,301
Hey!

498
00:26:18,861 --> 00:26:20,301
Down! On the table!

499
00:26:23,541 --> 00:26:26,461
I'll forgive the fact
that you sent assassins to kill me.

500
00:26:27,461 --> 00:26:30,141
Trying to trick me
with an empty briefcase...

501
00:26:30,461 --> 00:26:31,621
I'll forgive that too.

502
00:26:32,381 --> 00:26:34,980
But stepping into
my High Range hills

503
00:26:34,981 --> 00:26:37,821
and asking who I am
to my face?

504
00:26:38,101 --> 00:26:39,261
That I won't forgive.

505
00:26:42,581 --> 00:26:44,701
Six-seven!

506
00:26:45,181 --> 00:26:46,980
♪ Satan Xavier ♪

507
00:26:46,981 --> 00:26:52,381
♪ The High Range's highly dangerous
underworld kingpin renowned ♪

508
00:26:53,301 --> 00:26:57,021
That's how I met my Satan sir
for the first time.

509
00:26:58,301 --> 00:26:59,660
When did you see him after that?

510
00:26:59,661 --> 00:27:00,941
I met him many times after that.

511
00:27:01,341 --> 00:27:02,341
And now...

512
00:27:03,101 --> 00:27:05,420
Look at him, huddled in that cloak
like some budget Darth Vader!

513
00:27:05,421 --> 00:27:06,500
He's covered in cobwebs!

514
00:27:06,501 --> 00:27:07,740
- He needs a clean-up!
- Sir...

515
00:27:07,741 --> 00:27:09,220
Sir... it's me, Soman.

516
00:27:09,221 --> 00:27:10,180
- Say something to him.
- Like what?

517
00:27:10,181 --> 00:27:11,900
- Good heavens!
- He's a complete wreck.

518
00:27:11,901 --> 00:27:13,700
Come, let's see if there's
any alcohol here.

519
00:27:13,701 --> 00:27:14,861
- Hey, Simon...
- Yeah?

520
00:27:15,301 --> 00:27:17,460
At this rate,
we'll starve to death.

521
00:27:17,461 --> 00:27:18,661
Oh, Mother of spirits!

522
00:27:18,901 --> 00:27:21,501
Bless the Prime Minister
who gave us demonetisation!

523
00:27:21,781 --> 00:27:22,981
That's not all.

524
00:27:23,101 --> 00:27:27,140
He wanted to become the next Ambani
by printing crores with that money-mint.

525
00:27:27,141 --> 00:27:29,380
The whole underworld found out.
It was so humiliating!

526
00:27:29,381 --> 00:27:30,380
Yeah.

527
00:27:30,381 --> 00:27:32,741
Dude Sir and I
put so much effort into it!

528
00:27:32,861 --> 00:27:34,940
- Who's this "Dude" sir?
- Not Dude, I meant Dad.

529
00:27:34,941 --> 00:27:36,980
- Err...
- Whatever!

530
00:27:36,981 --> 00:27:38,701
Wait, who is this guy?

531
00:27:38,901 --> 00:27:40,181
That's Michael Sir.

532
00:27:40,341 --> 00:27:42,181
- Who's he?
- Xavier sir's cousin.

533
00:27:44,541 --> 00:27:45,741
Take a look at this.

534
00:27:45,981 --> 00:27:47,221
Just look at this, man!

535
00:27:48,101 --> 00:27:49,581
I know you've been feeling low.

536
00:27:51,581 --> 00:27:52,701
Sigh... damn it!

537
00:27:56,581 --> 00:27:57,660
Xavier...

538
00:27:57,661 --> 00:27:59,501
Just trust your cousin.
Please!

539
00:28:01,181 --> 00:28:03,661
This might be the El Dorado
you've been searching for.

540
00:28:04,341 --> 00:28:06,421
Maybe, this could be your greatest quest.

541
00:28:08,661 --> 00:28:09,901
No change at all, huh?

542
00:28:10,141 --> 00:28:11,301
No, Cousin sir.

543
00:28:11,621 --> 00:28:14,621
He's been curled up under
that blanket for five or six months.

544
00:28:16,061 --> 00:28:17,860
Sir, he has high compression.

545
00:28:17,861 --> 00:28:19,180
- Yeah.
- It's depression!

546
00:28:19,181 --> 00:28:20,381
Yeah.

547
00:28:21,221 --> 00:28:22,300
Xavier...

548
00:28:22,301 --> 00:28:23,941
I know a good psychologist.

549
00:28:24,101 --> 00:28:25,421
There's no shame
in getting help.

550
00:28:27,901 --> 00:28:29,181
I'm leaving it here, man.

551
00:28:30,021 --> 00:28:31,261
Just in case...

552
00:29:17,301 --> 00:29:18,421
El Dorado!

553
00:29:19,461 --> 00:29:20,701
Yeah!

554
00:29:22,341 --> 00:29:23,461
Soman!

555
00:29:23,581 --> 00:29:24,781
Simon!

556
00:29:24,901 --> 00:29:27,941
Our good old glory days
are coming back!

557
00:29:32,941 --> 00:29:36,621
[Timeline 3 - A.D. 1790
King Padmanabha's Kingdom]

558
00:30:05,341 --> 00:30:07,780
♪ Vareeth ♪

559
00:30:07,781 --> 00:30:09,141
- Get Kunjukunju here.
- Okay.

560
00:30:13,141 --> 00:30:17,061
♪ Vareeth ♪

561
00:30:20,701 --> 00:30:23,100
♪ Vareeth ♪

562
00:30:23,101 --> 00:30:24,661
I heard you were
seeking me, sir.

563
00:30:25,221 --> 00:30:26,541
Where were you, you idiot?

564
00:30:26,981 --> 00:30:28,501
I was pondering an idea.

565
00:30:28,661 --> 00:30:29,660
Go on then, speak.

566
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:33,461
Why not bring in more men
to finish this bridge sooner?

567
00:30:34,061 --> 00:30:35,181
Indeed.

568
00:30:35,381 --> 00:30:36,740
Bring in more men

569
00:30:36,741 --> 00:30:39,181
when we cannot even pay
the ones we already have!

570
00:30:39,381 --> 00:30:40,581
What a brilliant idea!

571
00:30:42,181 --> 00:30:44,941
I knew you would like it, Master!

572
00:30:46,421 --> 00:30:47,540
What do I even--

573
00:30:47,541 --> 00:30:48,701
Pathetic!

574
00:30:49,261 --> 00:30:51,620
What of my idea
to bring in more men, Master?

575
00:30:51,621 --> 00:30:52,621
Ugh!

576
00:30:53,941 --> 00:30:55,460
- Kunjukunju...
- Yes?

577
00:30:55,461 --> 00:30:56,660
Do you know something?

578
00:30:56,661 --> 00:30:57,780
No.

579
00:30:57,781 --> 00:31:00,301
When I was an engineering student
in London,

580
00:31:00,661 --> 00:31:02,820
the learned Father Victor
once told me this.

581
00:31:02,821 --> 00:31:03,860
What?

582
00:31:03,861 --> 00:31:05,020
Hey Vareeth...

583
00:31:05,021 --> 00:31:06,781
You shall accomplish great feats.

584
00:31:07,261 --> 00:31:08,781
You shall rise to great heights.

585
00:31:09,621 --> 00:31:13,061
But you shall never
find peace in your life.

586
00:31:14,541 --> 00:31:18,380
I remember those words each morning
when I see your face, Kunjukunju.

587
00:31:18,381 --> 00:31:19,300
I see.

588
00:31:19,301 --> 00:31:20,541
- Master...
- Yes?

589
00:31:20,741 --> 00:31:22,820
As the learned Father said,

590
00:31:22,821 --> 00:31:24,981
when you rise to great heights,

591
00:31:25,381 --> 00:31:31,461
by God's grace, we shall both
stand by your side forever.

592
00:31:31,621 --> 00:31:32,741
- Yes.
- Ugh!

593
00:31:32,981 --> 00:31:34,221
Forever? Really?

594
00:31:34,341 --> 00:31:35,540
Yes.

595
00:31:35,541 --> 00:31:36,821
Oh Jesus...

596
00:31:36,981 --> 00:31:39,181
Are my prayers
worth nothing to You?

597
00:31:45,301 --> 00:31:46,941
Water Sahib is coming!

598
00:32:11,141 --> 00:32:12,541
Hey! Hold that bottle straight!

599
00:32:13,261 --> 00:32:15,101
You'll have me out of work.
Move that umbrella!

600
00:32:24,661 --> 00:32:25,700
Good morning!

601
00:32:25,701 --> 00:32:26,781
At noon? Get lost!

602
00:32:28,981 --> 00:32:30,181
Everyone! Hear ye!

603
00:32:30,381 --> 00:32:33,700
To inspect the progress
of the Nagathan bridge works,

604
00:32:33,701 --> 00:32:38,461
here comes the Honourable
District Magistrate, Water Sahib.

605
00:32:39,741 --> 00:32:41,701
My poor back will be
pounded to pulp again today!

606
00:32:52,341 --> 00:32:53,901
Not Water Sahib, you idiots!

607
00:32:55,061 --> 00:32:56,141
Walter!

608
00:33:01,941 --> 00:33:03,221
District Magistrate

609
00:33:03,661 --> 00:33:04,941
Lieutenant Colonel

610
00:33:05,261 --> 00:33:06,981
Walter Joseph!

611
00:33:07,181 --> 00:33:08,301
Do you understand?

612
00:33:15,741 --> 00:33:17,060
Who's that fool
on the other side?

613
00:33:17,061 --> 00:33:18,101
Oh no!

614
00:33:18,221 --> 00:33:19,260
My Master!

615
00:33:19,261 --> 00:33:20,420
Oh no!

616
00:33:20,421 --> 00:33:21,781
- Who is this?
- Doomed!

617
00:33:21,941 --> 00:33:23,981
- My bridge works are doomed!
- And so is my job!

618
00:33:26,621 --> 00:33:27,741
Stupid idiots!

619
00:33:28,221 --> 00:33:29,581
Nobody knows a damn thing.

620
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:31,221
Sahib...

621
00:33:33,421 --> 00:33:34,581
Sir...

622
00:33:34,821 --> 00:33:35,820
What is this?

623
00:33:35,821 --> 00:33:36,901
A native remedy.

624
00:33:37,341 --> 00:33:38,741
Good for all sprains.

625
00:33:38,941 --> 00:33:40,341
- I don't want it.
- Go.

626
00:33:40,621 --> 00:33:42,661
You fell because of me, Sir.

627
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,500
Please have the mercy
to try this remedy.

628
00:33:44,501 --> 00:33:45,581
Give it now.
He'll have it.

629
00:33:58,341 --> 00:33:59,341
Oh no!

630
00:34:00,701 --> 00:34:02,261
- Mr. Vareeth Mappila!
- Sir.

631
00:34:02,621 --> 00:34:04,780
Here is the East India Company's

632
00:34:04,781 --> 00:34:06,941
final instalment for the
bridge construction fund.

633
00:34:07,461 --> 00:34:09,180
Have the funds
from Padmanabhan arrived?

634
00:34:09,181 --> 00:34:10,941
The King will release it
in two days, Sir.

635
00:34:12,661 --> 00:34:13,861
Bloody hell!

636
00:34:16,301 --> 00:34:18,141
Why is Padmanabhan delaying everything?

637
00:34:18,941 --> 00:34:21,821
Word is the Viceroy himself
may attend the inauguration.

638
00:34:22,501 --> 00:34:24,381
I've been a nervous wreck
ever since I heard it.

639
00:34:25,221 --> 00:34:26,540
- Don't delay the work.
- I won't, Sir.

640
00:34:26,541 --> 00:34:27,900
- Don't let me down.
- Never, Sir.

641
00:34:27,901 --> 00:34:29,660
The Viceroy must never regret

642
00:34:29,661 --> 00:34:32,740
appointing this Lieutenant Colonel
Walter Joseph as Magistrate.

643
00:34:32,741 --> 00:34:34,141
No! Certainly not, sir!

644
00:34:34,861 --> 00:34:38,100
The name, Mr. Walter Joseph, must be
remembered for generations.

645
00:34:38,101 --> 00:34:39,380
- No, Sir.
- What?

646
00:34:39,381 --> 00:34:42,061
I mean, it will be remembered
until the end of the world, Sir!

647
00:34:44,541 --> 00:34:47,221
This bridge is my dream, Vareeth.

648
00:34:50,501 --> 00:34:53,061
This bridge is going to
change our fortune forever.

649
00:34:54,381 --> 00:34:55,861
I know it in my heart.

650
00:34:58,221 --> 00:34:59,341
Don't worry, Sir.

651
00:34:59,461 --> 00:35:00,741
The money will be here shortly.

652
00:35:00,941 --> 00:35:04,101
Manager Narayanan Nair has
stepped up tax collection at the market.

653
00:35:05,221 --> 00:35:07,900
A golden opportunity to pay taxes
to the royal treasury!

654
00:35:07,901 --> 00:35:10,061
Merchants, come forth!
This way!

655
00:35:11,301 --> 00:35:13,061
Chathunni, two coins.

656
00:35:13,461 --> 00:35:15,021
Shankunni, one coin.

657
00:35:15,741 --> 00:35:17,581
Look there!
The Royal Manager arrives!

658
00:35:37,461 --> 00:35:39,140
Is the tax collection complete,
Achuthan?

659
00:35:39,141 --> 00:35:40,140
Nearly so, my lord.

660
00:35:40,141 --> 00:35:42,540
Some merchants insist
they cannot pay the tax.

661
00:35:42,541 --> 00:35:43,941
- They cannot?
- Yes, my Lord.

662
00:35:44,701 --> 00:35:48,941
Who are those wretches who claim
they cannot pay the King's tax?

663
00:36:12,941 --> 00:36:15,140
Climbing out of pits?
What are you, an ant-lion?

664
00:36:15,141 --> 00:36:16,140
You call that wit?

665
00:36:16,141 --> 00:36:19,020
Nair, blame no one else
for refusing to pay the taxes.

666
00:36:19,021 --> 00:36:21,581
From this day forth,
none of us will pay.

667
00:36:21,901 --> 00:36:23,261
That is my decree.

668
00:36:23,421 --> 00:36:24,580
Valiya Kelu's decree!

669
00:36:24,581 --> 00:36:26,701
And might I ask
why you refuse to pay?

670
00:36:27,461 --> 00:36:29,460
A merchant who thinks himself
greater than the King?

671
00:36:29,461 --> 00:36:31,701
Hah! Your so-called King!
Shame upon him!

672
00:36:32,141 --> 00:36:33,980
While the whole land starves,

673
00:36:33,981 --> 00:36:37,260
he plunders the poor
in the name of taxes,

674
00:36:37,261 --> 00:36:40,180
while he and his queen alone
wrap themselves in silk

675
00:36:40,181 --> 00:36:43,020
and glitter with gold,
living in luxury!

676
00:36:43,021 --> 00:36:45,341
Aye!
Well said, Master Kelu!

677
00:36:45,581 --> 00:36:48,021
Insolence and treason
in one breath!

678
00:36:48,701 --> 00:36:49,820
Where is my royal sword?

679
00:36:49,821 --> 00:36:51,221
- Take this!
- Oh no!

680
00:36:51,581 --> 00:36:52,700
Got it!

681
00:36:52,701 --> 00:36:53,821
Where am I?

682
00:36:57,221 --> 00:36:59,260
I'm of no Paanan, Parayan,
or Pulayan caste!

683
00:36:59,261 --> 00:37:01,260
- Aren't you from the Nair caste?
- And you are no Emperor!

684
00:37:01,261 --> 00:37:02,941
Shall we partake in some spirits?

685
00:37:03,341 --> 00:37:04,501
Oh no! Huh!

686
00:37:07,821 --> 00:37:09,060
You actually struck me?

687
00:37:09,061 --> 00:37:10,260
Yes.

688
00:37:10,261 --> 00:37:12,221
Your Majesty!

689
00:37:22,941 --> 00:37:27,220
Behold!
Sovereign of the lands and peoples

690
00:37:27,221 --> 00:37:29,781
between Travancore and Greater Kochi,

691
00:37:29,981 --> 00:37:32,900
Emperor and Guardian of the Realm,
Master of the Whip-Blade...

692
00:37:32,901 --> 00:37:36,981
Make way for His Majesty,
Sree Padmanabhan Thampuran!

693
00:38:09,461 --> 00:38:11,660
♪ Grandmaster of the duel,
sovereign of the land ♪

694
00:38:11,661 --> 00:38:13,980
♪ War-dance titan
none may ever withstand ♪

695
00:38:13,981 --> 00:38:16,260
♪ Lord of the realm,
great master of valour ♪

696
00:38:16,261 --> 00:38:18,500
♪ O fearless guardian,
protector of the order ♪

697
00:38:18,501 --> 00:38:20,900
♪ The Infinite One,
Scion of the royal bloodstream ♪

698
00:38:20,901 --> 00:38:23,220
♪ Despot of Empires,
Autocrat Supreme ♪

699
00:38:23,221 --> 00:38:25,500
♪ Monarch of the blade,
king of every crown ♪

700
00:38:25,501 --> 00:38:28,341
♪ Behold the mighty Padmanabha,
great king of renown ♪

701
00:38:29,941 --> 00:38:32,620
♪ O valiant warden,
steadfast and brave ♪

702
00:38:32,621 --> 00:38:33,861
Royal Manager Narayanan...

703
00:38:34,661 --> 00:38:37,421
♪ Padmanabha, the mighty,
lord of the brave ♪

704
00:38:39,581 --> 00:38:42,101
What grave cause
has summoned this gathering?

705
00:38:42,821 --> 00:38:43,900
Are you unaware

706
00:38:43,901 --> 00:38:46,780
that this is the hour when I play
my game of dice with the Queen?

707
00:38:46,781 --> 00:38:48,501
Forgive me, Your Majesty.

708
00:38:49,261 --> 00:38:51,700
Our merchants refuse
to render the tax

709
00:38:51,701 --> 00:38:53,981
Your Majesty has decreed
for the royal treasury.

710
00:38:54,981 --> 00:38:55,900
It is indeed true.

711
00:38:55,901 --> 00:38:58,820
Kelu and his men
laid hands upon me at the market

712
00:38:58,821 --> 00:39:01,500
when I went there in person
to levy Your Majesty's taxes.

713
00:39:01,501 --> 00:39:02,781
Right here... and here.

714
00:39:03,301 --> 00:39:04,500
I was left bruised and broken.

715
00:39:04,501 --> 00:39:05,820
That too is true.

716
00:39:05,821 --> 00:39:07,141
They demand a reduction in taxes?

717
00:39:08,501 --> 00:39:10,700
Tell me, how great a reduction
do they demand?

718
00:39:10,701 --> 00:39:12,061
A total exemption.

719
00:39:13,861 --> 00:39:15,060
A total exemption, you say?

720
00:39:15,061 --> 00:39:16,821
Do not attempt to frighten us
with your sword.

721
00:39:17,181 --> 00:39:19,981
Moreover, we have no intention
of paying taxes from this day forth!

722
00:39:20,301 --> 00:39:21,900
We have collectively
resolved to pledge

723
00:39:21,901 --> 00:39:23,860
our allegiance
to King Kuttan of Kottayam.

724
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:26,620
Reduced to ruin by the tribute
you pay to mighty rulers

725
00:39:26,621 --> 00:39:29,340
such as the Zamorin of Calicut
and the King of Thrissur,

726
00:39:29,341 --> 00:39:33,260
while you live like a pauper within
this thatched hut you call a palace...

727
00:39:33,261 --> 00:39:36,341
We consider it a disgrace to be
living as your subjects, Your Majesty!

728
00:39:36,541 --> 00:39:37,901
Furthermore, we--

729
00:39:38,541 --> 00:39:39,821
One leader will suffice here.

730
00:39:43,781 --> 00:39:45,541
I have already assured Walter Sahib

731
00:39:45,661 --> 00:39:47,700
that the King would settle
the payment in two days.

732
00:39:47,701 --> 00:39:49,100
Who gave you permission
to say that?

733
00:39:49,101 --> 00:39:50,181
Your Majesty!

734
00:39:51,901 --> 00:39:53,381
Have my subjects
grown so audacious

735
00:39:53,701 --> 00:39:55,461
as to question my authority?

736
00:39:57,261 --> 00:40:01,701
In beheading the insolent
who dare defy the throne,

737
00:40:01,821 --> 00:40:05,741
this King Padmanabhan
has always found great delight!

738
00:40:10,541 --> 00:40:13,421
I thought he auctioned off his weapons.
Where did he dig that up from?

739
00:40:15,501 --> 00:40:17,941
- Chop their heads, King!
- Shut up!

740
00:40:19,581 --> 00:40:21,820
♪ Lord of the realm,
great master of valour ♪

741
00:40:21,821 --> 00:40:24,301
♪ O fearless guardian,
protector of the order ♪

742
00:40:35,941 --> 00:40:37,061
Oh no!

743
00:40:37,941 --> 00:40:39,020
Isn't he dead?

744
00:40:39,021 --> 00:40:40,181
Naraya...

745
00:40:42,101 --> 00:40:43,180
Oh no!

746
00:40:43,181 --> 00:40:44,140
Doomed!

747
00:40:44,141 --> 00:40:45,620
My bridge construction
is doomed once more!

748
00:40:45,621 --> 00:40:46,901
Rohini!

749
00:40:47,901 --> 00:40:53,541
♪ Rohini ♪

750
00:40:58,221 --> 00:40:59,381
Rohini!

751
00:40:59,581 --> 00:41:01,181
- My King!
- Oh no!

752
00:41:02,421 --> 00:41:05,781
Rohini, something just struck
the very middle of my spine, my beloved!

753
00:41:05,981 --> 00:41:07,220
I cannot straighten myself.

754
00:41:07,221 --> 00:41:09,061
What has befallen
the King, Chief Physician?

755
00:41:09,181 --> 00:41:10,781
His back has sustained
a grave injury.

756
00:41:11,341 --> 00:41:13,820
- This matter lies beyond my expertise.
- Heavens!

757
00:41:13,821 --> 00:41:16,821
It would be prudent to summon
the Supreme Healer, Aandava Kaimal.

758
00:41:16,941 --> 00:41:18,300
Aandava! (Oh Lord!)

759
00:41:18,301 --> 00:41:19,980
He will not hear you
from this far away.

760
00:41:19,981 --> 00:41:21,381
Silence, you imbecile!

761
00:41:21,701 --> 00:41:23,220
- Who goes there!
- Yes, My Queen!

762
00:41:23,221 --> 00:41:25,380
Dispatch someone to summon
the Supreme Healer Aandava Kaimal!

763
00:41:25,381 --> 00:41:26,060
Yes, My Queen!

764
00:41:26,061 --> 00:41:28,421
It will not do to send
just any fool.

765
00:41:28,901 --> 00:41:31,461
Send a fool we can rely on.

766
00:41:31,581 --> 00:41:34,301
In that case, summon
Koran the Charioteer at once.

767
00:41:35,501 --> 00:41:36,901
- Hey...
- Yes?

768
00:41:37,021 --> 00:41:40,420
You said we would marry
once the sun and rain were gone.

769
00:41:40,421 --> 00:41:43,500
But the sun and rain
have not gone yet, my spring.

770
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,501
Koran!

771
00:41:44,661 --> 00:41:46,021
The King has fallen on his back.

772
00:41:46,621 --> 00:41:48,101
The Queen is summoning you.

773
00:41:48,581 --> 00:41:50,021
I hope the King drops dead!

774
00:41:52,741 --> 00:41:53,781
Oh dear...

775
00:41:55,061 --> 00:41:56,301
- Your Majesty...
- Yes.

776
00:41:56,501 --> 00:41:57,860
Koran the charioteer is here.

777
00:41:57,861 --> 00:41:59,901
Koran… tell… tell…

778
00:42:00,381 --> 00:42:02,180
- Tell what? I just got here!
- Not you!

779
00:42:02,181 --> 00:42:04,181
Tell healer Kaimal
he is needed at once!

780
00:42:04,341 --> 00:42:06,220
As you wish, Your Majesty.

781
00:42:06,221 --> 00:42:08,861
What shall I say if he asks
about Your Majesty's condition?

782
00:42:09,061 --> 00:42:11,460
Just tell him
the King has departed.

783
00:42:11,461 --> 00:42:13,181
- Truly?
- Silence!

784
00:42:13,581 --> 00:42:14,740
Is my end near?

785
00:42:14,741 --> 00:42:15,740
No.

786
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:18,260
Koran, simply tell him
the royal back has broken.

787
00:42:18,261 --> 00:42:20,181
- Huh?!
- Very well. I shall say exactly that.

788
00:42:20,901 --> 00:42:22,580
One more thing, Your Majesty.

789
00:42:22,581 --> 00:42:25,660
Since I must travel through the night
to meet such a distinguished healer,

790
00:42:25,661 --> 00:42:27,300
to explain the gravity
of the situation,

791
00:42:27,301 --> 00:42:28,861
may I be accompanied
by the Queen?

792
00:42:29,141 --> 00:42:30,381
Very well, you may.

793
00:42:30,941 --> 00:42:34,461
You may talk to each other along the road
and come back without going astray.

794
00:42:35,861 --> 00:42:37,021
That will not be necessary!

795
00:42:38,141 --> 00:42:39,261
He will proceed alone.

796
00:42:49,741 --> 00:42:50,980
You ought to have let her
go with him.

797
00:42:50,981 --> 00:42:52,021
Poor fellow!

798
00:43:04,181 --> 00:43:07,421
To preserve my honour
before the British,

799
00:43:07,901 --> 00:43:09,581
I must pay my share
for the bridge.

800
00:43:10,741 --> 00:43:13,901
Between the merchants rebelling
by refusing to pay their taxes,

801
00:43:14,221 --> 00:43:16,021
and the current condition
of my back,

802
00:43:16,941 --> 00:43:18,021
we have no choice

803
00:43:18,221 --> 00:43:20,181
but to unleash
Commander-in-Chief Kurup.

804
00:43:21,141 --> 00:43:22,580
Once Kurup is unleashed,

805
00:43:22,581 --> 00:43:25,500
he will not rest until the marketplace
is drenched in the merchants' blood.

806
00:43:25,501 --> 00:43:26,620
Is such violence necessary?

807
00:43:26,621 --> 00:43:27,620
Yes, yes.

808
00:43:27,621 --> 00:43:28,941
It is absolutely necessary.

809
00:43:29,381 --> 00:43:34,341
I want to witness the tears of those
merchants, especially Valiya Kelu.

810
00:43:36,901 --> 00:43:38,821
Tell Commander-in-Chief
Koma Kurup

811
00:43:39,501 --> 00:43:41,821
to return at once

812
00:43:42,541 --> 00:43:44,461
with Maadan Kandappan's head.

813
00:43:54,741 --> 00:43:56,460
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

814
00:43:56,461 --> 00:43:58,660
♪ Upon his unsheathed steel,
his courage shines bright ♪

815
00:43:58,661 --> 00:44:00,420
♪ Astride the war-cadence,
he lunges through the air ♪

816
00:44:00,421 --> 00:44:02,500
♪ A blazing sun of fire,
with a blinding glare ♪

817
00:44:02,501 --> 00:44:04,220
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

818
00:44:04,221 --> 00:44:06,340
♪ Upon his unsheathed steel,
his courage shines bright ♪

819
00:44:06,341 --> 00:44:08,940
♪ Astride the war-cadence,
he lunges through the air ♪

820
00:44:08,941 --> 00:44:12,581
Salutations to the dwellers of Madanmala
from Commander-in-Chief Koman Kurup.

821
00:44:13,181 --> 00:44:15,821
I have arrived to bring
a final end to your tribulations.

822
00:44:16,101 --> 00:44:18,460
The brigand, Madan Kandappan,

823
00:44:18,461 --> 00:44:20,540
intends to attack our village
once more tonight...

824
00:44:20,541 --> 00:44:22,141
or so my spies have reported.

825
00:44:22,421 --> 00:44:23,780
None of you need to be afraid.

826
00:44:23,781 --> 00:44:25,741
I... I shall cut him to pieces.

827
00:44:26,381 --> 00:44:27,700
This day's sunset

828
00:44:27,701 --> 00:44:29,501
shall be Kandappan's final sunset!

829
00:44:29,941 --> 00:44:31,460
Should I fail,

830
00:44:31,461 --> 00:44:33,340
I swear by the gods of Kalari,

831
00:44:33,341 --> 00:44:35,380
that my two loyal aides
at my left and right

832
00:44:35,381 --> 00:44:37,421
shall lay down their lives

833
00:44:37,621 --> 00:44:40,421
by striking their heads upon
the altar of your guardian deity!

834
00:44:41,261 --> 00:44:42,901
- Count me out!
- Me neither!

835
00:45:03,661 --> 00:45:04,860
Commander-in-Chief...

836
00:45:04,861 --> 00:45:06,381
- It's Kandappan!
- Hmm.

837
00:45:11,101 --> 00:45:16,861
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

838
00:45:19,861 --> 00:45:21,381
Don't eat the dirt,
Commander-in-Chief!

839
00:45:21,581 --> 00:45:23,860
The whole world will know
the palace has run out of food.

840
00:45:23,861 --> 00:45:25,021
Huh?

841
00:45:35,821 --> 00:45:37,541
Commander-in-Chief,
look at his arrogance!

842
00:45:40,261 --> 00:45:41,581
How dare you stare at us!

843
00:45:41,901 --> 00:45:43,100
- Kandappan!
- Kandappan!

844
00:45:43,101 --> 00:45:44,181
Huh!

845
00:45:45,381 --> 00:45:47,141
- Who here is the Commander-in-Chief?
- You.

846
00:45:47,461 --> 00:45:48,581
Right!

847
00:45:48,821 --> 00:45:50,061
Kandappan...

848
00:45:50,581 --> 00:45:51,941
Today you meet your end!

849
00:45:53,821 --> 00:45:55,060
- Huh?
- Huh!

850
00:45:55,061 --> 00:45:56,301
What move is this?

851
00:45:57,421 --> 00:45:58,501
Truly spectacular!

852
00:46:03,701 --> 00:46:05,261
Wait, is he actually dead?

853
00:46:06,341 --> 00:46:08,061
Whom did I dispatch
to the netherworld?

854
00:46:08,501 --> 00:46:09,701
Whose army's banner is that?

855
00:46:33,061 --> 00:46:34,181
Commander-in-Chief...

856
00:46:34,621 --> 00:46:35,741
What is approaching us?

857
00:46:36,301 --> 00:46:37,621
Heavens!

858
00:46:38,021 --> 00:46:39,421
Tipu Sultan's army!

859
00:46:47,941 --> 00:46:50,541
Tipu's Commander-in-Chief,
fresh from conquering the Zamorin...

860
00:46:50,781 --> 00:46:51,941
Azam Khan!

861
00:46:56,541 --> 00:46:59,460
♪ Azam Khan the King,
a lion of might ♪

862
00:46:59,461 --> 00:47:02,181
♪ The valiant knight ♪

863
00:47:03,101 --> 00:47:06,020
♪ Shoulders squared to reach the skies,
Bearing the lamp of justice high ♪

864
00:47:06,021 --> 00:47:08,861
♪ The One of boundless glory
drawing nigh ♪

865
00:47:12,981 --> 00:47:15,860
♪ Azam Khan the King,
a lion of might ♪

866
00:47:15,861 --> 00:47:18,581
♪ The valiant knight ♪

867
00:47:19,581 --> 00:47:22,500
♪ Shoulders squared to reach the skies,
Bearing the lamp of justice high ♪

868
00:47:22,501 --> 00:47:24,901
♪ The One of boundless glory
drawing nigh ♪

869
00:47:29,421 --> 00:47:30,781
Commander-in-Chief Koma Kurup!

870
00:47:31,381 --> 00:47:32,861
What shall be
our next strategic move?

871
00:47:34,381 --> 00:47:35,580
Huh! Oh no!

872
00:47:35,581 --> 00:47:37,260
Commander Kurup!
Commander Kurup!

873
00:47:37,261 --> 00:47:38,500
Did you forget to take
something?

874
00:47:38,501 --> 00:47:40,261
- Shall we come with you?
- Out of my way, you corpse!

875
00:47:40,741 --> 00:47:41,701
Oh no!

876
00:47:43,181 --> 00:47:44,220
Get going!

877
00:47:44,221 --> 00:47:46,340
Commander-in-Chief!
What are we supposed to do?

878
00:47:46,341 --> 00:47:48,421
You stay and fight!
I'll return with reinforcements!

879
00:47:48,781 --> 00:47:50,461
What reinforcements
is he talking about?

880
00:47:50,581 --> 00:47:51,861
We are the reinforcements!

881
00:47:52,061 --> 00:47:53,101
- Lord Padmanabhan!
- Huh!

882
00:47:56,021 --> 00:47:57,301
- Dragon!
- My Lord...

883
00:47:58,861 --> 00:48:01,181
Proclaim that the rightful king
has arrived!

884
00:48:03,421 --> 00:48:05,421
[Praying]

885
00:48:06,621 --> 00:48:07,820
- Dragon!
- My Lord...

886
00:48:07,821 --> 00:48:09,540
Should this kingdom
not know of your Lord's arrival?

887
00:48:09,541 --> 00:48:10,941
Certainly!
They must know, my Lord!

888
00:48:13,101 --> 00:48:14,381
Fire the cannon!

889
00:48:14,541 --> 00:48:15,741
Let the land tremble!

890
00:48:26,821 --> 00:48:28,940
After a crushing setback
in the local body polls,

891
00:48:28,941 --> 00:48:31,780
and staying away from the media
for the past seven days,

892
00:48:31,781 --> 00:48:34,340
Home & PWD Minister
P.P. Shashi

893
00:48:34,341 --> 00:48:37,181
is reportedly arriving shortly
at the Painavu Guest House.

894
00:48:37,621 --> 00:48:38,780
Yes, he's arriving now.

895
00:48:38,781 --> 00:48:42,300
We believe he will finally
address the media today.

896
00:48:42,301 --> 00:48:44,461
That's why the media has gathered here.

897
00:48:48,341 --> 00:48:50,220
♪ Deep in the emerald wild
where the dark woods abide ♪

898
00:48:50,221 --> 00:48:53,300
♪ Raising the revolt's immortal red banner
where raging clouds collide ♪

899
00:48:53,301 --> 00:48:57,860
♪ O Crimson Star who shattered
the chains of slavery; our pride ♪

900
00:48:57,861 --> 00:49:01,580
♪ Red Salute ♪

901
00:49:01,581 --> 00:49:04,541
Aashaan, why have you been avoiding
the press since the election results?

902
00:49:05,221 --> 00:49:08,780
And how do you respond to the opposition's
allegation that you were in hiding?

903
00:49:08,781 --> 00:49:10,060
What is the party's present situation, sir?

904
00:49:10,061 --> 00:49:12,820
As a senior leader,
is fear the reason for your silence

905
00:49:12,821 --> 00:49:16,261
after such a staggering defeat
for your party?

906
00:49:16,461 --> 00:49:17,541
Fear, you say?

907
00:49:17,821 --> 00:49:19,660
After pocketing the welfare pension

908
00:49:19,661 --> 00:49:23,180
and every benefit from the government
and stuffing their bellies,

909
00:49:23,181 --> 00:49:25,140
they shamelessly voted
for someone else!

910
00:49:25,141 --> 00:49:26,260
That's what happened.

911
00:49:26,261 --> 00:49:28,540
This has nothing to do
with fear or failure.

912
00:49:28,541 --> 00:49:30,460
Whose money do you think
tax revenue is?

913
00:49:30,461 --> 00:49:32,220
- It belongs to the public.
- What tax money?

914
00:49:32,221 --> 00:49:35,061
This is all borrowed money,
you... you "presstitute"!

915
00:49:35,221 --> 00:49:37,980
I won't give anyone even a penny now,
even if they're starving!

916
00:49:37,981 --> 00:49:39,020
Not a chance!

917
00:49:39,021 --> 00:49:40,740
It's because they still
have the strength to stand

918
00:49:40,741 --> 00:49:43,261
that they keep changing their vote
whenever they feel like it.

919
00:49:44,941 --> 00:49:46,181
- Hey George...
- Yes.

920
00:49:46,581 --> 00:49:50,060
Invite that annoying reporter
who asked the last question

921
00:49:50,061 --> 00:49:52,901
for an "exclusive interview"
near the dam tonight.

922
00:49:53,301 --> 00:49:54,661
- Done deal, Aashaan.
- Good. Go.

923
00:49:55,181 --> 00:49:56,100
Hey, Hyderali!

924
00:49:56,101 --> 00:49:58,261
The fish at the dam
haven't been fed for a while!

925
00:50:02,941 --> 00:50:04,101
They keep barging in!

926
00:50:04,781 --> 00:50:06,101
They ask whatever they like,

927
00:50:06,381 --> 00:50:08,141
and I must answer
exactly the way they want!

928
00:50:09,381 --> 00:50:10,981
These losers follow me
everywhere I go.

929
00:50:11,781 --> 00:50:12,941
So annoying!

930
00:50:14,341 --> 00:50:15,941
As if I am...

931
00:50:16,221 --> 00:50:17,221
Aashaan!!!

932
00:50:19,461 --> 00:50:20,701
Where did this guy pop up from?

933
00:50:21,221 --> 00:50:22,380
You scared the life out of me!

934
00:50:22,381 --> 00:50:24,181
- Who are you?
- Xavier.

935
00:50:24,301 --> 00:50:25,940
People call me Satan Xavier.

936
00:50:25,941 --> 00:50:27,260
Ah, I know who you are.

937
00:50:27,261 --> 00:50:29,261
You're the one
who owns those estates, right?

938
00:50:29,501 --> 00:50:30,941
What are you doing here?

939
00:50:32,541 --> 00:50:34,540
I prefer a direct approach,
just like you, Aashaan.

940
00:50:34,541 --> 00:50:35,901
That is precisely how I operate.

941
00:50:36,021 --> 00:50:37,501
So I will come
straight to the point.

942
00:50:37,741 --> 00:50:39,301
I need you to do me
a favour, Aashaan.

943
00:50:40,221 --> 00:50:41,901
And there is something
in it for you too.

944
00:50:43,741 --> 00:50:45,501
Consider this a small sample.

945
00:50:46,101 --> 00:50:47,941
It is a diamond, Aashaan.
A genuine diamond.

946
00:50:48,381 --> 00:50:51,541
Do you really think
a diamond is enough to sway me?

947
00:50:52,061 --> 00:50:53,541
No, no, this isn't for you, sir!

948
00:50:53,701 --> 00:50:57,180
I am not foolish enough
to think I can sway you with a bribe!

949
00:50:57,181 --> 00:50:59,901
Even children in Kerala know
you cannot be bought that way.

950
00:51:00,781 --> 00:51:03,300
This stone is for the development
of your High Range hills.

951
00:51:03,301 --> 00:51:05,180
Sell it and it will
fetch a fortune.

952
00:51:05,181 --> 00:51:07,901
That money can go straight
into your High Range development fund.

953
00:51:08,341 --> 00:51:10,901
Don't rely on the bankrupt
government treasury.

954
00:51:13,101 --> 00:51:15,941
If the job gets done, I'll give you
many more stones like this.

955
00:51:16,541 --> 00:51:19,020
The development you could bring
by selling all those diamonds

956
00:51:19,021 --> 00:51:21,341
could turn our High Range
hills into another Bolivia.

957
00:51:21,861 --> 00:51:23,461
Then the people shall hail you

958
00:51:23,941 --> 00:51:27,061
as the "Che Guevara"
of the High Range hills!

959
00:51:31,621 --> 00:51:32,740
Did he stop breathing?

960
00:51:32,741 --> 00:51:34,500
♪ Deep in the emerald wild
where the dark woods abide ♪

961
00:51:34,501 --> 00:51:36,100
♪ Raising the revolt's
immortal red banner ♪

962
00:51:36,101 --> 00:51:40,980
[background score
goes Spanish mode]

963
00:51:40,981 --> 00:51:42,300
♪ O Crimson Star ♪

964
00:51:42,301 --> 00:51:45,140
♪ Red Salute ♪

965
00:51:45,141 --> 00:51:52,221
♪ Saludo Rojo ♪

966
00:51:53,621 --> 00:51:54,900
- Rajesh...
- Yeah?

967
00:51:54,901 --> 00:51:56,421
- Handle this with care, okay?
- Alright.

968
00:51:56,581 --> 00:51:57,941
Don't get caught by anyone.

969
00:51:59,021 --> 00:52:00,461
- Catch you next week.
- See you then.

970
00:52:01,821 --> 00:52:02,940
Yes, sir.

971
00:52:02,941 --> 00:52:04,981
It's definitely Rajesh,
the Urban Naxalite.

972
00:52:05,981 --> 00:52:07,621
He has entered
the building complex, sir.

973
00:52:08,421 --> 00:52:09,621
I'm tailing him closely, sir.

974
00:52:11,621 --> 00:52:12,781
Yeah, fine. And you?

975
00:52:16,301 --> 00:52:17,301
- Hey!
- Hey! Stop there!

976
00:52:22,061 --> 00:52:23,461
- Out of the way!
- Move, move!

977
00:52:30,861 --> 00:52:31,981
Stop there, you!

978
00:52:35,021 --> 00:52:38,180
♪ Left, Right,
Left, Right ♪

979
00:52:38,181 --> 00:52:41,620
♪ If valour ever claimed a name,
If the fight for truth ignites a flame ♪

980
00:52:41,621 --> 00:52:47,140
♪ Who is the man emerging,
drenched in citrus sting? ♪

981
00:52:47,141 --> 00:52:48,421
♪ O Sarbath ♪

982
00:52:49,901 --> 00:52:50,940
♪ O Sarbath ♪

983
00:52:50,941 --> 00:53:03,900
♪ Shameer... Shameer...
O Sarbath Shameer! ♪

984
00:53:03,901 --> 00:53:05,420
♪ Shameer is in town, yeah ♪

985
00:53:05,421 --> 00:53:07,301
♪ Left, Right,
Left, Right ♪

986
00:53:08,301 --> 00:53:09,420
S.K.!

987
00:53:09,421 --> 00:53:10,741
Make it tight.

988
00:53:10,861 --> 00:53:12,741
It's a convention
with nearly a thousand people.

989
00:53:12,861 --> 00:53:14,581
At least a hundred of them
need to go down.

990
00:53:15,021 --> 00:53:16,260
Only a hundred?

991
00:53:16,261 --> 00:53:17,861
- Let's make it 150 then.
- Fine.

992
00:53:23,381 --> 00:53:24,500
- It's Rajesh.
- Okay.

993
00:53:24,501 --> 00:53:26,420
♪ Shameer... Shameer... ♪

994
00:53:26,421 --> 00:53:27,580
Get in!

995
00:53:27,581 --> 00:53:28,660
Good morning, sir.

996
00:53:28,661 --> 00:53:29,821
Good morning.

997
00:53:29,941 --> 00:53:31,020
Oh my God!

998
00:53:31,021 --> 00:53:33,500
Do you think you can trick Sarbath Shameer
by showing extra respect?

999
00:53:33,501 --> 00:53:34,621
Rascal!

1000
00:53:36,421 --> 00:53:37,581
Thomachan...

1001
00:53:37,781 --> 00:53:39,300
Film everything!

1002
00:53:39,301 --> 00:53:40,300
Okay, sir.

1003
00:53:40,301 --> 00:53:41,340
Huh!

1004
00:53:41,341 --> 00:53:43,181
Flattened rice, flowers,
and ghee coconut.

1005
00:53:43,581 --> 00:53:45,501
Are you heading
to Sabarimala Temple, Jesus?

1006
00:53:48,741 --> 00:53:50,781
You've got balls
in all shapes and sizes, old man!

1007
00:53:52,021 --> 00:53:54,501
Even at your age,
you're still itching for action, huh?

1008
00:53:54,701 --> 00:53:55,781
I'll fix that!

1009
00:53:56,861 --> 00:53:57,981
Get over there!

1010
00:54:02,101 --> 00:54:03,421
Sir!
A for "Aashaan"!

1011
00:54:04,741 --> 00:54:06,941
You swapped Apple for "Aashaan,"
didn't you?

1012
00:54:08,141 --> 00:54:09,260
- Dhanaya!
- Sir!

1013
00:54:09,261 --> 00:54:10,421
What on earth is this?

1014
00:54:10,541 --> 00:54:11,901
It's a brilliant plan, sir.

1015
00:54:12,461 --> 00:54:13,781
This right here is "Physics."

1016
00:54:14,621 --> 00:54:16,260
And that over there is "Chemistry."

1017
00:54:16,261 --> 00:54:18,221
And that up there
is "Diplomacy," sir.

1018
00:54:18,341 --> 00:54:19,900
These are nothing but
cunning schemes!

1019
00:54:19,901 --> 00:54:21,460
- Total frauds!
- I'll go and start the vehicle.

1020
00:54:21,461 --> 00:54:23,540
Even if you had spent half
this energy on studies,

1021
00:54:23,541 --> 00:54:25,061
you'd already have
a government job!

1022
00:54:28,261 --> 00:54:29,420
- Dhanaya!
- Yes!

1023
00:54:29,421 --> 00:54:30,580
They didn't laugh!

1024
00:54:30,581 --> 00:54:31,580
- Run! Run! Run!

1025
00:54:31,581 --> 00:54:34,861
Can't you rascals laugh
when sir cracks a joke?

1026
00:54:35,021 --> 00:54:35,981
Huh!

1027
00:54:37,101 --> 00:54:38,620
Sir, they've disappeared!

1028
00:54:38,621 --> 00:54:40,260
- Oh no! Where did they go?
- Who knows!

1029
00:54:40,261 --> 00:54:42,020
Good heavens!
They locked us inside!

1030
00:54:42,021 --> 00:54:44,501
- Why weren't you watching?
- I was learning from you, sir.

1031
00:54:46,941 --> 00:54:49,461
Then why carry a gun
and call yourself a cop?

1032
00:54:49,621 --> 00:54:52,381
You told me not to carry the gun,
so I left it in the police locker.

1033
00:54:52,741 --> 00:54:54,380
Otherwise, I'd have shot them
through the window--

1034
00:54:54,381 --> 00:54:56,181
Just shut up!
You'd have botched it anyway!

1035
00:54:56,941 --> 00:54:58,301
I told you not to take a gun

1036
00:54:58,421 --> 00:55:00,540
because I didn't want civilians
killed by your stray bullets!

1037
00:55:00,541 --> 00:55:01,941
- Oh!
- Did you know?

1038
00:55:02,221 --> 00:55:03,581
After leaving that lodge,

1039
00:55:03,821 --> 00:55:06,821
they drove the police vehicle for fifty
kilometres and fled into the forest.

1040
00:55:06,981 --> 00:55:08,300
Then they removed its battery.

1041
00:55:08,301 --> 00:55:09,981
And punctured
all four tires.

1042
00:55:10,221 --> 00:55:11,260
As if that wasn't enough,

1043
00:55:11,261 --> 00:55:14,300
the video of you being dragged out of that
locked room is now all over social media!

1044
00:55:14,301 --> 00:55:16,541
- Oh no!
- That humiliation is a separate issue.

1045
00:55:17,021 --> 00:55:18,860
What sort of fools are you?

1046
00:55:18,861 --> 00:55:20,941
- We're the best in the High Range, sir!
- Shut up!

1047
00:55:35,221 --> 00:55:36,621
Oh no!
Aashaan!

1048
00:55:36,821 --> 00:55:38,781
He's coming to hand-deliver
my suspension papers!

1049
00:55:39,301 --> 00:55:40,581
I should never get caught.

1050
00:55:46,461 --> 00:55:48,541
Great. Both of you
blocking the way like a dam!

1051
00:55:49,181 --> 00:55:50,700
No wonder
the state treasury is empty!

1052
00:55:50,701 --> 00:55:51,780
Move, move, move!

1053
00:55:51,781 --> 00:55:53,701
- I'll deal with you later!
- Get over here!

1054
00:55:54,101 --> 00:55:55,340
Where is that moron Shameer?

1055
00:55:55,341 --> 00:55:56,621
Shameer was here, sir.

1056
00:55:56,741 --> 00:55:58,220
He was here,
and now he's gone?

1057
00:55:58,221 --> 00:55:59,340
- Go find him now!
- Sir!

1058
00:55:59,341 --> 00:56:02,181
The moment I step into his station,
I start itching.

1059
00:56:02,581 --> 00:56:03,780
Hey Shameer...

1060
00:56:03,781 --> 00:56:04,901
Yeah!

1061
00:56:06,141 --> 00:56:08,221
♪ If valour ever claimed a name ♪

1062
00:56:08,341 --> 00:56:09,901
Are you busy, Shameer sir?

1063
00:56:10,141 --> 00:56:12,621
I was looking for
something I lost yesterday.

1064
00:56:12,861 --> 00:56:14,740
If that something is your brain,
don't bother.

1065
00:56:14,741 --> 00:56:15,901
You won't find it.

1066
00:56:16,421 --> 00:56:19,140
Even if you had just whistled,
I'd have come running.

1067
00:56:19,141 --> 00:56:21,500
Whistle or shout,

1068
00:56:21,501 --> 00:56:24,500
how could you reach me
while you were locked in by Naxalites?

1069
00:56:24,501 --> 00:56:26,420
- Well, then I--
- Stop!

1070
00:56:26,421 --> 00:56:28,221
If you open your mouth,
I'll change my mind.

1071
00:56:28,501 --> 00:56:29,980
So keep your mouth shut

1072
00:56:29,981 --> 00:56:31,941
and just listen to me.

1073
00:56:32,621 --> 00:56:33,741
Shameer...

1074
00:56:33,981 --> 00:56:35,981
I need you
to do something for me.

1075
00:56:36,541 --> 00:56:38,141
No one else should know.

1076
00:56:38,701 --> 00:56:40,221
It must be strictly confidential!

1077
00:56:40,581 --> 00:56:41,981
For you, Aashaan,
I would--

1078
00:56:42,381 --> 00:56:43,460
I've seen this quite a lot.

1079
00:56:43,461 --> 00:56:44,700
No need to fall
at my feet.

1080
00:56:44,701 --> 00:56:45,821
Just get the job done.

1081
00:56:45,941 --> 00:56:47,180
Consider it done.

1082
00:56:47,181 --> 00:56:48,901
Your humble slave
will do it, Aashaan.

1083
00:56:49,421 --> 00:56:50,461
Otherwise,

1084
00:56:50,861 --> 00:56:55,541
your cap and your head will end up
on my desk again as paperweights!

1085
00:56:59,221 --> 00:57:00,100
Stay still. Hold.

1086
00:57:00,101 --> 00:57:02,661
Hey! Show a little of your brother
Moonga's energy!

1087
00:57:03,821 --> 00:57:05,620
Are you trying
to yank my spine out?

1088
00:57:05,621 --> 00:57:07,660
We might have to pour
some concrete into that spine, Paappan.

1089
00:57:07,661 --> 00:57:09,020
- Shajiyetta!
- Yeah, and then bury you in it.

1090
00:57:09,021 --> 00:57:10,421
Shajiyetta, look!
Your mom's here!

1091
00:57:10,701 --> 00:57:12,420
- Mom?
- And she's brought your Stella with her!

1092
00:57:12,421 --> 00:57:13,420
- Huh?
- Good heavens!

1093
00:57:13,421 --> 00:57:15,061
♪ No, Paappan ♪

1094
00:57:15,461 --> 00:57:17,060
♪ She'll ditch you, Paappan ♪

1095
00:57:17,061 --> 00:57:18,580
- Oh, Stella...
- ♪ No, Paappan ♪

1096
00:57:18,581 --> 00:57:20,740
♪ You'll be in deep trouble, Paappan ♪

1097
00:57:20,741 --> 00:57:22,260
- Please wait for five minutes.
- Okay.

1098
00:57:22,261 --> 00:57:24,220
♪ You'll be in deep trouble, Paappan ♪

1099
00:57:24,221 --> 00:57:25,501
Mom, I was just about to--

1100
00:57:25,781 --> 00:57:27,581
I didn't come here
to speak with you.

1101
00:57:28,021 --> 00:57:30,781
I only came because she said
she had something to tell you.

1102
00:57:30,941 --> 00:57:32,141
- Go on, tell him.
- Okay.

1103
00:57:35,461 --> 00:57:38,060
I'm not staying away because
Mom doesn't let me enter the house.

1104
00:57:38,061 --> 00:57:39,981
He's staying away because
she's always home.

1105
00:57:42,501 --> 00:57:44,341
Don't I know how things are, Paappan?

1106
00:57:45,501 --> 00:57:47,781
I got a marriage proposal
from Erattupetta last month.

1107
00:57:48,341 --> 00:57:49,940
My father is going
to fix the marriage.

1108
00:57:49,941 --> 00:57:50,740
Oh no!

1109
00:57:50,741 --> 00:57:53,101
Since you never gave me
a solid promise...

1110
00:57:53,821 --> 00:57:55,141
I said yes.

1111
00:57:55,621 --> 00:57:56,820
So sad!

1112
00:57:56,821 --> 00:57:57,981
So that's gone too!

1113
00:57:58,421 --> 00:58:01,420
We're still rejoicing
over Paappan's house being seized!

1114
00:58:01,421 --> 00:58:03,060
Don't talk to us
so heartlessly!

1115
00:58:03,061 --> 00:58:04,181
Ugh, this guy!

1116
00:58:04,461 --> 00:58:06,181
- Captain!
- Did I say anything wrong?

1117
00:58:07,021 --> 00:58:08,420
Alright then, Paappan.

1118
00:58:08,421 --> 00:58:10,620
- Hope I'll see you again somewhere.
- Okay, bye. See you.

1119
00:58:10,621 --> 00:58:11,660
- Aunty...
- Yes?

1120
00:58:11,661 --> 00:58:12,740
Let's leave.

1121
00:58:12,741 --> 00:58:15,420
Why should I waste my time
being around these losers anyway!

1122
00:58:15,421 --> 00:58:16,701
Come, let's get out of here.

1123
00:58:18,621 --> 00:58:19,981
What will you do now, Shajiyetta?

1124
00:58:22,341 --> 00:58:23,661
What can I do now?

1125
00:58:23,981 --> 00:58:25,381
I'll just pray to God

1126
00:58:25,741 --> 00:58:27,301
not to give her
a happy married life.

1127
00:58:27,821 --> 00:58:28,901
Huh?!

1128
00:58:30,061 --> 00:58:31,301
Mom!

1129
00:58:32,381 --> 00:58:33,900
- What now?
- Just hold on a second.

1130
00:58:33,901 --> 00:58:35,220
- Did he feel bad?
- Yeah.

1131
00:58:35,221 --> 00:58:36,261
Err...

1132
00:58:37,141 --> 00:58:39,861
Your marriage is fixed, right?
You carry on. Let me talk to mom.

1133
00:58:40,941 --> 00:58:42,061
What is it now?

1134
00:58:42,421 --> 00:58:43,941
I've been meaning to visit you.

1135
00:58:44,421 --> 00:58:45,621
Why?

1136
00:58:46,781 --> 00:58:47,941
Happy Birthday!

1137
00:58:49,421 --> 00:58:50,661
Well...

1138
00:58:52,701 --> 00:58:53,940
I don't have a gift for you.

1139
00:58:53,941 --> 00:58:55,101
I'm completely broke.

1140
00:58:59,661 --> 00:59:00,980
Oh, my son...

1141
00:59:00,981 --> 00:59:02,100
This is all I have.

1142
00:59:02,101 --> 00:59:03,181
Okay.

1143
00:59:04,901 --> 00:59:06,061
Shaji, my son!

1144
00:59:06,221 --> 00:59:07,981
What would I ever do
without you, old lady?

1145
00:59:09,101 --> 00:59:10,180
Aww!

1146
00:59:10,181 --> 00:59:11,980
- Cute mom and son.
- Yes.

1147
00:59:11,981 --> 00:59:13,621
Like Baby Jesus and Mother Mary!

1148
00:59:16,341 --> 00:59:18,421
Mark my words.
You'll make it big!

1149
00:59:19,741 --> 00:59:21,140
- Shall I leave?
- Yes.

1150
00:59:21,141 --> 00:59:22,860
This scene would move
anyone to tears.

1151
00:59:22,861 --> 00:59:24,021
True!

1152
00:59:29,501 --> 00:59:30,340
Let it go, man.

1153
00:59:30,341 --> 00:59:31,300
- Hey...
- Yeah?

1154
00:59:31,301 --> 00:59:34,020
Didn’t you say the rent
for our new club was overdue?

1155
00:59:34,021 --> 00:59:35,420
It’s been due for a while now.

1156
00:59:35,421 --> 00:59:36,620
We'll settle that today.

1157
00:59:36,621 --> 00:59:37,940
- Huh?
- How exactly?

1158
00:59:37,941 --> 00:59:39,141
I have my ways.
Just watch.

1159
00:59:40,701 --> 00:59:41,821
Shaji, my son...

1160
00:59:42,181 --> 00:59:43,300
Come over here a second.

1161
00:59:43,301 --> 00:59:44,500
She's calling you!

1162
00:59:44,501 --> 00:59:46,900
- What is it, Mom?
- Come, we might get something too.

1163
00:59:46,901 --> 00:59:48,061
- What is it?
- Son...

1164
00:59:48,181 --> 00:59:51,181
Mom forgot to give
one little thing to you.

1165
00:59:52,341 --> 00:59:53,620
- What?
- This right here!

1166
00:59:53,621 --> 00:59:54,701
Yikes!

1167
00:59:55,221 --> 00:59:56,260
Give me my necklace!

1168
00:59:56,261 --> 00:59:58,100
What... nec... nec... necklace?

1169
00:59:58,101 --> 01:00:00,300
Not "What... nec... nec... necklace!"

1170
01:00:00,301 --> 01:00:01,900
I'm asking you to return
my necklace!

1171
01:00:01,901 --> 01:00:03,220
The moment you kissed me,

1172
01:00:03,221 --> 01:00:05,660
I knew you’d at least
try to steal a kidney.

1173
01:00:05,661 --> 01:00:08,180
- Give it back!
- Why does the hen need eggs?

1174
01:00:08,181 --> 01:00:09,700
- What?
- No, I thought...

1175
01:00:09,701 --> 01:00:12,540
I'd keep it safely
so you wouldn't pawn it off.

1176
01:00:12,541 --> 01:00:14,180
Oh, shut up and give it back!

1177
01:00:14,181 --> 01:00:15,381
Hand it over!

1178
01:00:18,101 --> 01:00:19,660
Listen, girl!

1179
01:00:19,661 --> 01:00:21,460
You’re better off marrying
someone else, sweetie.

1180
01:00:21,461 --> 01:00:24,181
Or else he'll strip you
of everything you own!

1181
01:00:24,541 --> 01:00:25,541
Get in.

1182
01:00:26,981 --> 01:00:28,141
- Shall we go?
- Paappan...

1183
01:00:28,381 --> 01:00:30,061
So, what about
the unpaid club rent?

1184
01:00:30,541 --> 01:00:31,820
Well, it’s back to being overdue.

1185
01:00:31,821 --> 01:00:33,581
Anyway, your luck
is at an all-time low.

1186
01:00:33,941 --> 01:00:36,861
Lost the girl, got caught during
a robbery and got thrashed!

1187
01:00:37,381 --> 01:00:38,741
Who knows
what calamity awaits next!

1188
01:00:39,181 --> 01:00:41,020
Why don't we consult that Babaji?

1189
01:00:41,021 --> 01:00:42,260
Which Pav Bhaji?

1190
01:00:42,261 --> 01:00:43,940
Not Pav Bhaji.
Let's go to Raman Panicker.

1191
01:00:43,941 --> 01:00:46,020
You mean that dark sorcerer,
Chudala Raman?

1192
01:00:46,021 --> 01:00:48,380
He's no sorcerer.
He's a top-tier wizard!

1193
01:00:48,381 --> 01:00:49,461
Hey, move aside.

1194
01:00:49,621 --> 01:00:50,941
A sorcerer will be perfect.

1195
01:00:51,221 --> 01:00:53,620
If he ties Paappan down
and hammers a nail into his skull,

1196
01:00:53,621 --> 01:00:55,020
everything will be solved!

1197
01:00:55,021 --> 01:00:56,460
Pick up a six-inch nail
on the way there.

1198
01:00:56,461 --> 01:00:57,820
And drive it
right into his mouth!

1199
01:00:57,821 --> 01:00:59,140
We can settle
for three inches too!

1200
01:00:59,141 --> 01:01:03,340
A threat over our heads!

1201
01:01:03,341 --> 01:01:05,421
The bridge called Nagathan!

1202
01:01:05,941 --> 01:01:07,140
- Sir...
- Yes?

1203
01:01:07,141 --> 01:01:09,301
We've all seen
the Nagathan bridge.

1204
01:01:09,541 --> 01:01:11,741
Why demolish
a perfectly good bridge, sir?

1205
01:01:12,101 --> 01:01:14,540
Did you shake the bridge
to see if it was weak?

1206
01:01:14,541 --> 01:01:16,661
- No, sir.
- Well, Aashaan did!

1207
01:01:17,061 --> 01:01:20,020
If Aashaan says it's weak,
we demolish it.

1208
01:01:20,021 --> 01:01:21,100
- Sir...
- Yes?

1209
01:01:21,101 --> 01:01:22,820
The one leading the slogans
at the front...

1210
01:01:22,821 --> 01:01:24,901
Isn't that Kokkachi Kareem
who got bail last week?

1211
01:01:25,221 --> 01:01:28,300
Then what? Should they bring Chachaji
instead of Kokkachi to raise slogans here?

1212
01:01:28,301 --> 01:01:29,261
Zip it!

1213
01:01:32,941 --> 01:01:36,860
Long live the people's protest!

1214
01:01:36,861 --> 01:01:39,340
In these terrible times!

1215
01:01:39,341 --> 01:01:42,381
A threat over our heads!

1216
01:01:42,541 --> 01:01:43,500
[Josettan's Tea Shop]

1217
01:01:43,501 --> 01:01:44,661
Hand me that newspaper.

1218
01:01:45,501 --> 01:01:46,420
Here you go, Paappan.

1219
01:01:46,421 --> 01:01:48,580
Come on, Paappan,
what's wrong with what I said?

1220
01:01:48,581 --> 01:01:49,780
Just give it a rest, will you?

1221
01:01:49,781 --> 01:01:51,461
Nothing's wrong.
Go on, Kunjikka.

1222
01:01:51,701 --> 01:01:53,421
You think the scrap business
is a bad idea?

1223
01:01:54,101 --> 01:01:55,461
You'll be rolling in millions!

1224
01:01:56,021 --> 01:01:59,860
And you already have the perfect property
to start your scrap business.

1225
01:01:59,861 --> 01:02:01,460
Why don't we
kick things off with that?

1226
01:02:01,461 --> 01:02:03,140
I'm not selling Cleetus
for scrap!

1227
01:02:03,141 --> 01:02:04,820
No! I'm not talking about Cleetus!

1228
01:02:04,821 --> 01:02:06,061
I'm talking about your van!

1229
01:02:07,021 --> 01:02:09,460
Even Mammootty offered to buy this van,
and we turned him down.

1230
01:02:09,461 --> 01:02:11,221
And you think we'd sell it
to you, Kunjikka?

1231
01:02:12,181 --> 01:02:13,700
Are you trying to kill me
before my time?

1232
01:02:13,701 --> 01:02:16,060
Well, just think about the van
and let me know.

1233
01:02:16,061 --> 01:02:17,020
Fine, I'll think about it.

1234
01:02:17,021 --> 01:02:18,340
- Tea's on me.
- No, no!

1235
01:02:18,341 --> 01:02:19,380
You may go.
I'll pay.

1236
01:02:19,381 --> 01:02:20,420
I'll keep in touch then.

1237
01:02:20,421 --> 01:02:21,621
- Sure thing.
- Alright then.

1238
01:02:22,781 --> 01:02:24,060
About the van--

1239
01:02:24,061 --> 01:02:25,341
Enough about the van.
Just get your butt moving!

1240
01:02:26,501 --> 01:02:27,741
Hey! Stop right there!

1241
01:02:29,861 --> 01:02:31,660
Where do you think you're going
without paying?

1242
01:02:31,661 --> 01:02:32,900
You're asking us
where we're going?

1243
01:02:32,901 --> 01:02:34,780
Even your dad
wouldn't dare ask that!

1244
01:02:34,781 --> 01:02:36,500
He might not.
But I will. Pay up!

1245
01:02:36,501 --> 01:02:37,581
Hey!

1246
01:02:46,181 --> 01:02:47,301
You little brat...

1247
01:02:47,701 --> 01:02:49,901
While you were still running through your
dad's veins, I was running the show here!

1248
01:02:50,861 --> 01:02:52,061
Do you know who I am?

1249
01:02:52,821 --> 01:02:54,020
No.

1250
01:02:54,021 --> 01:02:55,221
Paappan.

1251
01:02:57,341 --> 01:02:58,540
Shaji Paappan!

1252
01:02:58,541 --> 01:03:00,581
Oh! So you are Shaji Paappan!

1253
01:03:00,821 --> 01:03:02,220
Wait a minute!

1254
01:03:02,221 --> 01:03:03,500
Just a minute.

1255
01:03:03,501 --> 01:03:04,580
Ah!

1256
01:03:04,581 --> 01:03:06,020
You owe us ₹8500.

1257
01:03:06,021 --> 01:03:07,421
Leave only after
paying the money!

1258
01:03:08,301 --> 01:03:10,500
You show the debt book
to anyone who says their name?

1259
01:03:10,501 --> 01:03:12,580
This isn't a joke book.
It's the debt book.

1260
01:03:12,581 --> 01:03:13,781
Pay up!

1261
01:03:14,141 --> 01:03:15,660
Where would I go
without paying you, dear?

1262
01:03:15,661 --> 01:03:16,741
- Paappan!
- I'll pay up.

1263
01:03:17,301 --> 01:03:18,380
Yeah!

1264
01:03:18,381 --> 01:03:19,941
I'll leave and never
come back. Okay?

1265
01:03:21,381 --> 01:03:24,141
- You! I'll send your middle stump flying--
- Hey!

1266
01:03:24,461 --> 01:03:25,980
If you dare to touch my boy...

1267
01:03:25,981 --> 01:03:27,020
Get moving, you pest!

1268
01:03:27,021 --> 01:03:28,340
Convey my regards to your dad!

1269
01:03:28,341 --> 01:03:30,060
- Who'll pay a year's bill?
- Not me!

1270
01:03:30,061 --> 01:03:31,140
Were you busy, Paappan?

1271
01:03:31,141 --> 01:03:32,821
Yeah, busy doing nothing.
What's up?

1272
01:03:33,661 --> 01:03:36,020
It's this classic Paappan humour
we need for the closing speech.

1273
01:03:36,021 --> 01:03:37,060
A closing speech?

1274
01:03:37,061 --> 01:03:38,340
Yes, the vote of thanks.

1275
01:03:38,341 --> 01:03:42,100
Paappan, the Village Council is holding
a cultural summit on the 17th.

1276
01:03:42,101 --> 01:03:43,621
See that flex board there?

1277
01:03:43,781 --> 01:03:46,460
As part of the event, we'll honour
many personalities from our village,

1278
01:03:46,461 --> 01:03:49,500
who've made significant
contributions in various fields.

1279
01:03:49,501 --> 01:03:52,421
And how could we ever forget
your legendary contribution to Tug-of-War?

1280
01:03:53,141 --> 01:03:56,301
You must definitely attend the ceremony
and accept this honour, Paappan.

1281
01:03:56,941 --> 01:03:57,941
You'll come, right?

1282
01:03:58,381 --> 01:03:59,420
Is there any payment?

1283
01:03:59,421 --> 01:04:01,541
What you're getting
is far more precious than money.

1284
01:04:02,141 --> 01:04:03,220
Must be diamonds.

1285
01:04:03,221 --> 01:04:04,380
I'm not sharing it with you.

1286
01:04:04,381 --> 01:04:05,701
- A ceremonial shawl.
- Huh?!

1287
01:04:05,901 --> 01:04:06,901
Say what?!

1288
01:04:07,181 --> 01:04:08,860
Why did your face fall
when I said ceremonial shawl?

1289
01:04:08,861 --> 01:04:09,940
Don't you remember?

1290
01:04:09,941 --> 01:04:12,260
Didn't we honour you
with a ceremonial shawl

1291
01:04:12,261 --> 01:04:13,900
at the last community wedding?

1292
01:04:13,901 --> 01:04:14,980
One more thing, Paappan...

1293
01:04:14,981 --> 01:04:17,860
I've put your name down
for a ₹500 donation for the event.

1294
01:04:17,861 --> 01:04:19,060
I'll collect the cash later.

1295
01:04:19,061 --> 01:04:22,021
At least pay for the 50-rupee
shawl yourself, you cheapskates!

1296
01:04:23,661 --> 01:04:25,260
This is the classic Paappan humour!

1297
01:04:25,261 --> 01:04:26,380
That's Paappan's pressure point!

1298
01:04:26,381 --> 01:04:27,300
Now get out of here.
I'll pay up.

1299
01:04:27,301 --> 01:04:28,420
See you at the event!

1300
01:04:28,421 --> 01:04:30,421
Man, these guys deserve
to be the ministers here.

1301
01:04:31,781 --> 01:04:34,581
By the way, when did actor Mammootty
offer to buy our van?

1302
01:04:34,901 --> 01:04:35,900
When did he say that?

1303
01:04:35,901 --> 01:04:37,460
Weren't you the one
blabbering about it back there?

1304
01:04:37,461 --> 01:04:39,981
Some higher power makes
me say those things, Paappan!

1305
01:04:40,421 --> 01:04:42,861
Then tell your "higher power"
to tone it down a little.

1306
01:04:43,421 --> 01:04:44,660
Shajiyett!

1307
01:04:44,661 --> 01:04:46,060
Paappan!
Oi!

1308
01:04:46,061 --> 01:04:48,981
Today is our appointment with the
astrologer, Raman Panicker. Let's go.

1309
01:04:49,101 --> 01:04:50,500
Fine, sorcerer or whatever.
Let's go.

1310
01:04:50,501 --> 01:04:51,980
Is our luck really
that bad, Paappan?

1311
01:04:51,981 --> 01:04:54,420
Trust me,
the worst is yet to come!

1312
01:04:54,421 --> 01:04:55,381
Come.

1313
01:04:56,381 --> 01:04:58,100
If this involves a lot of hiking,
count me out.

1314
01:04:58,101 --> 01:05:00,820
It's not far, dude. We just have
get past this hill to find him.

1315
01:05:00,821 --> 01:05:02,020
Does anything he says
ever work?

1316
01:05:02,021 --> 01:05:04,181
Clearly! Why else would we be
"working" our way up this hill?

1317
01:05:04,461 --> 01:05:06,340
Look, I see someone
who looks human over there.

1318
01:05:06,341 --> 01:05:08,021
Obviously.
Did you think this was a zoo?

1319
01:05:09,301 --> 01:05:10,820
Why is that fellow
sitting like that?

1320
01:05:10,821 --> 01:05:12,060
He's meditating.

1321
01:05:12,061 --> 01:05:13,500
Oh, then he must be a Christian.

1322
01:05:13,501 --> 01:05:14,700
Shut up, Paappan!

1323
01:05:14,701 --> 01:05:16,261
How do we let him know we're here?

1324
01:05:16,781 --> 01:05:18,980
What's with all these chickens?
Is this some barbecue joint?

1325
01:05:18,981 --> 01:05:20,061
- I'm hungry.
- Yeah.

1326
01:05:20,781 --> 01:05:22,420
He has made fried chickens fly.

1327
01:05:22,421 --> 01:05:24,660
So did he tie them up now
so they wouldn't fly away?

1328
01:05:24,661 --> 01:05:26,181
Ugh!
He actually did it!

1329
01:05:28,821 --> 01:05:29,981
Panicker...

1330
01:05:30,381 --> 01:05:31,500
Has he departed?

1331
01:05:31,501 --> 01:05:33,261
Panicker! Oi!

1332
01:05:33,421 --> 01:05:34,780
Keep your voice down, Captain!

1333
01:05:34,781 --> 01:05:35,981
See, he has opened his eyes.

1334
01:05:38,261 --> 01:05:39,860
The one burdened with sorrow,
step forward.

1335
01:05:39,861 --> 01:05:40,700
- I'm ready.
- Move, man.

1336
01:05:40,701 --> 01:05:41,781
Make way, boys.

1337
01:05:42,861 --> 01:05:44,620
The elder of the group,
step forward and be seated.

1338
01:05:44,621 --> 01:05:46,180
Believe it or not,
you look like a senior citizen.

1339
01:05:46,181 --> 01:05:47,621
- He meant you, Shajiyettan.
- Huh!?

1340
01:05:47,901 --> 01:05:49,060
Go ahead, Shajiyettan.

1341
01:05:49,061 --> 01:05:50,460
He thought it was
a walking stick.

1342
01:05:50,461 --> 01:05:51,460
Sit in the bare state.

1343
01:05:51,461 --> 01:05:53,020
- Oh, do I have to strip bare now?
- What are you doing?!

1344
01:05:53,021 --> 01:05:53,981
Hey!

1345
01:05:54,221 --> 01:05:55,460
Just take off
your sandals and sit!

1346
01:05:55,461 --> 01:05:56,580
Oh, is that how you say that?

1347
01:05:56,581 --> 01:05:59,180
Can't you at least
get a couple of chairs on EMI?

1348
01:05:59,181 --> 01:06:00,380
Oh boy...

1349
01:06:00,381 --> 01:06:02,061
Don't sit like you're about
to take a dump. Sit properly.

1350
01:06:03,141 --> 01:06:05,021
Even while burdened
with so many troubles,

1351
01:06:05,221 --> 01:06:06,981
you still don't truly
believe in this, do you?

1352
01:06:07,181 --> 01:06:09,781
Our Old Testament warns that
the Lord will destroy the superstitious.

1353
01:06:10,901 --> 01:06:13,141
And yet, fate has brought you
before me.

1354
01:06:13,461 --> 01:06:15,381
So now, sit in silence.

1355
01:06:16,101 --> 01:06:17,260
- Sit silently.
- Captain!

1356
01:06:17,261 --> 01:06:18,421
Silence!

1357
01:06:18,661 --> 01:06:23,101
[chanting]

1358
01:06:25,221 --> 01:06:26,540
Look at him laying out
those Skibidis.

1359
01:06:26,541 --> 01:06:27,540
It's Kavadi (Cowrie shells).

1360
01:06:27,541 --> 01:06:28,661
Oh, that's
what they're called?

1361
01:06:28,781 --> 01:06:32,341
[continues chanting]

1362
01:06:40,941 --> 01:06:42,900
I've made my move.

1363
01:06:42,901 --> 01:06:44,461
It's your turn now, Sorcerer.

1364
01:06:44,981 --> 01:06:46,140
Huh!

1365
01:06:46,141 --> 01:06:47,140
Hey!

1366
01:06:47,141 --> 01:06:49,581
- This is your problem!
- Oh, did I move it to the wrong spot?

1367
01:06:49,701 --> 01:06:50,740
You're too impulsive!

1368
01:06:50,741 --> 01:06:52,021
Yeah, I knew that!

1369
01:06:52,221 --> 01:06:53,500
You must be more
careful when you play.

1370
01:06:53,501 --> 01:06:54,580
- You just lost a pawn!
- Stop it!

1371
01:06:54,581 --> 01:06:56,701
The path of the religious man
is the best!

1372
01:06:56,861 --> 01:06:58,500
Huh? What language is this?

1373
01:06:58,501 --> 01:06:59,461
It's Greek.

1374
01:06:59,581 --> 01:07:01,700
- How are we supposed to follow this?
- You will follow soon enough.

1375
01:07:01,701 --> 01:07:02,740
Look at him.

1376
01:07:02,741 --> 01:07:04,901
Lord Ayyappa! I'll offer you
genuine golden plates!

1377
01:07:07,701 --> 01:07:08,861
Shaji Paappan!

1378
01:07:08,981 --> 01:07:10,101
What is it?

1379
01:07:11,861 --> 01:07:13,421
You will ride
into battle on horseback,

1380
01:07:14,581 --> 01:07:15,981
like a king.

1381
01:07:17,461 --> 01:07:18,740
With his sprained back?

1382
01:07:18,741 --> 01:07:20,981
- Ruined it!
- Paappan has always been our King.

1383
01:07:21,221 --> 01:07:24,021
He'll arrive on horseback.
Sometimes he'll even arrive on a donkey.

1384
01:07:26,021 --> 01:07:27,821
Haven't you witnessed
such visions before?

1385
01:07:34,301 --> 01:07:36,101
I have.
I have.

1386
01:07:38,261 --> 01:07:40,301
A great battle
is about to unfold.

1387
01:07:46,301 --> 01:07:48,660
Your companions will perish
in the middle of that battle.

1388
01:07:48,661 --> 01:07:50,141
- Huh?
- Huh!

1389
01:07:52,541 --> 01:07:53,621
From then on,

1390
01:07:53,901 --> 01:07:55,821
you will have to fight
all by yourself, Paappan.

1391
01:08:10,261 --> 01:08:12,261
Do you not see
the cosmos aligning?

1392
01:08:13,581 --> 01:08:16,381
Gateways to unknown realms
are about to open.

1393
01:08:16,941 --> 01:08:19,701
The time for you
to fight is drawing near.

1394
01:08:20,821 --> 01:08:23,821
The very survival of this world
rests upon your victory.

1395
01:08:24,541 --> 01:08:25,980
You need not pay me.

1396
01:08:25,981 --> 01:08:27,101
You may leave.

1397
01:08:27,581 --> 01:08:28,701
But remember...

1398
01:08:28,901 --> 01:08:30,021
Victory...

1399
01:08:30,301 --> 01:08:32,261
must be inevitable
for you in every lifetime.

1400
01:08:34,261 --> 01:08:35,581
Mother Goddess!

1401
01:09:12,101 --> 01:09:13,221
There she is!

1402
01:09:16,261 --> 01:09:17,421
Cassandra!

1403
01:09:17,701 --> 01:09:19,221
How far did the Captain say?

1404
01:09:20,061 --> 01:09:21,501
Almost a hundred marine miles.

1405
01:09:22,021 --> 01:09:23,141
Hmm.

1406
01:09:23,381 --> 01:09:24,541
One more day.

1407
01:09:46,541 --> 01:09:47,620
What's happening?

1408
01:09:47,621 --> 01:09:49,541
- They have not finished eating yet.
- Is that so?

1409
01:09:52,301 --> 01:09:53,381
Mr. Padmanabhan...

1410
01:09:53,781 --> 01:09:55,660
The very thought
that came to your mind

1411
01:09:55,661 --> 01:09:57,380
would surely have
come to mine as well,

1412
01:09:57,381 --> 01:09:58,461
because I am brilliant.

1413
01:09:59,461 --> 01:10:00,620
Such is the way of things.

1414
01:10:00,621 --> 01:10:03,461
Great minds truly do think alike.

1415
01:10:03,581 --> 01:10:06,621
Indeed. Therefore,
we must begin our exodus today.

1416
01:10:06,901 --> 01:10:07,900
Let's flee!

1417
01:10:07,901 --> 01:10:08,940
Flee?

1418
01:10:08,941 --> 01:10:10,260
What in heaven's name
are you saying?

1419
01:10:10,261 --> 01:10:13,060
Since the East India Company
stands as our ally,

1420
01:10:13,061 --> 01:10:16,100
we can fight Azam Khan together.
That's what I meant!

1421
01:10:16,101 --> 01:10:17,180
Fight him?

1422
01:10:17,181 --> 01:10:18,381
You mean... war?

1423
01:10:18,981 --> 01:10:19,620
No!

1424
01:10:19,621 --> 01:10:22,421
Forget the fact that we do not
possess even one tenth of his forces.

1425
01:10:22,581 --> 01:10:24,460
He has cannons.

1426
01:10:24,461 --> 01:10:25,501
Let that pass as well.

1427
01:10:26,021 --> 01:10:28,581
He has got something even
bigger in his arsenal.

1428
01:10:28,741 --> 01:10:29,941
A big one!

1429
01:10:30,181 --> 01:10:31,301
What might that be?

1430
01:10:32,101 --> 01:10:34,060
That's called
the bloody Mysore Rocket.

1431
01:10:34,061 --> 01:10:36,340
Not even the East India Company
possesses such a weapon.

1432
01:10:36,341 --> 01:10:38,260
The orders are clear:
we are to hold our ground.

1433
01:10:38,261 --> 01:10:40,341
That means... fight to death!

1434
01:10:40,901 --> 01:10:41,980
To go up
in gunpowder smoke!

1435
01:10:41,981 --> 01:10:43,341
- Huh!
- Oh no!

1436
01:10:44,741 --> 01:10:45,820
I refuse to do that.

1437
01:10:45,821 --> 01:10:47,661
- I'm out of here today!
- So are we!

1438
01:10:48,301 --> 01:10:49,781
I, however,
shall remain and fight.

1439
01:10:51,061 --> 01:10:52,261
Poor!

1440
01:10:52,901 --> 01:10:53,980
Good luck, mate.

1441
01:10:53,981 --> 01:10:55,181
Good luck.

1442
01:10:58,501 --> 01:11:00,661
Until now, I had heard
only stories of exoduses.

1443
01:11:01,021 --> 01:11:04,101
By Your Majesty's grace, I now have
the fortune to witness one for myself.

1444
01:11:18,101 --> 01:11:20,180
My companion,
my pride!

1445
01:11:20,181 --> 01:11:21,301
Fire the cannon!

1446
01:11:30,581 --> 01:11:31,741
The Sultan's secret weapon!

1447
01:11:33,061 --> 01:11:34,581
My own invention.

1448
01:11:34,701 --> 01:11:35,901
The Mysore Rocket!

1449
01:11:36,141 --> 01:11:37,141
Fire!

1450
01:11:40,461 --> 01:11:44,381
Within two days, Padmanabhan's kingdom
shall be under my command.

1451
01:11:47,741 --> 01:11:51,060
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1452
01:11:51,061 --> 01:11:54,420
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1453
01:11:54,421 --> 01:11:57,740
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1454
01:11:57,741 --> 01:12:01,020
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1455
01:12:01,021 --> 01:12:04,220
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1456
01:12:04,221 --> 01:12:07,500
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1457
01:12:07,501 --> 01:12:09,141
♪ We shall lay down
our lives most gladly ♪

1458
01:12:16,061 --> 01:12:22,260
♪ O, Love Divine! ♪

1459
01:12:22,261 --> 01:12:25,420
♪ The Sultan who marches
to conquer the earth ♪

1460
01:12:25,421 --> 01:12:28,541
♪ A lone stag in this duel,
gleaming like gold in its worth ♪

1461
01:12:28,981 --> 01:12:35,300
♪ O, Love Divine! ♪

1462
01:12:35,301 --> 01:12:38,421
♪ The Sultan who marches
to conquer the earth ♪

1463
01:12:38,581 --> 01:12:41,821
♪ A lone stag in this duel,
gleaming like gold in its worth ♪

1464
01:12:42,141 --> 01:12:45,420
♪ My Sultan!
Lion-king Sultan! ♪

1465
01:12:45,421 --> 01:12:48,500
♪ Star of stars Sultan!
Valiant warrior Sultan! ♪

1466
01:12:48,501 --> 01:12:51,700
♪ The victor of Mysore,
mighty in renown ♪

1467
01:12:51,701 --> 01:12:55,060
♪ A hero the Huzoor
proudly calls his own ♪

1468
01:12:55,061 --> 01:12:58,580
♪ My Sultan!
Lion-king Sultan! ♪

1469
01:12:58,581 --> 01:13:01,421
♪ Star of stars Sultan!
Valiant warrior Sultan! ♪

1470
01:13:02,141 --> 01:13:04,900
The injury is in the fourteenth
vertebra of the spinal cord.

1471
01:13:04,901 --> 01:13:10,061
I fear this back pain will plague you
for many lifetimes to come.

1472
01:13:10,421 --> 01:13:11,580
Many lifetimes?!

1473
01:13:11,581 --> 01:13:14,621
♪ O, Love Divine! ♪

1474
01:13:14,781 --> 01:13:18,340
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1475
01:13:18,341 --> 01:13:21,420
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1476
01:13:21,421 --> 01:13:22,461
Wow!

1477
01:13:23,021 --> 01:13:25,381
At the sight of our arsenal
and our valiant soldiers,

1478
01:13:25,501 --> 01:13:27,300
I feel an urge
to march to battle tomorrow.

1479
01:13:27,301 --> 01:13:28,500
- What say you, Kurup?
- Indeed, Your Majesty.

1480
01:13:28,501 --> 01:13:31,420
Must we lead these thirty-seven men
to their deaths tomorrow itself?

1481
01:13:31,421 --> 01:13:33,101
Hey! Don't jinx it!

1482
01:13:33,261 --> 01:13:34,380
Follow me.

1483
01:13:34,381 --> 01:13:37,660
You have bound all the weapons in silk
threads for their safekeeping?

1484
01:13:37,661 --> 01:13:38,861
- Huh!
- Good job!

1485
01:13:39,501 --> 01:13:41,741
Brush away those cobwebs
and show them to His Majesty.

1486
01:13:48,301 --> 01:13:50,181
Has the sword
turned into a knife over time?

1487
01:13:54,941 --> 01:14:01,460
♪ As the Supreme Ruler Badshah
ascends the throne ♪

1488
01:14:01,461 --> 01:14:07,221
♪ My longing gaze
seeks you alone ♪

1489
01:14:07,941 --> 01:14:11,260
♪ Drenched in blood,
the monarch's blade ♪

1490
01:14:11,261 --> 01:14:14,540
♪ On its hilt where
the royal hand is laid ♪

1491
01:14:14,541 --> 01:14:20,781
♪ You are the priceless gem
set in that blade ♪

1492
01:14:21,701 --> 01:14:23,580
When that coward Azam Khan
arrives, inform him

1493
01:14:23,581 --> 01:14:26,780
that this District Court Magistrate
Lieutenant Colonel Walter Joseph

1494
01:14:26,781 --> 01:14:30,100
has no intention of speaking
with anyone except Tipu Sultan.

1495
01:14:30,101 --> 01:14:34,020
♪ An empire growing mightier day by day,
Are you the emperor who holds its sway? ♪

1496
01:14:34,021 --> 01:14:37,060
♪ The Sultan who marches
to conquer the earth ♪

1497
01:14:37,061 --> 01:14:40,220
♪ A lone stag in this duel,
gleaming like gold in its worth ♪

1498
01:14:40,221 --> 01:14:43,540
♪ The Sultan who marches
to conquer the earth ♪

1499
01:14:43,541 --> 01:14:47,060
♪ A lone stag in this duel,
gleaming like gold in its worth ♪

1500
01:14:47,061 --> 01:14:50,500
♪ My Sultan!
Lion-king Sultan! ♪

1501
01:14:50,501 --> 01:14:53,740
♪ Star of stars Sultan!
Valiant warrior Sultan! ♪

1502
01:14:53,741 --> 01:15:06,661
♪ O, Love Divine! ♪

1503
01:15:06,941 --> 01:15:10,220
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1504
01:15:10,221 --> 01:15:13,540
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1505
01:15:13,541 --> 01:15:16,860
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1506
01:15:16,861 --> 01:15:20,140
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1507
01:15:20,141 --> 01:15:23,460
♪ Lion of Mysore, brave and grand,
Your fame resounds through every land ♪

1508
01:15:23,461 --> 01:15:26,701
♪ By our motherland we vow to thee,
We shall lay down our lives most gladly ♪

1509
01:15:31,381 --> 01:15:32,541
What happened here?

1510
01:15:33,021 --> 01:15:34,221
Where is everyone?

1511
01:15:34,461 --> 01:15:36,061
Azam Khan coming.

1512
01:15:36,341 --> 01:15:37,460
Big army.

1513
01:15:37,461 --> 01:15:38,500
He kill all.

1514
01:15:38,501 --> 01:15:39,901
We all escaping, Madam.

1515
01:15:40,141 --> 01:15:43,141
Are these Azam Khan and boys
going to be a problem for us?

1516
01:15:43,461 --> 01:15:45,781
No. It's a blessing in disguise.

1517
01:15:46,301 --> 01:15:47,981
But we need to find Walter first.

1518
01:15:49,901 --> 01:15:51,221
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1519
01:15:54,661 --> 01:15:55,821
In my mind...

1520
01:15:56,461 --> 01:15:58,421
a most brilliant battle strategy
is taking shape.

1521
01:16:00,421 --> 01:16:04,101
The Nagathan bridge is now being
constructed across this river.

1522
01:16:05,341 --> 01:16:06,621
For their vast army

1523
01:16:07,861 --> 01:16:09,581
to cross this river,

1524
01:16:09,861 --> 01:16:11,141
a bridge is essential.

1525
01:16:11,581 --> 01:16:13,020
Boats alone will never suffice.

1526
01:16:13,021 --> 01:16:14,101
Thus,

1527
01:16:14,301 --> 01:16:16,461
let's destroy this bridge.

1528
01:16:17,101 --> 01:16:18,381
When desperation forces them

1529
01:16:18,581 --> 01:16:20,580
to cross the river
in small boats,

1530
01:16:20,581 --> 01:16:24,821
we can kill them one by one
by raining arrows from this vantage point.

1531
01:16:25,341 --> 01:16:26,540
What are your thoughts?

1532
01:16:26,541 --> 01:16:27,821
What can we say?

1533
01:16:28,101 --> 01:16:30,140
What do you think of
my genius, Narayanan?

1534
01:16:30,141 --> 01:16:31,180
Well...

1535
01:16:31,181 --> 01:16:33,700
My brilliance has rendered
you speechless, hasn't it?

1536
01:16:33,701 --> 01:16:34,860
Not quite.

1537
01:16:34,861 --> 01:16:38,221
Would it not be wiser to cross the
bridge and flee while we still can?

1538
01:16:38,461 --> 01:16:39,580
Hey, Narayanan!

1539
01:16:39,581 --> 01:16:40,701
Do not speak such nonsense!

1540
01:16:40,901 --> 01:16:42,101
But, my Lord...

1541
01:16:42,501 --> 01:16:45,021
Majority of our soldiers

1542
01:16:45,661 --> 01:16:47,940
fled the moment they heard
of Azam Khan's arrival,

1543
01:16:47,941 --> 01:16:49,301
and have not been seen since.

1544
01:16:49,981 --> 01:16:51,740
The word is they ran
without stopping,

1545
01:16:51,741 --> 01:16:54,741
crossed beyond the kingdom's borders,
and fled for good.

1546
01:16:55,501 --> 01:16:56,661
Cowards!

1547
01:16:57,141 --> 01:16:58,500
Where is Commander-in-Chief Kurup?

1548
01:16:58,501 --> 01:16:59,500
Summon him!

1549
01:16:59,501 --> 01:17:03,940
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

1550
01:17:03,941 --> 01:17:04,981
Your Highness...

1551
01:17:06,501 --> 01:17:07,621
Splendid!

1552
01:17:08,181 --> 01:17:10,941
To lift my spirits
in this time of crisis,

1553
01:17:11,221 --> 01:17:13,381
you have arrived to perform
some art form, I suppose?

1554
01:17:14,061 --> 01:17:15,501
Summon the royal dancers as well.

1555
01:17:15,821 --> 01:17:17,661
- Let the performance begin.
- Which dancers?

1556
01:17:18,061 --> 01:17:20,461
They must have fled and reached
the end of the earth by now.

1557
01:17:21,141 --> 01:17:22,981
This is no time for performances, my Lord.
It is time to flee.

1558
01:17:23,501 --> 01:17:26,221
Since this morning,
we all have become Muslims.

1559
01:17:26,701 --> 01:17:28,341
Thus I am no longer Kurup,

1560
01:17:28,941 --> 01:17:29,980
but Abu Salah.

1561
01:17:29,981 --> 01:17:31,180
Abu Salah.

1562
01:17:31,181 --> 01:17:32,501
This here is Salaam.

1563
01:17:32,661 --> 01:17:33,821
Salaam.

1564
01:17:34,381 --> 01:17:35,981
And this one…
who were you again?

1565
01:17:36,301 --> 01:17:38,181
Saifullah Hidhayath Al Anthruvan.

1566
01:17:38,901 --> 01:17:40,181
- Huh?
- Just "Anthru" will do.

1567
01:17:42,181 --> 01:17:43,541
The word is that General Khan

1568
01:17:43,781 --> 01:17:45,541
does not slay
his Muslim brethren.

1569
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:47,060
Truly?

1570
01:17:47,061 --> 01:17:48,180
Your Majesty!

1571
01:17:48,181 --> 01:17:49,580
Kurup! How could you--

1572
01:17:49,581 --> 01:17:52,180
Is it not better to lose
a little skin from the body

1573
01:17:52,181 --> 01:17:54,021
than to have one's head
severed from the neck?

1574
01:17:57,181 --> 01:17:58,261
Your Majesty,

1575
01:17:58,421 --> 01:17:59,781
we shall be safe here from now on.

1576
01:17:59,901 --> 01:18:00,980
But as for you...

1577
01:18:00,981 --> 01:18:03,581
Your Majesty, a message
has come from King Elayidathu.

1578
01:18:03,981 --> 01:18:05,541
They have already
begun their exodus.

1579
01:18:05,781 --> 01:18:07,420
It would be wise
to take the Royal Family

1580
01:18:07,421 --> 01:18:08,621
and seek refuge in the woods.

1581
01:18:09,101 --> 01:18:10,260
Your Majesty...

1582
01:18:10,261 --> 01:18:11,661
We do not bid farewell at night.

1583
01:18:12,221 --> 01:18:13,860
- Assalamu Alaikum.
- Salaam.

1584
01:18:13,861 --> 01:18:17,740
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

1585
01:18:17,741 --> 01:18:19,540
Don't look back,
or he'll summon us again!

1586
01:18:19,541 --> 01:18:21,581
And the Commander-in-Chief has
made his exit too!

1587
01:18:22,101 --> 01:18:23,781
What about you?
Do you want to exit too?

1588
01:18:23,981 --> 01:18:25,020
Never.

1589
01:18:25,021 --> 01:18:26,940
I'll betray you to Azam Khan

1590
01:18:26,941 --> 01:18:28,461
and remain here as his loyal servant.

1591
01:18:29,301 --> 01:18:31,140
You are carrying
the jest a little too far.

1592
01:18:31,141 --> 01:18:34,101
Who knows whether we shall have
the chance to jest ever again.

1593
01:18:36,581 --> 01:18:38,261
But in all seriousness,
Your Majesty...

1594
01:18:38,541 --> 01:18:40,621
Why are you so determined
to remain here?

1595
01:18:40,741 --> 01:18:42,661
We need not abandon the land
like the others.

1596
01:18:42,941 --> 01:18:44,620
Could we not remain hidden
for a few days?

1597
01:18:44,621 --> 01:18:47,461
Once that wretched Khan
returns to Mysore, we may return!

1598
01:18:47,981 --> 01:18:49,101
Nair...

1599
01:18:49,341 --> 01:18:52,380
Years ago, even when
the Portuguese Gama came,

1600
01:18:52,381 --> 01:18:54,381
my ancestors never
abandoned this land.

1601
01:18:54,821 --> 01:18:56,301
They never even attempted to.

1602
01:18:56,861 --> 01:18:58,981
They stood guard
over this palace and its riches.

1603
01:18:59,821 --> 01:19:01,821
And now this Azam Khan...

1604
01:19:02,261 --> 01:19:04,181
has not come
to this humble village

1605
01:19:05,221 --> 01:19:06,340
without reason.

1606
01:19:06,341 --> 01:19:07,861
What could his motive be, Highness?

1607
01:19:07,981 --> 01:19:10,581
What do we possess
that holds such great value?

1608
01:19:17,301 --> 01:19:19,701
Oh no! Oh no!

1609
01:19:20,221 --> 01:19:21,220
My Lord!

1610
01:19:21,221 --> 01:19:22,781
These men are from
the King's guard.

1611
01:19:22,981 --> 01:19:24,661
We seized them as they were fleeing.

1612
01:19:24,781 --> 01:19:27,340
They strayed from their path
and walked straight into our hands.

1613
01:19:27,341 --> 01:19:30,621
Yet they hold only the most
basic knowledge of the palace.

1614
01:19:30,861 --> 01:19:32,300
- Yes!
- True, Lord!

1615
01:19:32,301 --> 01:19:33,821
We know absolutely nothing, Lord!

1616
01:19:34,021 --> 01:19:37,021
Excellent! In reward for
telling me nothing of worth,

1617
01:19:37,381 --> 01:19:40,421
have their heads severed
and mounted on spears outside the tent!

1618
01:19:40,621 --> 01:19:41,901
- As you command, Lord.
- Oh no!

1619
01:19:42,061 --> 01:19:43,060
Oh no, Lord!

1620
01:19:43,061 --> 01:19:45,620
Not merely basic information,
we know remarkable secrets!

1621
01:19:45,621 --> 01:19:47,140
Hey! Tell him!

1622
01:19:47,141 --> 01:19:48,821
I have eight children, man!

1623
01:19:49,141 --> 01:19:51,061
Lord... it is but hearsay.

1624
01:19:52,101 --> 01:19:54,301
[whispers a secret]

1625
01:20:00,261 --> 01:20:01,860
So the tale I heard is true.

1626
01:20:01,861 --> 01:20:04,421
In a matter of days,
all of it shall be mine!

1627
01:20:05,381 --> 01:20:07,940
To celebrate this news, rip out the tongues
of the men who revealed it!

1628
01:20:07,941 --> 01:20:09,260
- Oh no!
- Lord!

1629
01:20:09,261 --> 01:20:10,581
Oh no!

1630
01:20:11,021 --> 01:20:12,740
- Your Majesty!
- You've lost your balance.

1631
01:20:12,741 --> 01:20:13,820
Mind the stairs.

1632
01:20:13,821 --> 01:20:15,141
I'm doing fine now.
Follow me.

1633
01:20:15,261 --> 01:20:16,461
I'm right behind you.

1634
01:20:17,581 --> 01:20:19,541
What brings you here
at this hour, Mappila?

1635
01:20:19,781 --> 01:20:21,300
I only came to show my face.

1636
01:20:21,301 --> 01:20:23,660
What else would you show
His Highness but your face?!

1637
01:20:23,661 --> 01:20:25,620
Do not utter such nonsense
at this twilight hour!

1638
01:20:25,621 --> 01:20:26,661
Okay.

1639
01:20:27,461 --> 01:20:28,581
Look at him!

1640
01:20:28,901 --> 01:20:31,100
Our engineer has laid aside
his official robes,

1641
01:20:31,101 --> 01:20:32,821
and has come prepared
to defend the kingdom.

1642
01:20:33,821 --> 01:20:36,101
Vareeth, only the brave
get the honour of...

1643
01:20:36,461 --> 01:20:37,541
a glorious death in battle.

1644
01:20:38,381 --> 01:20:39,380
Death?

1645
01:20:39,381 --> 01:20:40,860
- So, are we not leaving?
- We are.

1646
01:20:40,861 --> 01:20:42,220
What's all the whispering about?

1647
01:20:42,221 --> 01:20:43,421
It's nothing, Your Majesty.

1648
01:20:43,581 --> 01:20:46,421
They say Tipu's forces will arrive
in two days.

1649
01:20:47,941 --> 01:20:49,661
The villagers have already
begun to flee.

1650
01:20:50,341 --> 01:20:51,421
Cowards!

1651
01:20:51,861 --> 01:20:54,501
There is little point continuing
the bridge work now, is there?

1652
01:20:54,861 --> 01:20:56,181
So my men and I

1653
01:20:56,501 --> 01:20:58,940
were thinking of making
a strategic retreat to Travancore.

1654
01:20:58,941 --> 01:20:59,940
Why?

1655
01:20:59,941 --> 01:21:03,660
There, the mighty and powerful
Lord Padmanabhan will protect us.

1656
01:21:03,661 --> 01:21:05,661
Why? Do you doubt my strength?

1657
01:21:06,301 --> 01:21:07,701
I do not doubt it.

1658
01:21:08,141 --> 01:21:09,500
But my men remain unconvinced.

1659
01:21:09,501 --> 01:21:10,701
Hey Mappila...

1660
01:21:10,821 --> 01:21:14,060
The King had planned to raise
your status to the heavens.

1661
01:21:14,061 --> 01:21:16,221
I am in no haste to reach
the heavens just yet, Nair.

1662
01:21:16,781 --> 01:21:19,581
I'll go to Travancore
and work my way up gradually.

1663
01:21:20,661 --> 01:21:23,661
So I thought I would pay
my final respects before leaving.

1664
01:21:24,581 --> 01:21:25,661
I need your blessings.

1665
01:21:27,261 --> 01:21:28,701
We don't bid farewell at night.

1666
01:21:28,861 --> 01:21:30,421
So are we not leaving tonight?

1667
01:21:31,621 --> 01:21:32,660
Come on.

1668
01:21:32,661 --> 01:21:33,901
Vareeth Mappila, wait.

1669
01:21:34,941 --> 01:21:37,981
Nagathan bridge's construction
must be completed within two days.

1670
01:21:38,261 --> 01:21:39,741
- Huh?!
- On a war footing.

1671
01:21:39,901 --> 01:21:40,981
Why, Lord?

1672
01:21:41,221 --> 01:21:42,541
Won't they destroy the bridge?

1673
01:21:42,941 --> 01:21:44,861
Then would not all our efforts
be in vain?

1674
01:21:45,741 --> 01:21:47,101
They will not destroy the bridge.

1675
01:21:47,781 --> 01:21:49,341
Everyone needs the bridge, do they not?

1676
01:21:50,141 --> 01:21:52,541
Go and gather workers at once.

1677
01:21:53,541 --> 01:21:56,181
Tell them they will be paid
four or five times the wages.

1678
01:21:56,821 --> 01:21:58,221
I shall send Narayanan

1679
01:21:58,621 --> 01:21:59,821
with a formal letter...

1680
01:22:01,101 --> 01:22:02,181
and the required funds.

1681
01:22:03,101 --> 01:22:04,140
You may leave, Vareeth.

1682
01:22:04,141 --> 01:22:05,301
- You come with me.
- Okay.

1683
01:22:07,261 --> 01:22:09,300
What if we toss the letter
in the river and flee with the money?

1684
01:22:09,301 --> 01:22:10,661
- Ugh!
- Bad idea?

1685
01:22:11,141 --> 01:22:13,300
What if we discard the letter
and run off with the money?

1686
01:22:13,301 --> 01:22:14,261
Huh?

1687
01:22:16,181 --> 01:22:17,141
Here you go.

1688
01:22:18,381 --> 01:22:22,580
A threat over our heads!

1689
01:22:22,581 --> 01:22:26,341
The bridge called Nagathan!

1690
01:22:27,661 --> 01:22:28,740
Chief...

1691
01:22:28,741 --> 01:22:30,581
This protest is going
to be headache for us.

1692
01:22:31,101 --> 01:22:32,261
What headache?

1693
01:22:32,421 --> 01:22:33,660
No chance!

1694
01:22:33,661 --> 01:22:36,140
There are barely
seven people out there.

1695
01:22:36,141 --> 01:22:38,461
We are not going
to demolish a bridge for them.

1696
01:22:38,581 --> 01:22:40,580
Oh no! That won't do.
The bridge must be demolished.

1697
01:22:40,581 --> 01:22:43,300
If not, I'll have to resign
and join the frontline of that protest!

1698
01:22:43,301 --> 01:22:44,741
Fine, go ahead and resign then.

1699
01:22:45,141 --> 01:22:46,140
- That's better.
- Huh!

1700
01:22:46,141 --> 01:22:48,821
At least I will finally
have some peace in this office!

1701
01:22:52,501 --> 01:22:55,220
CM, if we demolish the old bridge,
we can build a new one.

1702
01:22:55,221 --> 01:22:58,301
Building a new bridge will be viewed
as an administrative reform.

1703
01:22:58,621 --> 01:23:01,181
Doesn't my department deserve
a chance to transform?

1704
01:23:01,301 --> 01:23:03,101
Ugh, you are becoming unbearable!

1705
01:23:04,101 --> 01:23:05,941
Fine, do whatever you want.
Damn it!

1706
01:23:06,101 --> 01:23:07,421
- Hey Shashi...
- Yes.

1707
01:23:07,581 --> 01:23:10,621
Is this going to create
more trouble later?

1708
01:23:10,861 --> 01:23:12,701
Why are you talking like that, Chief?

1709
01:23:13,061 --> 01:23:15,140
Clinging to this rusty old bridge,

1710
01:23:15,141 --> 01:23:17,301
what trouble could come
other than me?

1711
01:24:15,181 --> 01:24:16,220
Let me go!

1712
01:24:16,221 --> 01:24:17,301
Please let me go!

1713
01:24:17,661 --> 01:24:18,741
Michael...

1714
01:24:18,981 --> 01:24:20,981
I will repeat myself
one final time.

1715
01:24:21,701 --> 01:24:25,341
You stole a page from an ancient book
that everybody thought was a fairy tale.

1716
01:24:25,621 --> 01:24:26,781
Where is it?

1717
01:24:27,901 --> 01:24:29,740
Lady, I swear...
I'll call the police.

1718
01:24:29,741 --> 01:24:30,821
Police?

1719
01:24:31,061 --> 01:24:32,180
Go ahead.

1720
01:24:32,181 --> 01:24:33,221
Scream.

1721
01:24:33,461 --> 01:24:34,701
For every sound you make,

1722
01:24:35,181 --> 01:24:36,421
you will lose one finger.

1723
01:24:37,741 --> 01:24:38,861
Come on.

1724
01:24:39,181 --> 01:24:40,261
Scream.

1725
01:24:41,541 --> 01:24:42,621
Who are you people?

1726
01:24:43,261 --> 01:24:44,301
Michael...

1727
01:24:44,941 --> 01:24:47,620
I am associating with
some very serious people

1728
01:24:47,621 --> 01:24:49,061
and they don't like delays.

1729
01:24:49,901 --> 01:24:52,621
We had been to the
State Archive Directorate at Trivandrum.

1730
01:24:52,781 --> 01:24:54,541
We know you stole the page.

1731
01:24:55,021 --> 01:24:56,221
So, tell me...

1732
01:24:56,421 --> 01:24:57,461
Where is it?

1733
01:24:57,621 --> 01:24:59,101
Where is the location?

1734
01:24:59,301 --> 01:25:00,381
I don't know.

1735
01:25:00,621 --> 01:25:01,620
Wrong answer!

1736
01:25:01,621 --> 01:25:02,781
Please! No!

1737
01:25:05,981 --> 01:25:06,980
Get his phone.

1738
01:25:06,981 --> 01:25:08,421
I need that bloody location.

1739
01:25:08,701 --> 01:25:10,420
The deadline for submitting tenders

1740
01:25:10,421 --> 01:25:13,461
to demolish the Nagathan Bridge
via controlled implosion ended yesterday.

1741
01:25:13,581 --> 01:25:16,260
A press conference regarding the awarding
of the contract is currently underway.

1742
01:25:16,261 --> 01:25:17,140
On to it.

1743
01:25:17,141 --> 01:25:18,860
Thirteen companies have
submitted quotations

1744
01:25:18,861 --> 01:25:22,181
to demolish the Nagathan Bridge
through controlled implosion.

1745
01:25:22,341 --> 01:25:24,940
The company that submitted
the lowest quotation,

1746
01:25:24,941 --> 01:25:27,661
Xavier and Dawood Associates
from Mumbai,

1747
01:25:27,901 --> 01:25:28,941
will demolish the bridge.

1748
01:25:32,221 --> 01:25:34,021
- What's going on?
- I have no clue!

1749
01:25:34,741 --> 01:25:36,141
Has he gone completely nuts, Soman?

1750
01:25:38,141 --> 01:25:39,181
- Here.
- I don't need it.

1751
01:25:42,781 --> 01:25:43,861
Is this contagious?

1752
01:25:44,581 --> 01:25:45,620
Hey, wait!

1753
01:25:45,621 --> 01:25:47,820
Look, Paappan, your scrap business
idea is all well and good.

1754
01:25:47,821 --> 01:25:50,020
Those iron rods and wheels
you mentioned are indeed old.

1755
01:25:50,021 --> 01:25:52,301
But they are on Kerala
State Electricity Board property!

1756
01:25:52,541 --> 01:25:54,860
Without issuing a tender,
we cannot simply hand them to you.

1757
01:25:54,861 --> 01:25:58,341
Can we get this trend...
I mean, that thing, without anyone knowing?

1758
01:25:58,741 --> 01:26:00,100
Sure, if you manage

1759
01:26:00,101 --> 01:26:01,741
to become
the Chief Minister of Kerala.

1760
01:26:02,061 --> 01:26:03,500
Won't that take a lot of time?!

1761
01:26:03,501 --> 01:26:06,860
My dear Paappan, stop wasting my time
and find something that will actually work.

1762
01:26:06,861 --> 01:26:09,061
- Convey my regards to Rachel!
- Genzy!

1763
01:26:09,381 --> 01:26:11,501
Hey! You can make this happen! Hey!

1764
01:26:11,701 --> 01:26:13,021
Her name is Gen Z!

1765
01:26:13,261 --> 01:26:15,221
Yet she is as outdated
as Paappan himself!

1766
01:26:17,621 --> 01:26:18,860
Stop blabbering! Come.

1767
01:26:18,861 --> 01:26:19,861
He was talking to you.

1768
01:26:20,141 --> 01:26:21,140
You two are listed

1769
01:26:21,141 --> 01:26:23,580
as the Kerala proprietors for
Xavier & Dawood Associates.

1770
01:26:23,581 --> 01:26:24,780
Yeah, yeah.

1771
01:26:24,781 --> 01:26:26,260
I see you have experience

1772
01:26:26,261 --> 01:26:27,940
handling several explosions
across the country.

1773
01:26:27,941 --> 01:26:28,940
Yes, we do.

1774
01:26:28,941 --> 01:26:29,940
Even so, I must say...

1775
01:26:29,941 --> 01:26:31,980
You will be held fully responsible
for this explosion.

1776
01:26:31,981 --> 01:26:33,141
- Absolutely.
- Here you go.

1777
01:26:33,581 --> 01:26:34,700
- Sir...
- Yes.

1778
01:26:34,701 --> 01:26:36,180
Not just this explosion...

1779
01:26:36,181 --> 01:26:38,981
from now on, for every explosion in India

1780
01:26:39,541 --> 01:26:40,661
we will be responsible.

1781
01:26:41,341 --> 01:26:42,500
Yeah, fine. Whatever!

1782
01:26:42,501 --> 01:26:44,100
Safety during the explosion,

1783
01:26:44,101 --> 01:26:45,661
and clearing the debris
afterward.

1784
01:26:45,981 --> 01:26:47,620
All of that will be your responsibility.

1785
01:26:47,621 --> 01:26:50,341
And if there is any casualty
during the explosion,

1786
01:26:50,621 --> 01:26:52,740
you will be the first ones
charged with manslaughter.

1787
01:26:52,741 --> 01:26:54,700
- Got it?
- What was that mansl...?

1788
01:26:54,701 --> 01:26:55,981
Murder charge!

1789
01:26:58,101 --> 01:26:59,221
Fine, carry on.

1790
01:26:59,421 --> 01:27:00,461
Get lost!

1791
01:27:00,941 --> 01:27:02,701
- Good thing you're with me.
- I'm not coming.

1792
01:27:02,821 --> 01:27:04,580
Let's just forget about
this scrap business.

1793
01:27:04,581 --> 01:27:06,500
But that's how guys like
Ambani and Tata made it big.

1794
01:27:06,501 --> 01:27:07,581
Who on earth are they?

1795
01:27:07,741 --> 01:27:08,820
- What happened, Paappan?
- Hey!

1796
01:27:08,821 --> 01:27:10,340
Doesn't he look like
that loser we know?

1797
01:27:10,341 --> 01:27:11,540
Battery Simon.

1798
01:27:11,541 --> 01:27:13,020
- It's definitely that loser.
- Really?

1799
01:27:13,021 --> 01:27:14,741
- Yes.
- Chill. I won't shoot a video.

1800
01:27:16,621 --> 01:27:17,941
Pauper!
I mean, Paappan!

1801
01:27:20,741 --> 01:27:22,941
- So, you're a lawyer now?
- Yeah. At the bar of debt.

1802
01:27:23,341 --> 01:27:24,621
You're looking pretty sharp.

1803
01:27:25,141 --> 01:27:26,620
- Like a corpse in a coffin!
- Thanks.

1804
01:27:26,621 --> 01:27:28,940
By the way,
I've been looking for you.

1805
01:27:28,941 --> 01:27:29,660
Oh...

1806
01:27:29,661 --> 01:27:33,820
You tried to kidnap my
sister Rachel, did you not?

1807
01:27:33,821 --> 01:27:34,940
See!

1808
01:27:34,941 --> 01:27:37,140
Didn't I tell you
Paappan would ask that?

1809
01:27:37,141 --> 01:27:38,540
We weren't trying to kidnap her.

1810
01:27:38,541 --> 01:27:39,861
We were just mollycoddling her!

1811
01:27:40,741 --> 01:27:42,540
- Oh no!
- What is this?

1812
01:27:42,541 --> 01:27:44,140
Yes. Proceed, Your Honour.

1813
01:27:44,141 --> 01:27:45,501
- I am ready.
- It's in English.

1814
01:27:46,021 --> 01:27:47,381
- What is this?
- This is a cover.

1815
01:27:48,501 --> 01:27:50,261
- This is a cover.
- Isn't that what I said?

1816
01:28:02,061 --> 01:28:03,421
So there's a new player on board?

1817
01:28:03,661 --> 01:28:04,701
Hmm.

1818
01:28:04,861 --> 01:28:05,981
Let's play along then.

1819
01:28:15,301 --> 01:28:16,740
Hey! Isn't this for me to spit into?

1820
01:28:16,741 --> 01:28:18,141
Anyone can spit in it,
can't they?

1821
01:28:18,341 --> 01:28:19,500
Why are we in the cellar?

1822
01:28:19,501 --> 01:28:21,421
Did you bring me here to do chores?

1823
01:28:21,981 --> 01:28:23,101
Move this mat aside.

1824
01:28:29,061 --> 01:28:31,061
Do not stand there like a pole.
Bring that torch!

1825
01:28:35,741 --> 01:28:38,261
You're the first person I've ever
brought in here besides me.

1826
01:28:39,661 --> 01:28:40,700
What is that?

1827
01:28:40,701 --> 01:28:42,180
I dropped the spittoon.

1828
01:28:42,181 --> 01:28:43,701
The spittoon? Now?

1829
01:28:44,901 --> 01:28:45,941
Come this way.

1830
01:28:57,901 --> 01:29:01,261
This is a treasure passed down
through generations, Narayanan.

1831
01:29:01,501 --> 01:29:02,741
I know that.

1832
01:29:02,861 --> 01:29:05,821
After all, you haven't even done something
worth a proverb on your own!

1833
01:29:05,981 --> 01:29:07,101
Hey!

1834
01:29:08,101 --> 01:29:11,901
No king in these parts
possesses such wealth.

1835
01:29:13,781 --> 01:29:15,501
Everyone saw my hard times

1836
01:29:15,981 --> 01:29:18,781
and believed this rare treasure
was only a legend.

1837
01:29:19,181 --> 01:29:21,101
And I never went about
speaking of it.

1838
01:29:21,261 --> 01:29:22,381
Except you,

1839
01:29:22,741 --> 01:29:25,621
this palace holds many
priceless things.

1840
01:29:25,781 --> 01:29:27,021
- Isn't it?
- Narayanan!

1841
01:29:27,141 --> 01:29:28,541
Not another word from you!

1842
01:29:28,821 --> 01:29:30,301
- I'll do the talking.
- Sure.

1843
01:29:32,341 --> 01:29:34,061
Azam Khan did not come here...

1844
01:29:34,981 --> 01:29:36,581
for this priceless treasure alone.

1845
01:29:37,021 --> 01:29:38,061
Then?

1846
01:29:39,021 --> 01:29:40,101
Come with me.

1847
01:29:52,341 --> 01:29:53,781
This rare gemstone.

1848
01:29:55,981 --> 01:30:00,341
It emerged from an unknown realm
beyond the heavens.

1849
01:30:01,581 --> 01:30:03,781
Such is the legend
bestowed upon us by our ancestors.

1850
01:30:05,141 --> 01:30:08,021
It is believed to wield a force
unknown to mankind.

1851
01:30:08,941 --> 01:30:10,901
We call it Star Dust.

1852
01:30:13,141 --> 01:30:14,341
Under no circumstances,

1853
01:30:14,781 --> 01:30:17,301
must it fall into
another's hands.

1854
01:30:17,581 --> 01:30:19,141
What shall we do with it,
Your Majesty?

1855
01:30:19,581 --> 01:30:21,901
At first I thought of taking it
with me when I flee.

1856
01:30:22,501 --> 01:30:23,741
But if I am captured,

1857
01:30:23,861 --> 01:30:25,580
I will lose my life
and the stone with it.

1858
01:30:25,581 --> 01:30:26,500
True.

1859
01:30:26,501 --> 01:30:29,781
So follow my instructions...

1860
01:30:29,901 --> 01:30:31,741
exactly, and in complete secrecy.

1861
01:30:32,781 --> 01:30:33,861
Go...

1862
01:30:34,381 --> 01:30:35,981
and tell the guards to be ready.

1863
01:30:36,701 --> 01:30:37,460
Okay.

1864
01:30:37,461 --> 01:30:38,901
And do not go spreading the word

1865
01:30:39,381 --> 01:30:40,781
about what you saw here.

1866
01:30:40,941 --> 01:30:41,901
Never!

1867
01:31:16,021 --> 01:31:17,141
Comrades!

1868
01:31:17,781 --> 01:31:19,581
According to our readings,

1869
01:31:20,181 --> 01:31:23,181
the Stardust has become active
once again after centuries.

1870
01:31:23,981 --> 01:31:25,180
From now on,

1871
01:31:25,181 --> 01:31:28,781
critical events will unfold
across multiple timelines!

1872
01:31:45,381 --> 01:31:46,581
The King himself sent this...

1873
01:31:47,061 --> 01:31:48,581
so the bridge would not weaken.

1874
01:31:49,021 --> 01:31:50,501
Amulets blessed
with sacred chants.

1875
01:31:51,981 --> 01:31:53,821
Jesus, protect us!

1876
01:31:56,061 --> 01:31:58,461
Everything has been done
as you commanded.

1877
01:31:58,621 --> 01:32:01,221
- Subhadra, come.
- Shall we begin our escape?

1878
01:32:02,941 --> 01:32:04,021
We shall.

1879
01:32:05,181 --> 01:32:06,301
For one last time,

1880
01:32:06,901 --> 01:32:08,901
let me behold my entire realm.

1881
01:32:11,181 --> 01:32:12,941
What if I never return?

1882
01:32:18,181 --> 01:32:19,100
Scrap agreement.

1883
01:32:19,101 --> 01:32:20,820
First Party: Shaji Paappan
of Pannimattom.

1884
01:32:20,821 --> 01:32:22,860
Second Party: For Xavier
and Dawood Associates,

1885
01:32:22,861 --> 01:32:24,821
Soman Pachilakkunnil
and Simon Batteryparambil.

1886
01:32:25,101 --> 01:32:26,260
The agreement seems fine.

1887
01:32:26,261 --> 01:32:28,420
Since Rachel paid
the ₹10,000 on time,

1888
01:32:28,421 --> 01:32:29,621
we managed to secure the deal.

1889
01:32:31,261 --> 01:32:32,261
Abu...

1890
01:32:32,661 --> 01:32:33,821
I have a feeling...

1891
01:32:34,421 --> 01:32:36,781
once we get the scrap
from this bridge,

1892
01:32:37,541 --> 01:32:38,820
we're going to make it big!

1893
01:32:38,821 --> 01:32:39,820
Yes.

1894
01:32:39,821 --> 01:32:41,660
Like finding an egg
from a chicken biryani!

1895
01:32:41,661 --> 01:32:42,741
Yeah, right!

1896
01:32:43,021 --> 01:32:47,181
This will be yet another chapter
in Paappan's book of blunders.

1897
01:32:47,341 --> 01:32:49,020
- Stop it!
- What?

1898
01:32:49,021 --> 01:32:52,141
Take them away soon,
and let me stay here, Jesus!

1899
01:33:10,301 --> 01:33:11,701
Hey, Sulaiman!

1900
01:33:12,461 --> 01:33:13,661
Sulaiman!

1901
01:33:14,501 --> 01:33:15,981
Napping at work?

1902
01:33:16,661 --> 01:33:17,741
Moron!

1903
01:33:18,061 --> 01:33:19,221
Wake up!

1904
01:33:22,301 --> 01:33:23,381
Hey, you!

1905
01:33:23,541 --> 01:33:26,100
Haven't I told you a thousand times
not to daydream during work hours?

1906
01:33:26,101 --> 01:33:26,980
You have, boss.

1907
01:33:26,981 --> 01:33:28,021
Get up, you lazy bum!

1908
01:33:28,901 --> 01:33:31,221
If I catch you resting
one more time...

1909
01:33:33,421 --> 01:33:34,701
Rest in peace!

1910
01:33:36,381 --> 01:33:37,901
Move it!
Get back to work!

1911
01:33:38,141 --> 01:33:39,141
Moron!

1912
01:33:40,781 --> 01:33:43,541
Even the donkey got lazy
after hanging around this idiot!

1913
01:33:44,141 --> 01:33:46,581
There's no way out, Antony.
Just keep pulling.

1914
01:33:51,541 --> 01:33:52,861
Are you seeing this, DK?

1915
01:33:53,461 --> 01:33:54,861
Maruthunayagam's kicks

1916
01:33:55,181 --> 01:33:56,781
turned poor Dude's spine
to jelly.

1917
01:33:56,901 --> 01:33:59,420
Are you going to run away
like the other guy?

1918
01:33:59,421 --> 01:34:00,420
Look, Paily…

1919
01:34:00,421 --> 01:34:01,900
I'm not going
anywhere without Dude.

1920
01:34:01,901 --> 01:34:03,260
Dude is my god.
My own god.

1921
01:34:03,261 --> 01:34:04,221
Good for you.

1922
01:34:04,621 --> 01:34:07,941
We are all going to die getting
beaten up in this bandit's copra yard.

1923
01:34:10,221 --> 01:34:11,501
Hey! Get back to work!

1924
01:34:11,821 --> 01:34:12,981
On it!

1925
01:34:28,021 --> 01:34:30,261
With the old boss, all we had to do
was make parottas.

1926
01:34:30,421 --> 01:34:32,381
If we burn down his hotel
and try to run away,

1927
01:34:32,701 --> 01:34:34,501
- do you think he'll spare us?
- Exactly!

1928
01:34:36,341 --> 01:34:37,941
I won't spare you guys.

1929
01:34:39,021 --> 01:34:43,101
My uncle sold you to me
so I could make you work like slaves.

1930
01:34:43,901 --> 01:34:45,500
I won't let you go

1931
01:34:45,501 --> 01:34:49,181
until I recover the loss you caused him
with interest.

1932
01:34:49,661 --> 01:34:51,621
And you won't finish paying it
in this lifetime.

1933
01:34:52,341 --> 01:34:53,861
- Sulaiman!
- Yes?

1934
01:34:54,221 --> 01:34:58,260
Don't even dream of
escaping from my clutches.

1935
01:34:58,261 --> 01:35:00,980
Maruthu sir, at least add
some salt to this gruel.

1936
01:35:00,981 --> 01:35:02,260
I won't go anywhere.

1937
01:35:02,261 --> 01:35:04,980
Hey! Just shut up and eat
what you're given, you idiot!

1938
01:35:04,981 --> 01:35:06,141
Boss!

1939
01:35:06,621 --> 01:35:07,901
Listen here, you rascal!

1940
01:35:08,141 --> 01:35:10,940
You have to wake up early
and go break rocks.

1941
01:35:10,941 --> 01:35:12,861
Breaking rocks?!
Oh, my god!

1942
01:35:16,741 --> 01:35:17,741
Dude sir...

1943
01:35:18,261 --> 01:35:19,341
I'm sick of this life!

1944
01:35:20,061 --> 01:35:21,540
I couldn't even make it
to Hong Kong.

1945
01:35:21,541 --> 01:35:22,701
Forget that.

1946
01:35:22,901 --> 01:35:24,100
My Kerala...

1947
01:35:24,101 --> 01:35:25,861
I just want to see my Kerala
at least once.

1948
01:35:25,981 --> 01:35:28,220
Not Hong Kong, you baboon!
It was Bangkok!

1949
01:35:28,221 --> 01:35:30,660
We're already screwed
and I've got zero patience left.

1950
01:35:30,661 --> 01:35:31,821
So don't get me started.

1951
01:35:32,061 --> 01:35:34,421
I'm literally dying
to see Kerala again.

1952
01:35:35,421 --> 01:35:36,581
Dude sir...

1953
01:35:36,741 --> 01:35:38,141
Let's somehow escape from here.

1954
01:35:39,421 --> 01:35:40,901
It's not that I don't want to, Paily.

1955
01:35:42,141 --> 01:35:44,661
But I can't leave
without my Antony.

1956
01:35:46,541 --> 01:35:49,261
They treat people like trash here,
and he's worried about a donkey!

1957
01:35:57,061 --> 01:35:58,141
Antony!

1958
01:35:59,261 --> 01:36:00,260
Hey Antony...

1959
01:36:00,261 --> 01:36:01,301
You know what?

1960
01:36:01,821 --> 01:36:03,701
I have to work
at the quarry tomorrow.

1961
01:36:04,381 --> 01:36:05,461
You've got the day off.

1962
01:36:06,061 --> 01:36:07,181
Good night!

1963
01:36:12,181 --> 01:36:13,221
Oh, boy...

1964
01:36:15,181 --> 01:36:16,221
Antony...

1965
01:36:18,181 --> 01:36:19,221
Antony!

1966
01:36:23,621 --> 01:36:25,060
- Xavier sir...
- Yes!

1967
01:36:25,061 --> 01:36:26,660
The order to demolish the bridge...

1968
01:36:26,661 --> 01:36:28,661
You were too drunk
to read it yesterday.

1969
01:36:28,781 --> 01:36:31,621
Now that you're sober,
why don't you read it?

1970
01:36:31,781 --> 01:36:34,261
What for? Isn't it written
exactly the way I said?

1971
01:36:35,101 --> 01:36:37,180
Sir, that's true.
But once you read it,

1972
01:36:37,181 --> 01:36:40,220
you'll be so pleased
you'll pour yourself two extra drinks.

1973
01:36:40,221 --> 01:36:41,261
Have a look.

1974
01:36:45,021 --> 01:36:46,221
Nice, very nice!

1975
01:36:46,421 --> 01:36:48,261
We get to demolish the bridge ourselves.

1976
01:36:49,421 --> 01:36:51,540
Sir, that's not the only highlight.

1977
01:36:51,541 --> 01:36:53,181
There's more!
Take a look at this too.

1978
01:36:53,901 --> 01:36:55,021
Yeah.

1979
01:36:55,221 --> 01:36:56,581
Wow! This is another highlight.

1980
01:36:58,661 --> 01:37:00,020
Under the terms of this Agreement,

1981
01:37:00,021 --> 01:37:01,940
all the remaining scrap
from the Nagathan Bridge

1982
01:37:01,941 --> 01:37:03,740
being demolished
by Xavier & Dawood Company...

1983
01:37:03,741 --> 01:37:08,180
namely the rebar, bricks,
iron, rust, soil and stone,

1984
01:37:08,181 --> 01:37:10,381
including all debris
from the bridge site...

1985
01:37:10,741 --> 01:37:14,741
shall be acquired by the First Party,
Shaji Paappan of Pannimattom,

1986
01:37:15,141 --> 01:37:18,581
for a sum of ₹10,000,
without leaving anything behind.

1987
01:37:18,941 --> 01:37:21,381
It is hereby agreed.

1988
01:37:21,661 --> 01:37:22,740
Happy?

1989
01:37:22,741 --> 01:37:23,940
What on earth is this?

1990
01:37:23,941 --> 01:37:26,221
Signed on behalf of Dawood & Co.
by Soman and Simon.

1991
01:37:26,501 --> 01:37:28,220
You just wanted
the bridge demolished, right?

1992
01:37:28,221 --> 01:37:30,861
What do we need
all that rust and scrap for?

1993
01:37:30,981 --> 01:37:33,780
It would've cost us 10 lakhs
just to clear the debris.

1994
01:37:33,781 --> 01:37:34,300
Yes.

1995
01:37:34,301 --> 01:37:36,740
We ripped those guys off
for peanuts.

1996
01:37:36,741 --> 01:37:39,101
The rest is pure profit
for you, sir!

1997
01:37:39,341 --> 01:37:40,500
And that's not all, sir.

1998
01:37:40,501 --> 01:37:42,580
To make sure they wouldn't
change their minds later,

1999
01:37:42,581 --> 01:37:46,220
we called the officials there
and signed it right in front of them.

2000
01:37:46,221 --> 01:37:47,300
Now tell me...

2001
01:37:47,301 --> 01:37:49,660
aren't you going to celebrate
with two extra drinks?

2002
01:37:49,661 --> 01:37:50,660
- What?
- I asked...

2003
01:37:50,661 --> 01:37:52,500
if you're going to celebrate
with two more drinks.

2004
01:37:52,501 --> 01:37:53,660
Yeah.

2005
01:37:53,661 --> 01:37:54,580
- You...!
- Yikes!

2006
01:37:54,581 --> 01:37:56,020
You stupid Battery!

2007
01:37:56,021 --> 01:37:58,340
Sir, have mercy on him!
I'm the innocent one!

2008
01:37:58,341 --> 01:38:00,460
You're not innocent.
You're a walking disaster!

2009
01:38:00,461 --> 01:38:02,140
- Stop there!
- Yes, if you say so!

2010
01:38:02,141 --> 01:38:04,221
- I'll burn you alive today!
- Oh no!

2011
01:38:05,221 --> 01:38:06,501
What are you watching?

2012
01:38:06,661 --> 01:38:08,220
Some guy's wedding night vlog.

2013
01:38:08,221 --> 01:38:09,460
Wait... is the whole thing there?

2014
01:38:09,461 --> 01:38:10,741
Part two comes out
only next week.

2015
01:38:10,981 --> 01:38:11,981
I'll wait then.

2016
01:38:12,661 --> 01:38:14,301
- [Abu burps]
- Ugh!

2017
01:38:14,421 --> 01:38:17,261
Will you fill up the empty cylinder
with your gas?

2018
01:38:18,021 --> 01:38:19,181
Shajiyett...

2019
01:38:19,341 --> 01:38:21,540
Look, the full history of that bridge
is printed in the newspaper.

2020
01:38:21,541 --> 01:38:23,060
It was built during the British era.

2021
01:38:23,061 --> 01:38:24,700
- Built during the British era?
- Yeah.

2022
01:38:24,701 --> 01:38:26,140
Then there should be
iron rods and rings inside it.

2023
01:38:26,141 --> 01:38:26,900
Right.

2024
01:38:26,901 --> 01:38:29,060
- Paappoy!
- Ah, the virus arrives. What is it now?

2025
01:38:29,061 --> 01:38:31,701
We shouldn't stoop to
this miserable scrap business.

2026
01:38:32,021 --> 01:38:34,340
You already look like you came
straight out of a junkyard, Paappan.

2027
01:38:34,341 --> 01:38:36,381
This line of work
is far below our status.

2028
01:38:36,701 --> 01:38:39,180
Won't people call you "Scrap Paappan"
when they see you?

2029
01:38:39,181 --> 01:38:40,500
What do they call him now?

2030
01:38:40,501 --> 01:38:42,900
- "Pauper Paappan."
- Like that's much better!

2031
01:38:42,901 --> 01:38:44,021
Shut up, Captain!

2032
01:38:44,661 --> 01:38:48,181
This swing isn't strong enough
for all of you to cling to it.

2033
01:38:48,341 --> 01:38:50,220
I wish I had been born
a white man in America.

2034
01:38:50,221 --> 01:38:51,740
Yeah, then you'd be Sahib Paappan!

2035
01:38:51,741 --> 01:38:53,461
Paappan, look!
It's Satan Xavier.

2036
01:38:53,781 --> 01:38:55,300
- Who's that?
- Underworld, underworld!

2037
01:38:55,301 --> 01:38:58,021
♪ High Range,
Highly Danger ♪

2038
01:38:58,301 --> 01:38:59,540
You sneaky Paappan!

2039
01:38:59,541 --> 01:39:01,301
♪ High Range,
Highly Danger ♪

2040
01:39:02,781 --> 01:39:04,341
♪ Satan Xavier ♪

2041
01:39:04,581 --> 01:39:06,300
- Stand up, old hag!
- You bloody!

2042
01:39:06,301 --> 01:39:07,581
♪ Paappan ♪

2043
01:39:08,101 --> 01:39:09,261
♪ Paappan ♪

2044
01:39:10,101 --> 01:39:14,181
♪ The High Range's highly dangerous
underworld kingpin renowned ♪

2045
01:39:14,661 --> 01:39:15,820
Satan...

2046
01:39:15,821 --> 01:39:17,021
Satan Xavier!

2047
01:39:17,901 --> 01:39:19,061
Paappan...

2048
01:39:19,221 --> 01:39:20,220
Shaji Paappan.

2049
01:39:20,221 --> 01:39:21,421
Well, well!

2050
01:39:22,661 --> 01:39:23,741
These are my boys.

2051
01:39:23,901 --> 01:39:25,980
They made a small slip-up
yesterday morning.

2052
01:39:25,981 --> 01:39:28,461
That scrap agreement has to be
written the other way around.

2053
01:39:28,701 --> 01:39:30,740
The other way? If you write it backwards,
will anyone even understand it?

2054
01:39:30,741 --> 01:39:32,741
- Like we understood it earlier!
- Shut up!

2055
01:39:33,221 --> 01:39:34,901
Before you decide anything,

2056
01:39:35,221 --> 01:39:36,380
hear me out first.

2057
01:39:36,381 --> 01:39:38,780
Abu, uncle is about to tell a story.
Pay attention.

2058
01:39:38,781 --> 01:39:41,460
Back in the mid-1700s,

2059
01:39:41,461 --> 01:39:43,621
it was my great-great-grandfather,

2060
01:39:43,781 --> 01:39:45,981
Walter Sahib,
who built that bridge.

2061
01:39:46,101 --> 01:39:47,300
Oh!

2062
01:39:47,301 --> 01:39:49,181
Just a day before
the bridge's inauguration,

2063
01:39:50,581 --> 01:39:52,381
he passed away.

2064
01:39:52,501 --> 01:39:53,660
- How sad!
- Very good!

2065
01:39:53,661 --> 01:39:56,381
He loved this land so much that
they didn't take his body

2066
01:39:56,661 --> 01:39:57,981
back to London.

2067
01:39:58,581 --> 01:40:00,581
Instead, they placed his ashes

2068
01:40:01,341 --> 01:40:02,821
inside the bridge itself.

2069
01:40:03,621 --> 01:40:04,701
Huh?

2070
01:40:05,781 --> 01:40:09,021
Hoping to see those ashes
just once,

2071
01:40:09,261 --> 01:40:12,061
his beloved wife,
Dolores Aunty,

2072
01:40:13,101 --> 01:40:14,821
still waits,

2073
01:40:16,341 --> 01:40:19,221
her tears never drying.

2074
01:40:20,421 --> 01:40:21,740
He's not talking about your mom!

2075
01:40:21,741 --> 01:40:22,821
Dollar grandma!

2076
01:40:24,141 --> 01:40:25,580
Wait, if she's still waiting,

2077
01:40:25,581 --> 01:40:28,420
that Dollar Aunty must be
at least 300 years old now, right?

2078
01:40:28,421 --> 01:40:29,501
That's right!

2079
01:40:30,501 --> 01:40:31,300
Huh!

2080
01:40:31,301 --> 01:40:32,340
Not the aunty herself, Uncle!

2081
01:40:32,341 --> 01:40:34,660
- Aunty's aunt's brother's--
- Look, Xavier sir...

2082
01:40:34,661 --> 01:40:35,980
We need a moment
to think this over.

2083
01:40:35,981 --> 01:40:36,860
- Right?
- Yes.

2084
01:40:36,861 --> 01:40:39,180
You don't have to think.
You bought it for ₹10,000, right?

2085
01:40:39,181 --> 01:40:39,780
Yes.

2086
01:40:39,781 --> 01:40:41,820
- I'll give you ₹20,000.
- That's fair.

2087
01:40:41,821 --> 01:40:42,781
Isn't that enough?

2088
01:40:44,461 --> 01:40:45,620
Actually,

2089
01:40:45,621 --> 01:40:46,821
make it thirty.

2090
01:40:47,381 --> 01:40:48,741
Fine, let's make it fifty!

2091
01:40:49,141 --> 01:40:51,940
- Agree for fifty, Uncle!
- Fi... Fif... Fifty? No, sir.

2092
01:40:51,941 --> 01:40:53,140
It won't take long to count.

2093
01:40:53,141 --> 01:40:54,261
One lakh!

2094
01:40:55,061 --> 01:40:57,180
Shajiyetta, just stay quiet
for two minutes

2095
01:40:57,181 --> 01:40:58,501
and the price will keep rising.

2096
01:40:58,661 --> 01:40:59,740
Hmm?

2097
01:40:59,741 --> 01:41:01,100
- Two!
- Wow!

2098
01:41:01,101 --> 01:41:02,781
- Two lakhs!
- Told you!

2099
01:41:04,141 --> 01:41:05,221
Three lakhs!

2100
01:41:07,621 --> 01:41:08,660
Four lakhs!

2101
01:41:08,661 --> 01:41:10,021
- Five lakhs!
- Huh!

2102
01:41:10,341 --> 01:41:11,460
Six lakhs!

2103
01:41:11,461 --> 01:41:13,020
- Seven lakhs!
- Who the hell is that?

2104
01:41:13,021 --> 01:41:14,180
I'll throw this at you!

2105
01:41:14,181 --> 01:41:15,261
Eight lakhs!

2106
01:41:16,021 --> 01:41:17,421
- Nine lakhs!
- Huh?!

2107
01:41:17,861 --> 01:41:18,901
Ten lakhs!

2108
01:41:19,661 --> 01:41:21,181
- Eleven lakhs!
- Huh?!

2109
01:41:21,981 --> 01:41:23,300
Oh, that's the game?
Fine!

2110
01:41:23,301 --> 01:41:24,581
- Take this--
- Enough!!!

2111
01:41:25,461 --> 01:41:26,900
25 lakhs!

2112
01:41:26,901 --> 01:41:28,541
Twenty-five lakhs!

2113
01:41:29,101 --> 01:41:30,061
Err...

2114
01:41:30,741 --> 01:41:33,180
Even if you offer a fortune
in gold, we won't give it, sir.

2115
01:41:33,181 --> 01:41:35,980
We… we dreamt of a vulture.
That's why!

2116
01:41:35,981 --> 01:41:37,580
- You mean, 'Venture'.
- Yeah, that stuff.

2117
01:41:37,581 --> 01:41:39,740
You dogs! You're using
my grandfather's ashes

2118
01:41:39,741 --> 01:41:41,740
- to build your vulture dreams?
- Culture!

2119
01:41:41,741 --> 01:41:42,821
Shut up!

2120
01:41:43,261 --> 01:41:44,341
Hey!

2121
01:41:45,461 --> 01:41:47,460
- Shajiyetta!
- You better return my agreement!

2122
01:41:47,461 --> 01:41:48,541
Idiots!

2123
01:41:50,901 --> 01:41:52,221
- Oh no!
- Oh no!

2124
01:41:52,541 --> 01:41:53,981
- Abu!
- Shajiyettan!

2125
01:41:54,101 --> 01:41:55,540
- I'm leaving this world!
- Shajiyettan!

2126
01:41:55,541 --> 01:41:56,700
My Shajiyettan...!

2127
01:41:56,701 --> 01:41:59,260
- You must pay the van's EMI.
- The bullet didn't hit you, Shajiyettan!

2128
01:41:59,261 --> 01:42:00,661
The shot came from over there.

2129
01:42:01,621 --> 01:42:02,660
Look, it's Sarbath!

2130
01:42:02,661 --> 01:42:04,900
♪ If valour ever claimed a name,
If the fight for truth ignites a flame ♪

2131
01:42:04,901 --> 01:42:06,220
If you create a scene
on the public road,

2132
01:42:06,221 --> 01:42:07,740
I'll shoot all of you
and smoke you away!

2133
01:42:07,741 --> 01:42:08,701
Go home!

2134
01:42:10,661 --> 01:42:11,941
- Paappan...
- What the hell is it?

2135
01:42:12,181 --> 01:42:13,781
I'm going to get that agreement
back from you.

2136
01:42:13,901 --> 01:42:15,460
- Even if I have to kill you for it!
- Dream on!

2137
01:42:15,461 --> 01:42:17,740
- Just wait and see!
- Stop making me laugh. Get going.

2138
01:42:17,741 --> 01:42:19,660
If you don't want to get shot
by the police, disperse!

2139
01:42:19,661 --> 01:42:20,980
Shameer, we'll deal with you later!

2140
01:42:20,981 --> 01:42:22,861
Sir... did you see
that Xavier's attitude, sir?

2141
01:42:23,221 --> 01:42:26,541
You should go there, grab his gun,
and smack him across the face!

2142
01:42:27,461 --> 01:42:28,580
- Hey Dhanaya...
- Yes?

2143
01:42:28,581 --> 01:42:31,621
Every time we see him,
you keep egging me on for no reason.

2144
01:42:31,981 --> 01:42:33,860
Last time when our cars crashed,
only I went flying.

2145
01:42:33,861 --> 01:42:34,900
You didn't fly.

2146
01:42:34,901 --> 01:42:36,980
Switch on the siren!
Let the locals gather.

2147
01:42:36,981 --> 01:42:38,101
Let's embarrass them!

2148
01:42:39,221 --> 01:42:41,261
Shajiyetta, you should've
finished him right here.

2149
01:42:42,421 --> 01:42:44,261
Would a lion waste its time
fighting a rabbit?

2150
01:42:44,541 --> 01:42:45,580
So what if you're
the rabbit, Paappan?

2151
01:42:45,581 --> 01:42:46,981
Don't you have your
own unique strengths?

2152
01:42:47,301 --> 01:42:48,460
I'm the... lion...

2153
01:42:48,461 --> 01:42:49,421
Hey, hey, hey!

2154
01:42:49,701 --> 01:42:52,060
If our Chief steps out,
all hell will break loose!

2155
01:42:52,061 --> 01:42:53,700
- We know.
- What is he, a chimpanzee?

2156
01:42:53,701 --> 01:42:54,741
Let's go.

2157
01:42:56,501 --> 01:42:58,260
Good thing
that Sarbath guy stepped in.

2158
01:42:58,261 --> 01:43:00,020
Otherwise that Satan
would've shot us down!

2159
01:43:00,021 --> 01:43:02,061
Wouldn't it be wiser
to just return the agreement?

2160
01:43:02,221 --> 01:43:03,781
We can move on
to the next scrap deal.

2161
01:43:05,381 --> 01:43:06,461
No, man.

2162
01:43:07,181 --> 01:43:10,221
Something valuable
is hidden inside that bridge.

2163
01:43:10,341 --> 01:43:11,661
- Really?
- I'm certain.

2164
01:43:12,821 --> 01:43:15,380
Otherwise, he wouldn't turn up
all worked up and rattled like this.

2165
01:43:15,381 --> 01:43:16,581
Oh!

2166
01:43:16,981 --> 01:43:19,501
What do you think is actually
inside that bridge, Paappan?

2167
01:43:19,661 --> 01:43:21,621
You wouldn't understand
even if I explained it.

2168
01:43:22,021 --> 01:43:23,061
Inside it,

2169
01:43:23,341 --> 01:43:25,741
there's something that will change
my life, your life,

2170
01:43:26,341 --> 01:43:27,381
and his life.

2171
01:43:34,981 --> 01:43:39,140
My army and I battled Azam Khan
for three long days.

2172
01:43:39,141 --> 01:43:40,181
Three days!

2173
01:43:41,181 --> 01:43:42,180
You got it?

2174
01:43:42,181 --> 01:43:44,461
- When was that?
- At the end of a fierce battle,

2175
01:43:44,781 --> 01:43:46,781
only when no other way remained,

2176
01:43:47,021 --> 01:43:48,421
did we decide to flee.

2177
01:43:48,581 --> 01:43:53,861
And that too because
that stupid King Padmanabhan fled first.

2178
01:43:54,701 --> 01:43:55,741
Full stop.

2179
01:43:56,061 --> 01:43:57,180
Perfect.

2180
01:43:57,181 --> 01:43:58,380
Excuse me, Water sir...

2181
01:43:58,381 --> 01:44:00,820
Could you tell the Viceroy
about us as well, Water sir?

2182
01:44:00,821 --> 01:44:02,780
Just like the story you told now.
Feel free to make it up.

2183
01:44:02,781 --> 01:44:03,741
Why not!

2184
01:44:04,141 --> 01:44:06,180
- Then write down these two lines.
- Write.

2185
01:44:06,181 --> 01:44:07,180
Hype us up!

2186
01:44:07,181 --> 01:44:08,341
Who's that?

2187
01:44:08,701 --> 01:44:09,741
Did you hear something?

2188
01:44:12,141 --> 01:44:13,340
Azam Khan!

2189
01:44:13,341 --> 01:44:14,340
Hide!

2190
01:44:14,341 --> 01:44:15,460
Oh, my god!

2191
01:44:15,461 --> 01:44:16,981
Let's run with Sahib.
Come on!

2192
01:44:22,101 --> 01:44:23,221
Huh!

2193
01:44:26,861 --> 01:44:28,101
What a beautiful maiden!

2194
01:44:28,261 --> 01:44:29,340
- Is she not?
- Indeed.

2195
01:44:29,341 --> 01:44:31,181
A white madam!

2196
01:44:32,061 --> 01:44:34,301
A foreigner is here
without letting me know?

2197
01:44:34,621 --> 01:44:35,620
For what reason?

2198
01:44:35,621 --> 01:44:36,980
And that too a young lady!

2199
01:44:36,981 --> 01:44:39,660
Young or old, sir,
you shouldn't let anyone through.

2200
01:44:39,661 --> 01:44:41,701
- She shall not pass through!
- That's the spirit.

2201
01:44:41,901 --> 01:44:43,620
- I will not let her through!
- Go!

2202
01:44:43,621 --> 01:44:45,301
- Get my coat!
- Okay. Let's go!

2203
01:44:45,421 --> 01:44:46,501
Go.

2204
01:44:48,381 --> 01:44:51,340
♪ Riding wild on destiny ♪

2205
01:44:51,341 --> 01:44:54,260
♪ Charging to the end of time ♪

2206
01:44:54,261 --> 01:44:56,460
♪ Hark, she comes, she comes ♪

2207
01:44:56,461 --> 01:44:59,981
♪ Just as our seers divined ♪

2208
01:45:06,061 --> 01:45:07,180
Easy.

2209
01:45:07,181 --> 01:45:08,341
We come in peace.

2210
01:45:17,021 --> 01:45:18,781
Approach with caution, lady.

2211
01:45:20,141 --> 01:45:22,621
I only wish to speak with
Mr. Walter Joseph.

2212
01:45:23,141 --> 01:45:24,541
I am Walter Joseph.

2213
01:45:24,981 --> 01:45:26,021
Not Mister.

2214
01:45:26,421 --> 01:45:28,221
Lord Walter Joseph!

2215
01:45:28,741 --> 01:45:30,341
Well, well, well.

2216
01:45:30,581 --> 01:45:31,860
Look!

2217
01:45:31,861 --> 01:45:33,980
Who is here in Lord Walter's territory

2218
01:45:33,981 --> 01:45:36,101
without intimating him beforehand?

2219
01:45:36,421 --> 01:45:38,700
I had sent a letter
seeking your permission.

2220
01:45:38,701 --> 01:45:40,021
I regret you didn't receive it.

2221
01:45:40,381 --> 01:45:41,581
I don't care!

2222
01:45:42,141 --> 01:45:44,621
I care about protocols!

2223
01:45:45,461 --> 01:45:47,261
Without my prior permission,

2224
01:45:47,541 --> 01:45:49,181
without considering my convenience...

2225
01:45:49,621 --> 01:45:51,701
and with a group of armed men,

2226
01:45:52,861 --> 01:45:56,101
how dare you trespass here
just to disturb this Walter...

2227
01:45:56,541 --> 01:45:58,620
at a place where I simply
came for a picnic?

2228
01:45:58,621 --> 01:45:59,701
Are you that naive?

2229
01:46:00,221 --> 01:46:01,380
Answer me!

2230
01:46:01,381 --> 01:46:03,021
Water sir is rocking it!

2231
01:46:03,581 --> 01:46:06,901
Or you think your beauty is going
to save you from my wrath, huh?

2232
01:46:07,021 --> 01:46:08,861
- No, sir. I only--
- Shut up!

2233
01:46:08,981 --> 01:46:10,221
Who said, "Hands down"?

2234
01:46:10,421 --> 01:46:11,421
Hands in the air, lady!

2235
01:46:12,101 --> 01:46:13,781
Good, baby girl!

2236
01:46:15,941 --> 01:46:17,181
Mr. Walter...

2237
01:46:17,621 --> 01:46:19,941
I really hate guns
being pointed at my face.

2238
01:46:21,181 --> 01:46:22,580
- Boys!
- Yes?

2239
01:46:22,581 --> 01:46:23,940
You heard that?

2240
01:46:23,941 --> 01:46:25,220
We heard nothing, sir.

2241
01:46:25,221 --> 01:46:26,660
Ask her to say it louder.

2242
01:46:26,661 --> 01:46:30,140
It seems the lady does not fancy
guns pointed at her!

2243
01:46:30,141 --> 01:46:32,021
Is it? Then strike her
with the handle, sir.

2244
01:46:35,861 --> 01:46:38,421
♪ District Magistrate... ♪

2245
01:46:46,701 --> 01:46:47,701
Oh no!

2246
01:46:49,141 --> 01:46:50,261
Walter...

2247
01:46:50,861 --> 01:46:52,381
Tell me about King Padmanabhan.

2248
01:46:52,901 --> 01:46:55,380
It is certain
Padmanabhan will lose his kingdom.

2249
01:46:55,381 --> 01:46:57,980
He may either hide in the woods
or flee the province.

2250
01:46:57,981 --> 01:47:01,100
What becomes of him
no longer concerns the Company.

2251
01:47:01,101 --> 01:47:03,621
For the Company has
already forsaken even me.

2252
01:47:03,821 --> 01:47:04,940
I swear!

2253
01:47:04,941 --> 01:47:06,060
Pinky promise.

2254
01:47:06,061 --> 01:47:08,180
Please do not hurt
our Sahib any further, Madam.

2255
01:47:08,181 --> 01:47:09,461
He is all we have.

2256
01:47:10,501 --> 01:47:11,781
Oh! Is that so?

2257
01:47:13,021 --> 01:47:14,141
Madam...

2258
01:47:14,541 --> 01:47:17,341
Wh... wh... Why do you care
about Padmanabhan?

2259
01:47:17,701 --> 01:47:18,660
Nothing.

2260
01:47:18,661 --> 01:47:20,140
Just a friend in Portugal had asked

2261
01:47:20,141 --> 01:47:22,021
that I convey his regards
to Padmanabhan.

2262
01:47:22,261 --> 01:47:23,421
Right?

2263
01:47:23,781 --> 01:47:24,901
That's all.

2264
01:47:35,781 --> 01:47:38,581
♪ Riding wild on destiny ♪

2265
01:47:38,741 --> 01:47:41,660
♪ Charging to the end of time ♪

2266
01:47:41,661 --> 01:47:43,860
♪ Hark, she comes, she comes ♪

2267
01:47:43,861 --> 01:47:47,300
♪ Just as our seers divined ♪

2268
01:47:47,301 --> 01:47:50,140
♪ We wait, we watch as stars conspire ♪

2269
01:47:50,141 --> 01:47:53,020
♪ We pray, we bow to the cosmic choir ♪

2270
01:47:53,021 --> 01:47:55,300
♪ Lo! She's here, she's here ♪

2271
01:47:55,301 --> 01:47:58,860
♪ To reap death and desire ♪

2272
01:47:58,861 --> 01:48:01,581
♪ Riding wild on destiny ♪

2273
01:48:01,741 --> 01:48:04,660
♪ Charging to the end of time ♪

2274
01:48:04,661 --> 01:48:06,860
♪ Hark, she comes, she comes ♪

2275
01:48:06,861 --> 01:48:10,300
♪ Just as our seers divined ♪

2276
01:48:10,301 --> 01:48:13,140
♪ We wait, we watch as stars conspire ♪

2277
01:48:13,141 --> 01:48:16,060
♪ We pray, we bow to the cosmic choir ♪

2278
01:48:16,061 --> 01:48:17,340
♪ Lo! She's here, she's here ♪

2279
01:48:17,341 --> 01:48:19,021
There's nothing here.
He moved it.

2280
01:48:19,821 --> 01:48:20,900
What now?

2281
01:48:20,901 --> 01:48:23,901
We have to find him
before someone else does.

2282
01:48:25,581 --> 01:48:26,701
Cassandra...

2283
01:48:27,061 --> 01:48:28,101
The informer says...

2284
01:48:28,381 --> 01:48:30,941
Azam Khan has started his march.

2285
01:48:33,181 --> 01:48:34,221
Let's go.

2286
01:48:39,781 --> 01:48:42,181
Our new base of operations
shall be in Mysore.

2287
01:48:42,661 --> 01:48:44,461
We shall build
our future bridges there.

2288
01:48:44,781 --> 01:48:46,260
Then what about our trip
to Travancore?

2289
01:48:46,261 --> 01:48:47,741
Why should the whole lot
rush there?

2290
01:48:48,061 --> 01:48:49,181
Good morning!

2291
01:48:53,301 --> 01:48:54,381
Well done, my subjects.

2292
01:48:54,901 --> 01:48:58,061
I am delighted you have built
a new bridge for my arrival.

2293
01:49:02,741 --> 01:49:04,180
Ordinarily, when such works
are finished,

2294
01:49:04,181 --> 01:49:05,701
kings reward us
with silk and gold.

2295
01:49:06,341 --> 01:49:09,421
This is the first time I'm receiving
a golden necklace with a medallion.

2296
01:49:09,621 --> 01:49:11,861
I shall never forget
this gift in my lifetime!

2297
01:49:12,341 --> 01:49:15,581
As a token of gratitude for building
this magnificent bridge and aiding me,

2298
01:49:15,941 --> 01:49:17,461
hurl this idiot Mappila
into the river!

2299
01:49:18,101 --> 01:49:20,100
Why?
I do not know how to swim, Khan!

2300
01:49:20,101 --> 01:49:21,140
I do not know how to swim!

2301
01:49:21,141 --> 01:49:22,701
- Twice the joy. Splendid!
- Oh no!

2302
01:49:23,181 --> 01:49:24,381
- Dragon!
- My Lord!

2303
01:49:24,781 --> 01:49:26,540
I'm afraid of water snakes!

2304
01:49:26,541 --> 01:49:27,660
Oh no!

2305
01:49:27,661 --> 01:49:29,980
I shall never build a bridge
in any lifetime again!

2306
01:49:29,981 --> 01:49:31,780
I'm scared of water snakes!

2307
01:49:31,781 --> 01:49:33,141
Oh no!

2308
01:49:40,221 --> 01:49:45,741
♪ Ko.. Ko.. Ko...
Koran... Koran... ♪

2309
01:50:12,101 --> 01:50:13,141
Oh my!

2310
01:50:20,581 --> 01:50:21,780
They seem to be good folk.

2311
01:50:21,781 --> 01:50:25,061
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

2312
01:50:28,381 --> 01:50:31,501
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

2313
01:50:38,421 --> 01:50:39,540
Peace be upon you.

2314
01:50:39,541 --> 01:50:41,780
And upon you be peace
and the mercy of Allah...

2315
01:50:41,781 --> 01:50:43,460
Err... the mercy of Allah...

2316
01:50:43,461 --> 01:50:44,581
And His blessings.

2317
01:50:44,741 --> 01:50:46,101
Ah... and His blessings.

2318
01:50:46,221 --> 01:50:47,300
What is your name?

2319
01:50:47,301 --> 01:50:48,381
Abu Salah.

2320
01:50:49,341 --> 01:50:50,860
Have you heard of telescopes?

2321
01:50:50,861 --> 01:50:53,341
No, no! We are not
that sort of people, Lord.

2322
01:50:54,021 --> 01:50:55,101
[in Kannada] Very nice.

2323
01:50:58,781 --> 01:51:00,661
♪ Commander of the Legion,
a hero of might ♪

2324
01:51:04,941 --> 01:51:06,021
Oh no!

2325
01:51:06,381 --> 01:51:07,420
Allah!

2326
01:51:07,421 --> 01:51:09,421
That will not help now, Commander!
O Goddess!

2327
01:51:09,861 --> 01:51:11,021
Oh no!

2328
01:51:11,301 --> 01:51:13,740
Did I not warn you
not to pull hair from the horse's tail

2329
01:51:13,741 --> 01:51:14,940
and stick it on our beards?

2330
01:51:14,941 --> 01:51:16,901
- It's itching as well!
- Oh no!

2331
01:51:41,061 --> 01:51:42,020
A royal massage!

2332
01:51:42,021 --> 01:51:43,181
A royal 'message'!!

2333
01:51:47,421 --> 01:51:48,420
Your Majesty,

2334
01:51:48,421 --> 01:51:49,741
I have fulfilled your command.

2335
01:51:50,181 --> 01:51:52,221
The arch in the heart
of the forest marks the spot.

2336
01:51:52,341 --> 01:51:53,461
Proceed with caution.

2337
01:52:00,501 --> 01:52:01,901
As I said before,

2338
01:52:02,261 --> 01:52:04,061
I shall proceed
from here on my own.

2339
01:52:05,381 --> 01:52:06,461
Do not follow me

2340
01:52:06,981 --> 01:52:08,501
and put yourselves
in danger as well.

2341
01:52:09,301 --> 01:52:10,661
You remember my instructions?

2342
01:52:11,101 --> 01:52:12,621
Go to the secret hideout.

2343
01:52:13,461 --> 01:52:14,661
If I fail to return,

2344
01:52:14,981 --> 01:52:16,861
head straight
to the Chudala hills.

2345
01:52:17,861 --> 01:52:19,220
You need not wait for my return.

2346
01:52:19,221 --> 01:52:21,500
♪ Grandmaster of the duel,
sovereign of the land ♪

2347
01:52:21,501 --> 01:52:23,901
♪ War-dance titan
none may ever withstand ♪

2348
01:52:25,141 --> 01:52:26,260
Look at him go.

2349
01:52:26,261 --> 01:52:27,460
There's nothing on his head.

2350
01:52:27,461 --> 01:52:28,740
- True.
- Huh?

2351
01:52:28,741 --> 01:52:30,180
I meant he isn't
wearing his crown.

2352
01:52:30,181 --> 01:52:31,260
Oh, that's what I meant too.

2353
01:52:31,261 --> 01:52:33,581
♪ O fearless guardian,
protector of the order ♪

2354
01:52:45,421 --> 01:52:46,780
[In Kannada] My dear subjects,

2355
01:52:46,781 --> 01:52:48,060
lend me your ears.

2356
01:52:48,061 --> 01:52:49,260
Is that Sanskrit?

2357
01:52:49,261 --> 01:52:51,061
My war is with kings,

2358
01:52:51,781 --> 01:52:52,941
not with the people.

2359
01:52:54,181 --> 01:52:56,141
Whoever reveals
where the King hides

2360
01:52:56,541 --> 01:52:57,541
may claim this reward.

2361
01:52:58,501 --> 01:52:59,581
Come right here!

2362
01:53:00,661 --> 01:53:02,340
Those gold coins are mine!

2363
01:53:02,341 --> 01:53:03,941
Hold this.
I'm going to tell him.

2364
01:53:04,261 --> 01:53:05,380
Do not tell him.

2365
01:53:05,381 --> 01:53:07,421
It is a trap.
He will never give the coins.

2366
01:53:07,541 --> 01:53:09,340
This is not your
pauper King Pappanabhan

2367
01:53:09,341 --> 01:53:11,020
who cheats men
without paying them.

2368
01:53:11,021 --> 01:53:12,140
This is Azam Khan!

2369
01:53:12,141 --> 01:53:13,181
My Lord!

2370
01:53:13,861 --> 01:53:14,940
I know it, Lord.

2371
01:53:14,941 --> 01:53:16,021
Bravo!

2372
01:53:16,181 --> 01:53:19,060
I am pleased
someone has chosen to cooperate.

2373
01:53:19,061 --> 01:53:21,140
Tell me then.
Where does he hide?

2374
01:53:21,141 --> 01:53:22,140
Where exactly?

2375
01:53:22,141 --> 01:53:23,740
Here... I mean... No!

2376
01:53:23,741 --> 01:53:25,461
Over there... I'm certain.

2377
01:53:26,661 --> 01:53:28,221
Clever fellow.
Very clever.

2378
01:53:28,701 --> 01:53:30,541
Are you not pleased
to have become a rich man?

2379
01:53:31,061 --> 01:53:32,141
He is done for!

2380
01:53:33,421 --> 01:53:34,821
- Who goes there!
- Yes, Lord!

2381
01:53:34,941 --> 01:53:36,341
Prepare the horses!

2382
01:53:36,941 --> 01:53:38,861
I would like a white one
and a red one.

2383
01:53:46,101 --> 01:53:47,221
Oh no!

2384
01:54:01,021 --> 01:54:02,061
Oh my God!

2385
01:54:04,901 --> 01:54:06,021
Relax!

2386
01:54:06,341 --> 01:54:08,021
It is only that fool Koma Kurup

2387
01:54:08,221 --> 01:54:09,261
and his men.

2388
01:54:13,021 --> 01:54:15,100
Where are you rushing
in such haste, Koma Kurup?

2389
01:54:15,101 --> 01:54:16,060
Where is Padmanabhan?

2390
01:54:16,061 --> 01:54:18,821
I am going in search of
King Padmanabhan, Walter Sahib.

2391
01:54:19,101 --> 01:54:20,941
After we allowed the King to flee,

2392
01:54:21,501 --> 01:54:23,700
some of us attempted
to battle Azam Khan ourselves.

2393
01:54:23,701 --> 01:54:26,341
- Oh, is it?
- But the whipping was unbearable.

2394
01:54:27,221 --> 01:54:28,540
What?! Whips in a war?

2395
01:54:28,541 --> 01:54:29,540
Err...

2396
01:54:29,541 --> 01:54:31,300
Not a whip.
It was a whip-sword!

2397
01:54:31,301 --> 01:54:34,420
And... did the army march
past Padmanabhan's kingdom?

2398
01:54:34,421 --> 01:54:36,581
- The army has--
- The army shall go nowhere, Sahib,

2399
01:54:37,061 --> 01:54:40,261
Not until they seize
King Padmanabhan's secret treasure.

2400
01:54:40,381 --> 01:54:41,380
Oh!?

2401
01:54:41,381 --> 01:54:43,300
We are going after him.

2402
01:54:43,301 --> 01:54:44,341
All right.

2403
01:54:45,821 --> 01:54:46,820
Hurry!

2404
01:54:46,821 --> 01:54:47,820
Walter sir,

2405
01:54:47,821 --> 01:54:50,261
could this be the reason
behind that white lady's arrival?

2406
01:54:51,301 --> 01:54:52,421
Cassandra...

2407
01:54:53,101 --> 01:54:54,181
Azam Khan...

2408
01:54:54,301 --> 01:54:56,021
Now all the dots are connected.

2409
01:54:56,581 --> 01:54:58,021
You lying King...

2410
01:54:58,181 --> 01:54:59,541
Your time is up!

2411
01:54:59,901 --> 01:55:01,141
Guys!

2412
01:55:01,821 --> 01:55:04,461
Let's go for a treasure hunt!

2413
01:55:04,621 --> 01:55:05,701
Yeah!

2414
01:55:10,181 --> 01:55:11,261
Antony...

2415
01:55:12,381 --> 01:55:13,501
Did you know?

2416
01:55:14,381 --> 01:55:15,981
I've been seeing my aunty lately.

2417
01:55:17,101 --> 01:55:18,821
Not in my dreams,
but in real life.

2418
01:55:20,021 --> 01:55:21,341
She actually talks to me.

2419
01:55:22,381 --> 01:55:23,821
And I talk back to her.

2420
01:55:25,421 --> 01:55:27,261
You probably think
I've gone crazy, right?

2421
01:55:27,941 --> 01:55:29,181
I'm not crazy, you donkey.

2422
01:55:29,861 --> 01:55:30,901
Sorry, buddy!

2423
01:55:31,581 --> 01:55:32,621
This is...

2424
01:55:33,381 --> 01:55:34,741
extrasensory perception.

2425
01:55:38,101 --> 01:55:39,101
Oh God!

2426
01:55:41,021 --> 01:55:43,421
I can see you laughing at me.

2427
01:55:44,461 --> 01:55:46,341
How could you possibly
believe any of this?

2428
01:55:46,661 --> 01:55:48,460
After all, you're all rationalists, right?

2429
01:55:48,461 --> 01:55:49,821
Oh, my Dude sir!

2430
01:55:53,341 --> 01:55:54,421
Antony...

2431
01:55:54,781 --> 01:55:57,620
I can see Soman, the venomous snake
that once wrapped around my neck,

2432
01:55:57,621 --> 01:55:58,741
standing right behind me.

2433
01:55:59,341 --> 01:56:00,381
Dude sir!

2434
01:56:00,581 --> 01:56:02,660
I can see you sitting here
as well. Clearly.

2435
01:56:02,661 --> 01:56:04,540
So did you attain
extrasensory perception too?

2436
01:56:04,541 --> 01:56:06,501
Of course!
I've got the "sensory" gear too! Ugh!

2437
01:56:06,701 --> 01:56:09,020
Dude sir... what the hell
are you even talking about?

2438
01:56:09,021 --> 01:56:10,060
What is it?

2439
01:56:10,061 --> 01:56:11,620
- Hey, Soman!
- Yeah!

2440
01:56:11,621 --> 01:56:13,300
- How did you get here?
- Me?

2441
01:56:13,301 --> 01:56:15,780
Didn't I slog across
the desert just to meet you, sir?

2442
01:56:15,781 --> 01:56:16,821
- Is that so?
- Yeah!

2443
01:56:19,221 --> 01:56:20,341
Listen!

2444
01:56:20,701 --> 01:56:22,460
I've brought a huge deal.

2445
01:56:22,461 --> 01:56:23,861
- Huh?
- Oh, yeah...

2446
01:56:24,981 --> 01:56:26,181
It's a mega jackpot!

2447
01:56:26,901 --> 01:56:29,540
[In Tamil] Does this face
look like someone who wins jackpots?

2448
01:56:29,541 --> 01:56:30,500
Yes, it does.

2449
01:56:30,501 --> 01:56:31,460
"Dude!"

2450
01:56:31,461 --> 01:56:33,141
I've left
that life behind, Soman.

2451
01:56:33,901 --> 01:56:35,820
Dilman died long ago
in another life.

2452
01:56:35,821 --> 01:56:36,820
When?

2453
01:56:36,821 --> 01:56:38,701
All that remains now
is Sulaiman.

2454
01:56:39,541 --> 01:56:41,020
I'm perfectly content
with my life now.

2455
01:56:41,021 --> 01:56:42,100
But I'm not!

2456
01:56:42,101 --> 01:56:43,461
- You know why?
- Why?

2457
01:56:44,861 --> 01:56:46,460
Because I killed my ambition.

2458
01:56:46,461 --> 01:56:47,500
My god!

2459
01:56:47,501 --> 01:56:49,141
You killed Nambeeshan?

2460
01:56:51,661 --> 01:56:54,021
If you don't come, Paappan is going
to grab the jackpot!

2461
01:56:55,461 --> 01:56:56,581
Paappan?

2462
01:56:56,821 --> 01:56:58,581
- That bloody village bumpkin?
- Yes.

2463
01:56:58,821 --> 01:57:02,261
That village bumpkin who never lets us
succeed, no matter what!

2464
01:57:02,421 --> 01:57:03,581
That bloody Paappan!

2465
01:57:10,781 --> 01:57:13,661
Boss, if you set me free,
with a few resources,

2466
01:57:14,381 --> 01:57:16,781
we'll rake in
crores, boss, crores!

2467
01:57:17,181 --> 01:57:18,941
Fifty percent will be yours, Boss!

2468
01:57:20,141 --> 01:57:21,141
Huh!

2469
01:57:23,341 --> 01:57:24,381
Huh!

2470
01:57:30,741 --> 01:57:31,941
- Dude!
- Oh no!

2471
01:57:33,461 --> 01:57:35,461
- Hey, Sulaiman...
- Yes, Boss!

2472
01:57:35,621 --> 01:57:37,901
You don't know the rules of our gang.

2473
01:57:38,701 --> 01:57:40,421
You are my property.

2474
01:57:40,741 --> 01:57:44,261
I will be the owner
of everything you get!

2475
01:57:44,661 --> 01:57:46,421
The entire 100% will be mine!

2476
01:57:46,781 --> 01:57:47,901
That's the deal.

2477
01:57:48,621 --> 01:57:50,101
Do you understand, sir?

2478
01:57:50,461 --> 01:57:51,981
I have heard this somewhere before!

2479
01:57:52,141 --> 01:57:54,221
Boss, I agree to this deal!

2480
01:57:54,661 --> 01:57:55,981
Thank you, Boss!
Thank you!

2481
01:57:56,781 --> 01:57:57,781
You scoundrel!

2482
01:57:58,101 --> 01:57:59,900
The minute I step out of here,
I'll vanish.

2483
01:57:59,901 --> 01:58:02,221
You won't find a single trace of me,
however hard you try.

2484
01:58:02,941 --> 01:58:04,021
Hey, Azhaku!

2485
01:58:04,541 --> 01:58:05,901
Call Pulikesi.

2486
01:58:14,821 --> 01:58:16,021
- Nice undies!
- Of course!

2487
01:58:16,741 --> 01:58:17,820
Superb!

2488
01:58:17,821 --> 01:58:19,780
I don't wear local undies, Boss.

2489
01:58:19,781 --> 01:58:20,901
I prefer Armani.

2490
01:58:21,621 --> 01:58:23,381
This isn't Armani.

2491
01:58:23,781 --> 01:58:24,780
Then?

2492
01:58:24,781 --> 01:58:27,220
It's "Harm"ani.
Way more deadly!

2493
01:58:27,221 --> 01:58:28,380
Really?

2494
01:58:28,381 --> 01:58:29,541
Yes, it is.

2495
01:58:29,781 --> 01:58:31,540
You're right.
It's making a buzzing sound!

2496
01:58:31,541 --> 01:58:34,100
Those undies carry
an electric current, Sulaiman.

2497
01:58:34,101 --> 01:58:35,421
That's the noise you're hearing.

2498
01:58:36,941 --> 01:58:38,661
Don't stress yourself out.

2499
01:58:39,061 --> 01:58:41,300
There are holes for
number one and two.

2500
01:58:41,301 --> 01:58:43,141
Why do his undies
need a power supply?

2501
01:58:51,781 --> 01:58:52,740
For this!

2502
01:58:52,741 --> 01:58:53,740
Boss!

2503
01:58:53,741 --> 01:58:56,061
If you talk too much
or cross your limits,

2504
01:58:56,301 --> 01:58:58,100
you'll get a shock, just like this.

2505
01:58:58,101 --> 01:59:00,341
Even if the thought
of removing them crosses your mind,

2506
01:59:01,101 --> 01:59:04,821
the GPS will trigger a blast
and you'll be finished.

2507
01:59:07,421 --> 01:59:09,421
- Pulikesi...
- Yes, Boss!

2508
01:59:11,221 --> 01:59:13,301
Pulikesi will come with you.

2509
01:59:13,501 --> 01:59:14,540
Okay?

2510
01:59:14,541 --> 01:59:17,940
If you even think
of escaping from him...

2511
01:59:17,941 --> 01:59:19,381
I'll press the button immediately!

2512
01:59:19,701 --> 01:59:21,021
You'll be reduced to dust!

2513
01:59:21,821 --> 01:59:24,181
What, Sulaiman?
Is this deal okay?

2514
01:59:24,421 --> 01:59:25,740
Why even bother asking him?

2515
01:59:25,741 --> 01:59:26,981
He is ready for everything.

2516
01:59:27,221 --> 01:59:28,701
- Aren't you?
- Yes.

2517
01:59:31,661 --> 01:59:32,781
Don't be upset.

2518
01:59:33,061 --> 01:59:34,580
I'm going to take you
away from here.

2519
01:59:34,581 --> 01:59:36,381
I won't let you suffer
here for long.

2520
01:59:37,461 --> 01:59:39,540
And that boss of ours?
I'll finish him!

2521
01:59:39,541 --> 01:59:41,420
I blew up his uncle's shop
with a bomb!

2522
01:59:41,421 --> 01:59:42,981
You don't know me well enough.

2523
01:59:44,101 --> 01:59:45,421
What the hell is this, Paily?

2524
01:59:45,541 --> 01:59:46,740
Okay, my bro!

2525
01:59:46,741 --> 01:59:48,461
- This is 'The Donkey Life'!
- Huh!

2526
01:59:49,221 --> 01:59:50,301
Don't be sad.

2527
01:59:50,541 --> 01:59:52,181
- He is like this now.
- I'll see you soon.

2528
01:59:57,381 --> 01:59:59,381
Sitting on ticking time bombs

2529
01:59:59,661 --> 02:00:02,501
and playing "Mission Impossible"
is nothing new to me.

2530
02:00:03,101 --> 02:00:04,301
- Let's go, boys.
- Sir...

2531
02:00:04,781 --> 02:00:07,020
Don't forget me
once you get what you want.

2532
02:00:07,021 --> 02:00:08,901
At least this time,
I have to make it big!

2533
02:00:10,941 --> 02:00:12,101
Of course, Soman.

2534
02:00:12,341 --> 02:00:14,101
Announce it to the whole world...

2535
02:00:14,581 --> 02:00:15,580
Once again,

2536
02:00:15,581 --> 02:00:16,860
Dude is on the way!

2537
02:00:16,861 --> 02:00:17,980
- Yeah!
- Yes!

2538
02:00:17,981 --> 02:00:19,140
Dear fellow citizens,

2539
02:00:19,141 --> 02:00:22,620
this sturdy Nagathan Bridge,
which has served us for centuries,

2540
02:00:22,621 --> 02:00:24,660
is being demolished
via controlled implosion

2541
02:00:24,661 --> 02:00:26,220
for no particular reason.

2542
02:00:26,221 --> 02:00:30,500
King Padmanabha, who ruled
these highlands in the 1800s,

2543
02:00:30,501 --> 02:00:32,541
completed the construction
of this bridge

2544
02:00:32,661 --> 02:00:37,501
in collaboration with Walter Joseph
of the British East India Company.

2545
02:00:37,741 --> 02:00:40,700
At that time, the construction
of this bridge was spearheaded

2546
02:00:40,701 --> 02:00:43,940
by the eminent engineer,
Vareeth Mappila.

2547
02:00:43,941 --> 02:00:46,860
You have to give credit to Mappila,
that engineer who built this bridge!

2548
02:00:46,861 --> 02:00:49,460
Look at it, standing firm
for over three hundred years!

2549
02:00:49,461 --> 02:00:50,740
But didn't Aashaan say
that it was shaking?

2550
02:00:50,741 --> 02:00:51,820
Shut up!

2551
02:00:51,821 --> 02:00:54,260
[media reports]

2552
02:00:54,261 --> 02:00:55,260
- Paappan...
- Yes?

2553
02:00:55,261 --> 02:00:56,940
- Satan Xavier!
- Don't look at him.

2554
02:00:56,941 --> 02:00:58,300
That's the opposition's allegation.

2555
02:00:58,301 --> 02:01:00,660
Minister P.P. Shashi took to social media

2556
02:01:00,661 --> 02:01:03,100
to state that wise administrators
prioritise public safety

2557
02:01:03,101 --> 02:01:05,341
by pre-emptively eliminating
potential hazards.

2558
02:01:07,861 --> 02:01:09,740
What are you doing,
you frog-face?

2559
02:01:09,741 --> 02:01:11,740
It's your first scrap deal, right?
Let's shoot a reel.

2560
02:01:11,741 --> 02:01:13,500
I'll break that thing
and throw it in the water!

2561
02:01:13,501 --> 02:01:14,500
You've been at it
for quite a while now!

2562
02:01:14,501 --> 02:01:15,500
Making a reel
while the bridge blows up!

2563
02:01:15,501 --> 02:01:17,581
Paappan, you're giving off
major "Dad vibes" right now.

2564
02:01:17,781 --> 02:01:21,141
Yes. My "Dad vibe" is better than
your "Dad-less vibe"!

2565
02:01:21,341 --> 02:01:23,381
Sigh!
Emotional damage!

2566
02:01:25,381 --> 02:01:27,700
Quit grinning and make sure
you grab everything once it explodes.

2567
02:01:27,701 --> 02:01:30,340
What if the bridge collapses on my head
and I die, Shajiyetta?

2568
02:01:30,341 --> 02:01:31,861
Wouldn't that be a heroic death?

2569
02:01:32,781 --> 02:01:34,941
We must rush there
as soon as the bridge collapses.

2570
02:01:35,461 --> 02:01:38,061
Let them take the stones, iron,
cement, or gravel.

2571
02:01:38,341 --> 02:01:40,700
There will be boxes hidden there.
We must take those.

2572
02:01:40,701 --> 02:01:41,861
Sir... one doubt.

2573
02:01:42,101 --> 02:01:44,500
What if Sarbath shoots us in the butt
while we're running there?

2574
02:01:44,501 --> 02:01:45,660
- Shut up!
- Yes.

2575
02:01:45,661 --> 02:01:47,141
Precisely because of that danger,

2576
02:01:47,461 --> 02:01:48,621
only you two are going.

2577
02:01:49,061 --> 02:01:50,061
Just us?

2578
02:01:50,381 --> 02:01:51,941
The countdown will begin shortly.

2579
02:01:52,061 --> 02:01:53,620
Welcome to the bridge
demolition festival...

2580
02:01:53,621 --> 02:01:54,500
- It's procedure!
- Errr...

2581
02:01:54,501 --> 02:01:56,021
Everyone is welcome
to witness the procedure.

2582
02:01:56,901 --> 02:01:59,941
This explosion will give me
plenty of Satan's stones.

2583
02:02:00,061 --> 02:02:02,141
Will you really get
Satan's stones, Aashaan?

2584
02:02:02,661 --> 02:02:05,260
Why are you glued to me?
Stand back and listen to the countdown.

2585
02:02:05,261 --> 02:02:07,060
- Damn you!
- Thousands of residents across

2586
02:02:07,061 --> 02:02:09,100
the neighbouring areas
of the Nagathan Bridge,

2587
02:02:09,101 --> 02:02:11,660
including Muthiyanmala,
Pothumukku, and Marayikkonam

2588
02:02:11,661 --> 02:02:15,541
are set to face severe travel hardships
following the bridge's demolition.

2589
02:02:15,661 --> 02:02:17,500
And... as soon as
the bridge collapses,

2590
02:02:17,501 --> 02:02:20,380
those rascals Paappan and Xavier
will start tearing into each other.

2591
02:02:20,381 --> 02:02:22,140
We must reach the spot
before anyone else.

2592
02:02:22,141 --> 02:02:23,901
They should step in
only under our control.

2593
02:02:27,621 --> 02:02:28,901
Okay.
Are you ready, sir?

2594
02:02:29,301 --> 02:02:31,301
Yes, ready.
Countdown begins.

2595
02:02:31,621 --> 02:02:32,701
Ten...

2596
02:02:32,861 --> 02:02:34,100
Nine...

2597
02:02:34,101 --> 02:02:35,340
Eight...

2598
02:02:35,341 --> 02:02:36,620
Seven...

2599
02:02:36,621 --> 02:02:37,820
Six...

2600
02:02:37,821 --> 02:02:39,060
Five...

2601
02:02:39,061 --> 02:02:40,300
Four...

2602
02:02:40,301 --> 02:02:41,341
Three...

2603
02:02:41,501 --> 02:02:42,580
Two...

2604
02:02:42,581 --> 02:02:43,621
One!

2605
02:02:52,581 --> 02:02:54,301
Run, Soman!

2606
02:02:54,981 --> 02:02:56,220
The explosion has just happened.

2607
02:02:56,221 --> 02:02:57,380
The historic bridge...

2608
02:02:57,381 --> 02:03:00,061
- There's a helicopter above the bridge.
- Look, a helicopter!

2609
02:03:03,021 --> 02:03:04,261
Huh! Who's that?

2610
02:03:06,221 --> 02:03:07,541
What on earth is that?
A vulture?

2611
02:03:09,381 --> 02:03:11,741
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

2612
02:03:12,781 --> 02:03:14,581
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

2613
02:03:15,821 --> 02:03:17,861
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

2614
02:03:20,141 --> 02:03:21,901
Who the hell is that?!

2615
02:03:22,341 --> 02:03:24,101
No, Shajiyetta!
That's the gunman!

2616
02:03:24,461 --> 02:03:25,780
Is he dead and going to heaven?

2617
02:03:25,781 --> 02:03:27,581
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

2618
02:03:28,861 --> 02:03:30,340
He's not going
to heaven, Paappan.

2619
02:03:30,341 --> 02:03:31,980
He's making off with our stuff!

2620
02:03:31,981 --> 02:03:34,020
There's something
in those boxes, Shajiyetta!

2621
02:03:34,021 --> 02:03:36,781
Otherwise, he wouldn't have hired
a helicopter to get here, Paappan.

2622
02:03:37,101 --> 02:03:39,061
Do you recognise him, sir?

2623
02:03:40,181 --> 02:03:41,301
That scoundrel in the suit!

2624
02:03:41,821 --> 02:03:44,660
- He is the "Dude"!
- Yay!

2625
02:03:44,661 --> 02:03:46,300
Oh no!
This is that other fellow!

2626
02:03:46,301 --> 02:03:47,860
- Dude sir!
- Huh!

2627
02:03:47,861 --> 02:03:49,861
- Yeah, the boxes!
- ♪ DUDE ♪

2628
02:03:51,421 --> 02:03:53,381
Hasta la vista, skibidis!

2629
02:03:54,301 --> 02:03:55,820
Turn it around!

2630
02:03:55,821 --> 02:03:57,300
Go! Fly away!

2631
02:03:57,301 --> 02:03:59,141
Go fast, man!

2632
02:04:01,101 --> 02:04:02,941
♪ DUDE ♪

2633
02:04:04,221 --> 02:04:06,060
Don't go!
Please don't go!

2634
02:04:06,061 --> 02:04:08,540
A helicopter is flying away
from the bridge after the explosion.

2635
02:04:08,541 --> 02:04:10,700
Listen to your police uncle!
Drop the boxes!

2636
02:04:10,701 --> 02:04:11,821
Drop the boxes!

2637
02:04:13,581 --> 02:04:14,781
It's gone!

2638
02:04:15,021 --> 02:04:16,181
That's gone!

2639
02:04:19,501 --> 02:04:21,300
The bridge was demolished
very well, Aashaan.

2640
02:04:21,301 --> 02:04:22,821
You...!
I saw the whole thing.

2641
02:04:23,541 --> 02:04:26,020
I want those boxes you just
waved goodbye to, right now.

2642
02:04:26,021 --> 02:04:27,940
No, Aashaan!
I wasn't waving goodbye!

2643
02:04:27,941 --> 02:04:30,340
- I was saying "don't go, don't go."
- Shut up!

2644
02:04:30,341 --> 02:04:32,621
Are you all ganging up to trick me?

2645
02:04:32,901 --> 02:04:34,661
If you don't bring the goods…

2646
02:04:35,101 --> 02:04:38,901
The red snappers and ribbonfish
in my dam are starving.

2647
02:04:39,421 --> 02:04:40,701
I'll serve them

2648
02:04:41,421 --> 02:04:44,181
a chilled Soda Sarbath
brewed from your blood!

2649
02:04:45,021 --> 02:04:46,981
- No, Aashaan! No!
- I need my blood.

2650
02:04:47,461 --> 02:04:49,661
You'll get your boxes
in no time, Aashaan!

2651
02:04:49,901 --> 02:04:51,180
I need your blessings, Aashaan.

2652
02:04:51,181 --> 02:04:52,741
Go find those boxes, you dog!

2653
02:04:54,221 --> 02:04:55,500
- Start the jeep!
- Sir!

2654
02:04:55,501 --> 02:04:57,301
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

2655
02:04:59,821 --> 02:05:01,221
- Yeah!
- Come up!

2656
02:05:02,621 --> 02:05:03,780
Thank you, boys!

2657
02:05:03,781 --> 02:05:05,221
Yaay, yaay, yaay!

2658
02:05:10,901 --> 02:05:12,021
♪ Paappan, Paappan ♪

2659
02:05:12,661 --> 02:05:13,861
♪ The elder Paappan ♪

2660
02:05:14,421 --> 02:05:15,780
♪ Paappan, Paappan ♪

2661
02:05:15,781 --> 02:05:17,821
- Throw the net, Thankappan!
- ♪ Thomas Paappan ♪

2662
02:05:17,981 --> 02:05:19,101
♪ Paappan, Paappan ♪

2663
02:05:19,781 --> 02:05:20,981
♪ The elder Paappan ♪

2664
02:05:21,501 --> 02:05:22,700
♪ Paappan, Paappan ♪

2665
02:05:22,701 --> 02:05:24,861
- Hey! Psst!
- ♪ Thomas Paappan ♪

2666
02:05:26,581 --> 02:05:28,381
You bloody old village bumpkins!

2667
02:05:28,621 --> 02:05:29,621
You again?!

2668
02:05:29,901 --> 02:05:32,340
Hey, I warned you long ago

2669
02:05:32,341 --> 02:05:34,901
not to come to the High Range hills
and mess with my boys.

2670
02:05:35,221 --> 02:05:36,501
He'll tell you the rest.

2671
02:05:40,221 --> 02:05:44,061
♪ Even Haji Mastan would salute the man,
The brave and mighty Shaji Paappan ♪

2672
02:05:44,781 --> 02:05:46,901
Is that...
the bloody village bumpkin?

2673
02:05:47,501 --> 02:05:51,101
♪ Even Haji Mastan would salute the man,
The brave and mighty Shaji Paappan ♪

2674
02:05:51,261 --> 02:05:52,381
Bloody nemesis!

2675
02:05:52,501 --> 02:05:53,741
My archenemy!

2676
02:05:54,781 --> 02:05:55,861
- Martin!
- Yes, Paappan!

2677
02:05:56,341 --> 02:05:57,381
Step on it!

2678
02:05:57,621 --> 02:05:59,341
I've got a scarecrow to roast.

2679
02:06:03,941 --> 02:06:05,900
- That was awesome, brother!
- You bet!

2680
02:06:05,901 --> 02:06:07,061
Hey there, Mr. Gunman!

2681
02:06:07,381 --> 02:06:08,421
What did you think?

2682
02:06:08,701 --> 02:06:10,301
That I wouldn't expect you?

2683
02:06:10,461 --> 02:06:13,301
Every time the Lord
blesses me with something,

2684
02:06:13,581 --> 02:06:17,101
why do you always come after me
in that filthy jacket to mess it up?

2685
02:06:18,701 --> 02:06:19,861
Any time, guys!

2686
02:06:27,661 --> 02:06:29,221
You bloody village bumpkin!

2687
02:06:30,061 --> 02:06:31,141
I will--

2688
02:06:32,341 --> 02:06:33,661
Listen up, you moron!

2689
02:06:33,861 --> 02:06:35,181
You better watch your back!

2690
02:06:35,621 --> 02:06:37,461
If you come after me again,

2691
02:06:37,821 --> 02:06:40,181
I'll shove a bomb down your throat
and blow you to bits!

2692
02:06:40,661 --> 02:06:41,660
Oh no!

2693
02:06:41,661 --> 02:06:43,061
- Oh no! A bomb!
- Oh God!

2694
02:06:43,181 --> 02:06:44,261
Bomb!

2695
02:06:54,581 --> 02:06:55,701
Oh no! The boxes!

2696
02:06:57,981 --> 02:06:59,261
What the hell just happened?

2697
02:07:00,621 --> 02:07:01,900
Hey Shaji...

2698
02:07:01,901 --> 02:07:03,500
You kept bragging
about planting bombs…

2699
02:07:03,501 --> 02:07:05,940
And you planted one
under our own butts? You moron!

2700
02:07:05,941 --> 02:07:08,141
This wasn't my bomb, Chettayi!

2701
02:07:08,421 --> 02:07:10,581
Don't you know
our bombs never explode?

2702
02:07:10,821 --> 02:07:12,460
This was planted by someone
who knows their job.

2703
02:07:12,461 --> 02:07:14,700
Whoever it is, don't come back
until you take him down.

2704
02:07:14,701 --> 02:07:16,460
Let me reach the shore first
before I get taken down.

2705
02:07:16,461 --> 02:07:17,661
Where is the shore now?

2706
02:07:21,501 --> 02:07:23,301
Andre, fetch our things.

2707
02:07:23,541 --> 02:07:24,501
Yeah!

2708
02:07:24,821 --> 02:07:27,301
You know what to do
in situations like this, right?

2709
02:07:27,981 --> 02:07:29,061
Yeah!

2710
02:07:30,861 --> 02:07:31,940
Okay.

2711
02:07:31,941 --> 02:07:33,021
I understand.

2712
02:07:33,381 --> 02:07:34,541
Thanks.

2713
02:07:35,021 --> 02:07:36,060
Listen up, guys.

2714
02:07:36,061 --> 02:07:37,741
Change of plans.
We're going to go to--

2715
02:07:38,581 --> 02:07:42,141
♪ Shameer... Shameer...
O Sarbath Shameer! ♪

2716
02:07:43,021 --> 02:07:44,180
No.

2717
02:07:44,181 --> 02:07:46,261
Don't shoot the police.
It will only cause trouble.

2718
02:07:53,661 --> 02:07:54,981
Bloody bombers!

2719
02:07:59,381 --> 02:08:01,221
Did that rascal reach that shore?

2720
02:08:01,781 --> 02:08:04,621
So now even foreigners
are messing with my job!

2721
02:08:04,861 --> 02:08:07,221
- Officer, we were just trying to--
- Where are the boxes?

2722
02:08:07,621 --> 02:08:08,980
The boxes are in that vehicle.

2723
02:08:08,981 --> 02:08:12,260
Well, sir... didn't we hear that
the British helped build this bridge?

2724
02:08:12,261 --> 02:08:14,620
What if they're taking the boxes
they left behind while building it?

2725
02:08:14,621 --> 02:08:16,100
Then it's "lost and found,"
right, sir?

2726
02:08:16,101 --> 02:08:18,301
Explain our laws to them, sir.

2727
02:08:18,941 --> 02:08:21,100
- Alright. I'll explain it in English.
- Got the key!

2728
02:08:21,101 --> 02:08:22,661
Madam, listen carefully.

2729
02:08:23,181 --> 02:08:24,261
This box...

2730
02:08:24,581 --> 02:08:25,821
Bridge broke.

2731
02:08:26,261 --> 02:08:27,741
One dog take the box.

2732
02:08:28,021 --> 02:08:29,261
Aashaan waiting.

2733
02:08:29,381 --> 02:08:31,780
And you come take, I no--

2734
02:08:31,781 --> 02:08:34,180
[In Malayalam]
You're a special kind of fool, officer!

2735
02:08:34,181 --> 02:08:35,660
- A fool?
- Huh! No need subtitles!

2736
02:08:35,661 --> 02:08:37,460
Dhanaya, she knows Malayalam!

2737
02:08:37,461 --> 02:08:38,581
Hands up, woman!

2738
02:08:39,741 --> 02:08:42,260
Officer, I hate guns
being pointed at my face.

2739
02:08:42,261 --> 02:08:43,780
Hmph!
What did she just say?

2740
02:08:43,781 --> 02:08:46,180
She says she hates guns
being pointed at her face.

2741
02:08:46,181 --> 02:08:47,220
Oh, really?

2742
02:08:47,221 --> 02:08:48,461
What will she--

2743
02:08:51,541 --> 02:08:52,581
- Sir!
- It's true!

2744
02:08:53,021 --> 02:08:54,461
She really hates it!

2745
02:08:55,661 --> 02:08:56,821
Sir!

2746
02:08:57,541 --> 02:08:58,621
Hello...

2747
02:08:59,941 --> 02:09:01,101
Run for your lives!

2748
02:09:05,501 --> 02:09:08,061
♪ The burning fire ♪

2749
02:09:08,341 --> 02:09:10,020
There's room for only one foreigner
around here!

2750
02:09:10,021 --> 02:09:11,060
You heard that?

2751
02:09:11,061 --> 02:09:12,101
Useless buffalo!

2752
02:09:12,941 --> 02:09:15,781
♪ Go home, little girl ♪

2753
02:09:16,341 --> 02:09:19,301
♪ Striking like high-voltage
lightning crashing to the ground ♪

2754
02:09:20,101 --> 02:09:21,101
Shit!

2755
02:09:24,821 --> 02:09:25,861
Come out! Come out!

2756
02:09:35,941 --> 02:09:37,101
Bullshit!

2757
02:09:38,981 --> 02:09:40,381
Where are the boxes, Shajiyetta?

2758
02:09:40,901 --> 02:09:43,180
I couldn't search for it
in the chaos after the blast.

2759
02:09:43,181 --> 02:09:44,100
Sigh!

2760
02:09:44,101 --> 02:09:45,460
I'm really curious!

2761
02:09:45,461 --> 02:09:46,580
My dear Dude sir,

2762
02:09:46,581 --> 02:09:48,501
when will you learn to handle
a box properly?

2763
02:09:49,781 --> 02:09:50,901
Mr. Dragon...

2764
02:09:51,541 --> 02:09:52,821
I'll be asking the questions.

2765
02:09:53,101 --> 02:09:54,100
Where is my chopper?

2766
02:09:54,101 --> 02:09:55,620
The chopper?
When you fell into the water,

2767
02:09:55,621 --> 02:09:57,780
it dropped us
at a nearby school ground.

2768
02:09:57,781 --> 02:09:59,900
Then the chopper driver
flew off with it.

2769
02:09:59,901 --> 02:10:02,140
I waved goodbye and thanked him.

2770
02:10:02,141 --> 02:10:03,020
What else could we do?

2771
02:10:03,021 --> 02:10:05,340
Then we spotted a vehicle, hijacked it,
and came straight here.

2772
02:10:05,341 --> 02:10:06,581
Happy?

2773
02:10:07,261 --> 02:10:08,781
- Very good.
- Oh no!

2774
02:10:12,301 --> 02:10:14,020
You lost the chopper just when

2775
02:10:14,021 --> 02:10:16,461
a high-speed chase
was about to start? Stupid!

2776
02:10:18,181 --> 02:10:19,301
Idiots!

2777
02:10:19,621 --> 02:10:20,661
Idiots!

2778
02:10:21,141 --> 02:10:22,380
Bad Idiots!

2779
02:10:22,381 --> 02:10:24,221
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

2780
02:10:25,461 --> 02:10:27,100
Even a dog wouldn't want
a Paappan who lost the boxes.

2781
02:10:27,101 --> 02:10:28,140
Just jump back into the water.

2782
02:10:28,141 --> 02:10:29,901
I'll smash that
useless head of yours—

2783
02:10:30,181 --> 02:10:32,581
- You bloody village bumpkin!!!
- I didn't die because... Huh!

2784
02:10:33,141 --> 02:10:34,301
What, you beggar?

2785
02:10:34,541 --> 02:10:35,541
This isn't over yet!

2786
02:10:35,741 --> 02:10:37,620
I'll incinerate you
and that ride of yours.

2787
02:10:37,621 --> 02:10:38,861
And your village...

2788
02:10:39,021 --> 02:10:40,140
I'll burn it to the ground!

2789
02:10:40,141 --> 02:10:41,380
Then come here and burn it!

2790
02:10:41,381 --> 02:10:43,340
I'll write 'village'
on a piece of paper.

2791
02:10:43,341 --> 02:10:44,500
Take it and go burn that.

2792
02:10:44,501 --> 02:10:46,500
But you don't know
how to write 'village, ' Paappan!

2793
02:10:46,501 --> 02:10:47,820
He doesn't know
that I don't know it!

2794
02:10:47,821 --> 02:10:48,861
Get lost, you dog!

2795
02:10:51,181 --> 02:10:52,860
- He's crying sadly.
- No.

2796
02:10:52,861 --> 02:10:54,381
- He's making faces at us.
- Like this?

2797
02:10:55,301 --> 02:10:56,981
- Yeah, that's what he's doing.
- Oh yeah?

2798
02:10:58,661 --> 02:10:59,941
Wow, such a perfect monkey!

2799
02:11:02,421 --> 02:11:03,820
Don't give up, Dude sir!

2800
02:11:03,821 --> 02:11:04,901
Keep up, Abu!

2801
02:11:09,541 --> 02:11:10,701
Forget it.

2802
02:11:10,901 --> 02:11:12,460
He's better at making faces.

2803
02:11:12,461 --> 02:11:14,020
- We might lose.
- Shajiyetta!

2804
02:11:14,021 --> 02:11:15,260
Don't give up, Dude sir!

2805
02:11:15,261 --> 02:11:16,581
Damn! A phone call
right now!

2806
02:11:23,381 --> 02:11:24,660
Mr. Village Bumpkin!

2807
02:11:24,661 --> 02:11:25,700
What?

2808
02:11:25,701 --> 02:11:28,381
The chopper pilot told me
which way the boxes went.

2809
02:11:31,901 --> 02:11:33,061
Have a good day!

2810
02:11:33,501 --> 02:11:34,781
He said "Have a good day."

2811
02:11:34,941 --> 02:11:36,141
What do we do, Shajiyetta?

2812
02:11:36,501 --> 02:11:37,580
Shajiyetta...

2813
02:11:37,581 --> 02:11:38,861
Look, your brother is calling.

2814
02:11:40,061 --> 02:11:42,420
Chettayi, someone took the boxes.

2815
02:11:42,421 --> 02:11:44,580
It wasn't just anyone.
It was Satan Xavier!

2816
02:11:44,581 --> 02:11:46,180
He's heading for the border.

2817
02:11:46,181 --> 02:11:47,381
Hurry up!

2818
02:11:48,221 --> 02:11:49,421
Come on, boys!

2819
02:11:49,581 --> 02:11:51,541
- I won't let him get away!
- Start the van, Paappan!

2820
02:11:51,821 --> 02:11:53,420
♪ Stardust falling down ♪

2821
02:11:53,421 --> 02:11:54,861
♪ Oh baby who gonna catch it ♪

2822
02:11:55,141 --> 02:11:56,900
♪ The treasure's flyin off ♪

2823
02:11:56,901 --> 02:11:58,500
♪ Paappan's running for it ♪

2824
02:11:58,501 --> 02:12:00,380
♪ Crazy like the Aries
Cool with the shades on ♪

2825
02:12:00,381 --> 02:12:01,860
♪ Moving in a hurry
Gotta get the star back ♪

2826
02:12:01,861 --> 02:12:03,540
♪ Paappan's in a hurry,
Paappan's in a hurry ♪

2827
02:12:03,541 --> 02:12:04,781
♪ Move aside, boy ♪

2828
02:12:04,941 --> 02:12:06,500
♪ No time to play around ♪

2829
02:12:06,501 --> 02:12:08,180
♪ The dude is on the front ♪

2830
02:12:08,181 --> 02:12:12,461
♪ If you wanna win the chase,
you better run ♪

2831
02:12:13,901 --> 02:12:15,020
♪ You better run ♪

2832
02:12:15,021 --> 02:12:17,341
From here, we head directly
to Madurai this evening.

2833
02:12:17,461 --> 02:12:21,621
A container must be ready there
to head to Dubai port.

2834
02:12:21,981 --> 02:12:24,261
I need no mistakes!

2835
02:12:24,701 --> 02:12:26,061
We're all going together, right?

2836
02:12:26,341 --> 02:12:27,380
- No.
- Oh.

2837
02:12:27,381 --> 02:12:28,581
I'm going to Portugal.

2838
02:12:28,701 --> 02:12:29,941
You're going to Pollachi.

2839
02:12:31,341 --> 02:12:32,461
Ugh!

2840
02:12:32,701 --> 02:12:34,741
- Dude was better than this guy.
- Who?

2841
02:12:37,781 --> 02:12:38,940
Brief me, Jack.

2842
02:12:38,941 --> 02:12:40,020
Lara...

2843
02:12:40,021 --> 02:12:42,021
The organisation is not happy.

2844
02:12:42,661 --> 02:12:45,181
I have covered this one for you,
but do not mess up.

2845
02:12:45,621 --> 02:12:47,141
Thanks, Jack.
I owe you one.

2846
02:12:47,501 --> 02:12:49,061
Please send a party to intercept.

2847
02:12:49,341 --> 02:12:50,460
Already did.

2848
02:12:50,461 --> 02:12:52,820
It's almost time
and we need Star Dust.

2849
02:12:52,821 --> 02:12:53,861
Do not fail.

2850
02:12:54,061 --> 02:12:55,180
I won't.

2851
02:12:55,181 --> 02:12:56,901
What happened was just a small delay.

2852
02:12:57,181 --> 02:12:59,061
Well, no more delays then.

2853
02:13:03,261 --> 02:13:04,301
Shit!

2854
02:13:07,541 --> 02:13:09,581
Boys, your lifetime settlement

2855
02:13:10,421 --> 02:13:11,980
is waiting in this
dashboard box.

2856
02:13:11,981 --> 02:13:13,301
Vehicle spotted.

2857
02:13:14,341 --> 02:13:15,381
Near the valley.

2858
02:13:15,941 --> 02:13:17,621
800 meters and closing.

2859
02:13:17,781 --> 02:13:19,420
We never expected this
when we joined you.

2860
02:13:19,421 --> 02:13:21,660
At least you remembered
to pay us our worth.

2861
02:13:21,661 --> 02:13:23,180
Don't talk about worth.
We won't get a penny.

2862
02:13:23,181 --> 02:13:24,261
Take the shot now.

2863
02:13:25,741 --> 02:13:27,340
Oh no!

2864
02:13:27,341 --> 02:13:28,861
My God!

2865
02:13:55,981 --> 02:13:58,101
This is not over yet.

2866
02:14:04,981 --> 02:14:06,341
Sweet dreams, little boy.

2867
02:14:07,541 --> 02:14:08,661
Grab the boxes.

2868
02:14:13,661 --> 02:14:14,741
Check the other one.

2869
02:14:17,501 --> 02:14:18,581
It's empty.

2870
02:14:19,261 --> 02:14:20,341
What!

2871
02:14:21,741 --> 02:14:22,821
It's empty!

2872
02:14:23,461 --> 02:14:24,821
Where the hell is the Star Dust?

2873
02:14:26,181 --> 02:14:27,541
Shift to the right and stomp...

2874
02:14:27,701 --> 02:14:28,661
Bend down and rise up...

2875
02:14:28,781 --> 02:14:29,741
Shift to the left...

2876
02:14:38,141 --> 02:14:40,381
Why has the training ceased, Vikraman?

2877
02:14:40,941 --> 02:14:42,341
A guest awaits you, my Lord.

2878
02:15:06,781 --> 02:15:07,900
What troubles you, elder brother?

2879
02:15:07,901 --> 02:15:10,301
Why does your face show no joy
even at the sight of your younger brother?

2880
02:15:11,461 --> 02:15:14,101
You renounced the kingdom
and its rule.

2881
02:15:14,741 --> 02:15:18,341
Are you displeased because I keep
coming here and troubling you?

2882
02:15:20,421 --> 02:15:22,820
Hey! Why do you stand there
like stone?

2883
02:15:22,821 --> 02:15:23,941
Speak. What is the reason?

2884
02:15:24,461 --> 02:15:25,901
I shall tell you the reason!

2885
02:15:30,661 --> 02:15:31,781
Walter Sahib?

2886
02:15:32,461 --> 02:15:33,941
So this is where
you fled to, Sahib?

2887
02:15:34,141 --> 02:15:35,221
Shut up!

2888
02:15:35,861 --> 02:15:38,941
Those grand titles held weight
only until Azam Khan arrived.

2889
02:15:40,061 --> 02:15:41,261
Where is my treasure?

2890
02:15:42,461 --> 02:15:43,501
Huh? Who is that?

2891
02:15:43,941 --> 02:15:45,980
Treasure... treasure...
the treasure!

2892
02:15:45,981 --> 02:15:46,980
Treasure?

2893
02:15:46,981 --> 02:15:47,980
Which treasure?

2894
02:15:47,981 --> 02:15:49,261
Are you deceiving me again?

2895
02:15:50,381 --> 02:15:52,221
I will grant you
exactly one moment.

2896
02:15:52,861 --> 02:15:54,301
Where is my treasure?

2897
02:15:54,981 --> 02:15:56,260
- Water Sahib!
- Yes?

2898
02:15:56,261 --> 02:15:58,221
If we kill him,
how shall we obtain the treasure?

2899
02:15:58,661 --> 02:15:59,861
That is true.

2900
02:16:01,141 --> 02:16:02,141
Change of target!

2901
02:16:03,501 --> 02:16:04,581
Padmanabhan...

2902
02:16:04,901 --> 02:16:06,261
I shall count to three.

2903
02:16:07,501 --> 02:16:08,661
One!

2904
02:16:09,741 --> 02:16:11,021
- Two!
- Four!

2905
02:16:11,221 --> 02:16:12,421
Don't!

2906
02:16:13,061 --> 02:16:14,221
- I'll tell you.
- Don't!

2907
02:16:14,461 --> 02:16:16,821
Even if we lose our lives,
do not tell them where it is!

2908
02:16:17,341 --> 02:16:18,300
Oh, really?

2909
02:16:18,301 --> 02:16:19,301
Say three, sir.

2910
02:16:20,341 --> 02:16:21,700
Fine. Three!

2911
02:16:21,701 --> 02:16:22,981
O Goddess!

2912
02:16:23,621 --> 02:16:24,701
Oh no!

2913
02:16:32,541 --> 02:16:33,661
O Goddess!

2914
02:16:40,261 --> 02:16:42,661
That white lady is coming
to wallop us again, Sahib!

2915
02:16:49,341 --> 02:16:50,501
Oh no!

2916
02:16:52,341 --> 02:16:54,260
- Fire!
- Oh no!

2917
02:16:54,261 --> 02:16:55,660
Please don't shoot me, Madam!

2918
02:16:55,661 --> 02:16:56,701
Oh no! She shot me!

2919
02:17:11,941 --> 02:17:12,940
- Hey, Vikraman!
- Yes.

2920
02:17:12,941 --> 02:17:15,301
Stop practising your moves in hiding.
Stand forth and fight!

2921
02:17:26,061 --> 02:17:27,381
Come forward, younger brother!

2922
02:17:27,861 --> 02:17:28,981
Shit!

2923
02:17:34,341 --> 02:17:35,340
Oh no! My rear!

2924
02:17:35,341 --> 02:17:37,140
Don't stop.
Keep running!

2925
02:17:37,141 --> 02:17:38,221
Hey, Padmanabhan!

2926
02:17:48,341 --> 02:17:49,821
Oh God! Mother!

2927
02:17:50,301 --> 02:17:51,380
Oh God!

2928
02:17:51,381 --> 02:17:53,341
- My little brother! Padmanabhan!
- Big brother!

2929
02:17:55,221 --> 02:17:57,181
- Here I go, brother.
- Going where?

2930
02:17:57,341 --> 02:17:58,700
The bullet didn't even hit you,
you fool!

2931
02:17:58,701 --> 02:18:00,541
It struck your armour!
Now rise!

2932
02:18:01,061 --> 02:18:02,580
So the bullet did not pierce me?

2933
02:18:02,581 --> 02:18:03,700
Silence! Up, now!

2934
02:18:03,701 --> 02:18:04,860
Get up and run!

2935
02:18:04,861 --> 02:18:06,221
- Come here!
- Kill her, Sahib!

2936
02:18:06,421 --> 02:18:07,621
Oh no!

2937
02:18:19,181 --> 02:18:21,741
Your horse awaits
at the end of this tunnel.

2938
02:18:22,421 --> 02:18:25,141
Gather your men and
ride to Eraniel Palace at once.

2939
02:18:25,581 --> 02:18:28,581
The Emperor of Travancore will protect you!

2940
02:18:30,581 --> 02:18:31,741
O Guardian Deity!

2941
02:18:36,341 --> 02:18:37,501
May your journey be safe.

2942
02:18:50,501 --> 02:18:52,221
- Where is the bomb?
- What?

2943
02:18:52,741 --> 02:18:54,061
The country bomb!

2944
02:18:54,221 --> 02:18:55,461
Oh no! I forgot to bring it!

2945
02:18:55,821 --> 02:18:56,860
You stupid!

2946
02:18:56,861 --> 02:18:58,020
- Where is the bomb?
- Oh no!

2947
02:18:58,021 --> 02:18:59,940
Hey, soldier! Give me the bomb!

2948
02:18:59,941 --> 02:19:01,900
Please bomb me!
Throw! Throw!

2949
02:19:01,901 --> 02:19:02,940
Throw! Throw!

2950
02:19:02,941 --> 02:19:04,780
- Throwing!
- Hey, give the bomb to Sahib!

2951
02:19:04,781 --> 02:19:05,860
Not this way!

2952
02:19:05,861 --> 02:19:07,701
Oh no!!!

2953
02:19:28,701 --> 02:19:29,861
Oh God!

2954
02:20:15,021 --> 02:20:16,500
No matter how much
herbal remedy I apply,

2955
02:20:16,501 --> 02:20:18,581
this pain from the whipping
just won't go away.

2956
02:20:23,021 --> 02:20:24,221
- Huh!
- Look, it's the King!

2957
02:20:25,661 --> 02:20:26,900
Shankaran! Achyuthan!

2958
02:20:26,901 --> 02:20:28,301
Look! His Majesty is alive!

2959
02:20:28,541 --> 02:20:30,700
My eyes and heart never tire
of seeing you, Your Majesty!

2960
02:20:30,701 --> 02:20:33,501
You said you don't bid farewell
after dark and left, Abu Salah!

2961
02:20:33,821 --> 02:20:35,700
So why are you back here
covered in cow dung?

2962
02:20:35,701 --> 02:20:36,701
Answer me.

2963
02:20:38,541 --> 02:20:40,020
Before we even realised it,

2964
02:20:40,021 --> 02:20:41,861
we have become warriors again,
Your Highness.

2965
02:20:41,981 --> 02:20:43,940
Along with that,
our patriotism has also grown.

2966
02:20:43,941 --> 02:20:45,021
For what?

2967
02:20:45,661 --> 02:20:47,101
Just forget all that, my Lord.

2968
02:20:47,221 --> 02:20:48,420
How did you come here?

2969
02:20:48,421 --> 02:20:49,701
- Kurup...
- Yes.

2970
02:20:49,901 --> 02:20:51,621
You must realise something
at least now.

2971
02:20:52,021 --> 02:20:54,341
It is not only
Azam Khan pursuing us.

2972
02:20:54,861 --> 02:20:56,501
There is that traitor Walter Sahib

2973
02:20:56,661 --> 02:20:58,421
and other foreign powers as well.

2974
02:20:58,781 --> 02:21:00,781
So Kurup, we must go

2975
02:21:01,021 --> 02:21:03,900
and meet His Highness of Travancore
at once.

2976
02:21:03,901 --> 02:21:05,381
We shall obtain
weapons from there--

2977
02:21:06,501 --> 02:21:07,661
Where did that come from?

2978
02:21:12,141 --> 02:21:13,141
Azam Khan!

2979
02:21:14,301 --> 02:21:16,021
I used to be a real terror once!

2980
02:21:16,741 --> 02:21:19,540
And now? Stranded in the middle
of a tea estate with a flat tire!

2981
02:21:19,541 --> 02:21:20,620
Bad!

2982
02:21:20,621 --> 02:21:21,941
- It's too bad!
- Hey!

2983
02:21:22,221 --> 02:21:24,580
This isn't a tea estate, man.
It's a pineapple estate.

2984
02:21:24,581 --> 02:21:25,941
Can't you see that?

2985
02:21:30,381 --> 02:21:31,861
Tea, pineapple, who gives a damn!

2986
02:21:32,661 --> 02:21:33,860
Mr. Dragon...

2987
02:21:33,861 --> 02:21:36,541
Back in Bangkok,
I wasn't giving massages.

2988
02:21:36,941 --> 02:21:38,101
I was a gangster.

2989
02:21:38,341 --> 02:21:39,461
A monster.

2990
02:21:39,741 --> 02:21:44,220
I've stormed through downtown Bangkok
in epic chases,

2991
02:21:44,221 --> 02:21:47,660
smashing through police cruisers
and the armed trucks of rival gangs.

2992
02:21:47,661 --> 02:21:50,541
That's Son of Damodaran Unni,
Dilman Edakochi for you!

2993
02:21:51,341 --> 02:21:52,501
Now look at me!

2994
02:21:53,061 --> 02:21:55,181
I've ended up like a soggy,
burnt onion fritter!

2995
02:21:57,021 --> 02:21:58,460
Dude's Bangkok slap!

2996
02:21:58,461 --> 02:21:59,620
Very nice.

2997
02:21:59,621 --> 02:22:01,101
Oh God, time is running out.

2998
02:22:01,981 --> 02:22:03,020
Paappan!

2999
02:22:03,021 --> 02:22:04,661
Where are we racing off to?

3000
02:22:04,941 --> 02:22:06,700
Now that it's on the news,

3001
02:22:06,701 --> 02:22:08,381
they'll try
to slip into Tamil Nadu.

3002
02:22:08,621 --> 02:22:10,540
We can grab them in Madurai.

3003
02:22:10,541 --> 02:22:11,420
Right.

3004
02:22:11,421 --> 02:22:13,021
Then step on
the accelerator, Paappan!

3005
02:22:13,781 --> 02:22:15,980
Do you think I'm stepping on
your father's chest here?

3006
02:22:15,981 --> 02:22:17,661
We're lucky it even has
four decent tires.

3007
02:22:17,981 --> 02:22:19,740
We have to find out
what's in those boxes.

3008
02:22:19,741 --> 02:22:21,261
Let's take this route.

3009
02:22:22,101 --> 02:22:23,260
This field used to be
my outdoor toilet.

3010
02:22:23,261 --> 02:22:25,461
You can do that even now,
but there won't be any water.

3011
02:22:27,901 --> 02:22:29,301
No screw-ups this time, boys.

3012
02:22:29,421 --> 02:22:30,421
I am optimistic.

3013
02:22:30,941 --> 02:22:32,941
As they say,
third time's a charm.

3014
02:22:33,061 --> 02:22:34,220
Correct!

3015
02:22:34,221 --> 02:22:35,341
This is your last chance.

3016
02:22:35,461 --> 02:22:36,741
There won't be a fourth chance.

3017
02:22:39,621 --> 02:22:40,860
I don't need four.
I'll take the fifth.

3018
02:22:40,861 --> 02:22:41,700
No way.

3019
02:22:41,701 --> 02:22:42,820
Mr. Pulikesi...

3020
02:22:42,821 --> 02:22:46,381
Don't try to act tough with me just because
of that transformer in my underwear.

3021
02:22:46,941 --> 02:22:49,141
The shock it gives today
may not be there tomorrow.

3022
02:22:49,981 --> 02:22:51,101
Because--

3023
02:22:51,221 --> 02:22:53,020
Ow! Oh no!
Stop pressing it!

3024
02:22:53,021 --> 02:22:54,060
He'll die!

3025
02:22:54,061 --> 02:22:55,421
We can't even grab him!

3026
02:22:55,821 --> 02:22:56,861
Hey, nutcase...

3027
02:22:57,221 --> 02:23:00,420
How are you still dropping punchlines
after getting your butt electrocuted?

3028
02:23:00,421 --> 02:23:02,300
If the boss doesn't get the box,

3029
02:23:02,301 --> 02:23:03,900
it's my butt that
will get electrocuted!

3030
02:23:03,901 --> 02:23:05,701
The helicopter rent
was too expensive.

3031
02:23:06,501 --> 02:23:07,540
Dude!

3032
02:23:07,541 --> 02:23:08,821
- Vehicle is ready!
- Yes.

3033
02:23:08,981 --> 02:23:10,020
- Chase!
- Okay!

3034
02:23:10,021 --> 02:23:11,661
- Start the vehicle!
- ♪ He is the DUDE! ♪

3035
02:23:14,781 --> 02:23:17,540
Paappan, I want to leave this gang.
Give me a transfer certificate.

3036
02:23:17,541 --> 02:23:20,180
And I want to join
that gunman's gang instead!

3037
02:23:20,181 --> 02:23:22,501
- Fantastic!
- I want to be a don like him!

3038
02:23:24,261 --> 02:23:25,821
Why are you silent, Paappan?

3039
02:23:26,061 --> 02:23:27,260
I don't respond to such crap!

3040
02:23:27,261 --> 02:23:28,901
Paappan, look over there!

3041
02:23:29,621 --> 02:23:30,701
Huh!

3042
02:23:37,661 --> 02:23:42,341
♪ Within a mind shattered
by broken dreams... ♪

3043
02:23:42,461 --> 02:23:46,701
♪ Upon the steps stained
by the weight of a curse... ♪

3044
02:23:47,181 --> 02:23:51,900
♪ I stood in prayer
as the twilight deepened... ♪

3045
02:23:51,901 --> 02:23:56,141
♪ O, beauty of my soul,
who drifts away into the distance... ♪

3046
02:23:56,541 --> 02:23:58,981
♪ Dissolve into my life-breath ♪

3047
02:23:59,421 --> 02:24:00,620
Look!

3048
02:24:00,621 --> 02:24:03,220
♪ And do it swiftly ♪

3049
02:24:03,221 --> 02:24:04,340
Who's that?

3050
02:24:04,341 --> 02:24:05,940
He is a distant relative,
named Paappan.

3051
02:24:05,941 --> 02:24:07,021
Ah, alright.

3052
02:24:11,941 --> 02:24:13,181
You know, I was thinking...

3053
02:24:13,421 --> 02:24:14,620
I was having the same thought.

3054
02:24:14,621 --> 02:24:16,220
We missed the wedding biryani.

3055
02:24:16,221 --> 02:24:17,261
- Right?
- Will you shut up?

3056
02:24:18,261 --> 02:24:19,581
- Hey, Pookie boy!
- Yes?

3057
02:24:20,421 --> 02:24:22,300
What do you call it
when people go back in time?

3058
02:24:22,301 --> 02:24:23,461
That's time travel, Paappan.

3059
02:24:23,581 --> 02:24:24,580
Right.

3060
02:24:24,581 --> 02:24:25,740
If I could do that,

3061
02:24:25,741 --> 02:24:27,501
I'd go back
and stop his parents' wedding!

3062
02:24:27,701 --> 02:24:29,420
Then I wouldn't have had
to deal with him.

3063
02:24:29,421 --> 02:24:30,741
Now I'm stuck with no choice.

3064
02:24:31,301 --> 02:24:33,500
Take that wreath off the vehicle
and put it on him.

3065
02:24:33,501 --> 02:24:36,261
Are you talking about the wreath
on top of our vehicle, Paappan?

3066
02:24:36,861 --> 02:24:38,461
Don't take it to heart, Shajiyettan.

3067
02:24:39,381 --> 02:24:41,701
She's never going to have
a happy marriage.

3068
02:24:42,581 --> 02:24:44,340
Did you see
the way that groom stood?

3069
02:24:44,341 --> 02:24:46,301
He's a total dud.
Just like you, Shajiyettan.

3070
02:24:46,981 --> 02:24:49,100
Damn right!
I am a dud.

3071
02:24:49,101 --> 02:24:52,300
No wonder I keep dragging you all around
like a lottery ticket that never wins!

3072
02:24:52,301 --> 02:24:54,181
Abu, what kind of talk is that?

3073
02:24:54,621 --> 02:24:56,820
He looks like a civet.
And you call him a dud?

3074
02:24:56,821 --> 02:24:58,140
Your father is the civet!

3075
02:24:58,141 --> 02:25:00,140
Trying to swing from a doomed
man's rope, you low-life?

3076
02:25:00,141 --> 02:25:01,700
- Drop it, Paappan.
- Drop it?!

3077
02:25:01,701 --> 02:25:03,340
I should drop you
guys off a cliff first!

3078
02:25:03,341 --> 02:25:05,740
My mother warned me
never to let you guys into the house.

3079
02:25:05,741 --> 02:25:07,781
Because of you guys,
now even I got kicked out!

3080
02:25:08,141 --> 02:25:09,821
- Paappan! Jeep! Jeep!
- Jeep!

3081
02:25:12,581 --> 02:25:14,381
Turn the Jeep!
Turn it around!

3082
02:25:19,101 --> 02:25:20,341
Oh my God!

3083
02:25:49,301 --> 02:25:50,340
Sir...

3084
02:25:50,341 --> 02:25:53,060
The vehicles of that Dude
who took the boxes and Paappan

3085
02:25:53,061 --> 02:25:54,580
have crashed in front of our station!

3086
02:25:54,581 --> 02:25:56,460
If the tug-of-war guy and
the gunman are together,

3087
02:25:56,461 --> 02:25:57,580
one thing is certain.

3088
02:25:57,581 --> 02:25:59,500
Those rascals definitely know
where the loot is.

3089
02:25:59,501 --> 02:26:00,660
Pounce on them, Paappi!

3090
02:26:00,661 --> 02:26:01,940
What are you saying, sir?

3091
02:26:01,941 --> 02:26:03,341
I'm all alone here, sir.

3092
02:26:05,021 --> 02:26:06,741
In that case,
just keep a close eye on them.

3093
02:26:06,941 --> 02:26:08,181
Of course, I will!

3094
02:26:16,901 --> 02:26:18,341
Hear me, King!

3095
02:26:18,581 --> 02:26:20,701
Today, you shall meet your end!

3096
02:26:20,981 --> 02:26:22,141
Your Majesty!

3097
02:26:32,581 --> 02:26:34,061
It is time to end this.

3098
02:26:35,301 --> 02:26:36,501
Azam Khan!

3099
02:26:37,021 --> 02:26:39,261
The timeline crossing process
is about to begin.

3100
02:26:39,901 --> 02:26:42,181
Let's hope for a good outcome.

3101
02:27:00,141 --> 02:27:02,381
If you truly have the mettle,
face me one-on-one!

3102
02:27:02,661 --> 02:27:04,061
A wise choice, Your Majesty.

3103
02:27:04,621 --> 02:27:06,340
Better to die
with a blade to the chest

3104
02:27:06,341 --> 02:27:09,421
than to die with an arrow in the back
while fleeing like a coward.

3105
02:27:09,901 --> 02:27:11,581
Paappan has nothing
left to lose now!

3106
02:27:12,421 --> 02:27:13,701
Flip, and it's Malappuram.

3107
02:27:14,301 --> 02:27:15,701
Turn, and it's Thiruvananthapuram!

3108
02:27:16,141 --> 02:27:17,261
You wretch!

3109
02:27:17,821 --> 02:27:20,781
Paappan won't rest
until you're done and dusted!

3110
02:27:21,301 --> 02:27:23,140
Flip Malappuram,
turn Thiruvananthapuram,

3111
02:27:23,141 --> 02:27:24,941
or do whatever the hell you want!

3112
02:27:26,941 --> 02:27:28,341
Bangkok is behind me...

3113
02:27:28,821 --> 02:27:30,181
and Miami is waiting ahead!

3114
02:27:31,061 --> 02:27:32,261
Come to Daddy!

3115
02:27:35,101 --> 02:27:36,661
Look at his arrogance!

3116
02:27:36,821 --> 02:27:38,661
- Yeah.
- He'll meet his end today!

3117
02:27:39,141 --> 02:27:40,500
Crush him, Shajiyetta!

3118
02:27:40,501 --> 02:27:42,581
No sentiments, no compromise!

3119
02:27:42,981 --> 02:27:45,020
You lunatic!
The box is all that matters.

3120
02:27:45,021 --> 02:27:47,421
- Do we really need a fight right now?
- This guy is getting on my nerves!

3121
02:27:47,901 --> 02:27:49,061
It is necessary!

3122
02:27:49,301 --> 02:27:51,621
Because we won't get another chance.

3123
02:27:52,621 --> 02:27:53,821
This is our last ride.

3124
02:27:54,061 --> 02:27:55,861
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

3125
02:28:02,541 --> 02:28:03,901
I'm coming for you.

3126
02:28:04,541 --> 02:28:05,661
Toofaan!

3127
02:28:05,901 --> 02:28:07,101
Charge!

3128
02:28:08,221 --> 02:28:09,701
Kill him, my Lord.

3129
02:28:09,941 --> 02:28:11,141
Bhairava!

3130
02:28:15,101 --> 02:28:17,060
Finish him off, Your Majesty!

3131
02:28:17,061 --> 02:28:19,540
♪ Valiant heroes,
Sound the battle cry! ♪

3132
02:28:19,541 --> 02:28:23,261
♪ Blazing wrath on fire,
Strike and charge on high! ♪

3133
02:28:26,781 --> 02:28:29,220
♪ Valiant heroes,
Sound the battle cry! ♪

3134
02:28:29,221 --> 02:28:33,101
♪ Blood-red war arises,
Strike and charge on high! ♪

3135
02:28:36,181 --> 02:28:37,661
Shajiyetta!!!

3136
02:29:46,581 --> 02:29:48,020
What was that tremor?

3137
02:29:48,021 --> 02:29:49,141
My Lord!

3138
02:29:49,261 --> 02:29:50,660
Your Majesty! Huh!

3139
02:29:50,661 --> 02:29:51,781
Was that lightning?

3140
02:29:53,101 --> 02:29:54,340
Where has our king gone?

3141
02:29:54,341 --> 02:29:55,700
Did the king just
vanish into thin air?

3142
02:29:55,701 --> 02:29:56,781
- What?
- What?

3143
02:29:57,421 --> 02:29:58,620
He disappeared!

3144
02:29:58,621 --> 02:30:00,421
- Huh! Dude sir!
- Where is that nutcase?

3145
02:30:03,141 --> 02:30:04,301
Sir...

3146
02:30:04,581 --> 02:30:06,941
Lightning struck them both
and they just vanished!

3147
02:30:07,581 --> 02:30:08,500
Huh?!

3148
02:30:08,501 --> 02:30:10,820
Struck by lightning and vanished?
What are they, Minnal Murali?

3149
02:30:10,821 --> 02:30:11,780
Tell the truth, you rascal!

3150
02:30:11,781 --> 02:30:12,780
Hey, where did Paappan go?

3151
02:30:12,781 --> 02:30:14,820
Hey, that gunman is missing too!

3152
02:30:14,821 --> 02:30:18,261
He pressed that switch
and made our Dude Sir vanish.

3153
02:30:19,021 --> 02:30:20,780
Hey, why are you hitting me?

3154
02:30:20,781 --> 02:30:22,580
Both the box and that nutcase
have vanished!

3155
02:30:22,581 --> 02:30:26,501
If I go back and tell this,
the boss will chop me into pieces!

3156
02:30:27,301 --> 02:30:31,020
It is during times of crisis like these
that true heroes are forged.

3157
02:30:31,021 --> 02:30:32,141
It is!

3158
02:30:33,341 --> 02:30:35,060
- Oh! Abu, don't run!
- He ran away!

3159
02:30:35,061 --> 02:30:36,700
Abu ran.
Shouldn't we run too?

3160
02:30:36,701 --> 02:30:38,580
Man, you guys are so stupid!

3161
02:30:38,581 --> 02:30:40,820
- Paappan already told us before he left.
- He told us?

3162
02:30:40,821 --> 02:30:43,300
Didn't he say he'd go back
and stop my parents' wedding?

3163
02:30:43,301 --> 02:30:45,180
- In some Tempo traveller, right?
- Time travel.

3164
02:30:45,181 --> 02:30:46,380
Ah, time traveller.

3165
02:30:46,381 --> 02:30:47,941
Let him do his thing
and come back.

3166
02:31:02,421 --> 02:31:04,621
If it's sesame oil pressing,
Antony and I can handle it.

3167
02:31:04,981 --> 02:31:06,461
Just Antony and I are enough.

3168
02:31:07,021 --> 02:31:08,500
But for copra work,
I need an assistant.

3169
02:31:08,501 --> 02:31:09,540
I need a donkey.

3170
02:31:09,541 --> 02:31:11,701
Antony!

3171
02:31:17,541 --> 02:31:18,701
What the hell happened?

3172
02:31:22,901 --> 02:31:24,021
Where am I?

3173
02:31:29,301 --> 02:31:30,621
Where on earth am I?

3174
02:31:33,141 --> 02:31:35,381
♪ He is the DUDE ♪

3175
02:31:40,861 --> 02:31:44,900
♪ Your neatly combed feathery hair...
how were they ruffled, my lass? ♪

3176
02:31:44,901 --> 02:31:47,581
♪ How were they ruffled, my lass? ♪

3177
02:31:47,941 --> 02:31:51,781
♪ To the thorny wild I went for a lily,
the brambles snagged them loose ♪

3178
02:31:52,941 --> 02:31:54,181
Seriously, which is this place?

3179
02:31:55,421 --> 02:32:00,500
♪ That mark of sandal upon your brow,
how did it vanish, my lass? ♪

3180
02:32:00,501 --> 02:32:02,020
♪ Whither did it fade? ♪

3181
02:32:02,021 --> 02:32:04,700
♪ Under the scorching sun
on the long, winding paths ♪

3182
02:32:04,701 --> 02:32:06,060
Somebody should be there.

3183
02:32:06,061 --> 02:32:09,181
♪ The salt of my sweat
washed it clean, my lad... ♪

3184
02:32:09,621 --> 02:32:14,300
♪ The golden ring that graced your nose,
how was it lost, my lass? ♪

3185
02:32:14,301 --> 02:32:16,061
♪ How was it lost? ♪

3186
02:32:16,701 --> 02:32:18,501
Gentleman, one Martini Gold.

3187
02:32:19,381 --> 02:32:20,620
Sharp and elegant.

3188
02:32:20,621 --> 02:32:22,301
Make it dry. Please.

3189
02:32:22,541 --> 02:32:25,740
I cannot quite understand
what drink you desire, local foreigner.

3190
02:32:25,741 --> 02:32:30,021
♪ The golden bangles that clasped
your arms, how did they vanish, my lass? ♪

3191
02:32:30,381 --> 02:32:31,901
Oh! It's a vintage theme here, is it?

3192
02:32:32,701 --> 02:32:34,501
Then give me a glass of
your finest wine.

3193
02:32:34,781 --> 02:32:35,940
Very well, sir.

3194
02:32:35,941 --> 02:32:38,540
♪ They snapped
and shattered apart, my lad... ♪

3195
02:32:38,541 --> 02:32:44,540
♪ I knew not of these wiles and clever
tricks, my bird of five-coloured plumes! ♪

3196
02:32:44,541 --> 02:32:45,740
Stop it, you mongrels!

3197
02:32:45,741 --> 02:32:49,421
♪ Vareeth ♪

3198
02:32:51,501 --> 02:32:54,301
No song or dance
shall calm my rage!

3199
02:32:55,701 --> 02:32:59,301
I could have gone to Mysore
and built so many new bridges!

3200
02:33:00,061 --> 02:33:03,421
Instead, he threw me off
my own bridge into the river!

3201
02:33:04,901 --> 02:33:07,181
That lying scoundrel, Azam Khan!

3202
02:33:08,581 --> 02:33:09,780
Azam Khan.

3203
02:33:09,781 --> 02:33:10,740
Dirty fellow.

3204
02:33:10,741 --> 02:33:13,780
Even after I told him I could not swim
and was terrified of snakes,

3205
02:33:13,781 --> 02:33:14,821
he would not heed me!

3206
02:33:15,101 --> 02:33:17,500
Even my coat, gifted to me
by Father Victor in London,

3207
02:33:17,501 --> 02:33:18,861
was ripped apart by alligators!

3208
02:33:19,701 --> 02:33:20,861
So sad!

3209
02:33:21,381 --> 02:33:23,621
Had those fishermen not
cast their nets in time,

3210
02:33:23,901 --> 02:33:25,421
think what would have
become of me!

3211
02:33:25,661 --> 02:33:28,301
I will kill him!

3212
02:33:29,141 --> 02:33:31,861
I need no guns or swords
to kill him.

3213
02:33:33,021 --> 02:33:35,341
My spanner is all I need!
A spanner!

3214
02:33:36,141 --> 02:33:38,221
I shall unscrew
every nut and bolt of his...

3215
02:33:38,541 --> 02:33:40,340
every single nut...

3216
02:33:40,341 --> 02:33:41,501
his...

3217
02:33:42,341 --> 02:33:43,421
nut...

3218
02:33:45,821 --> 02:33:47,141
Very emotional story.

3219
02:33:47,581 --> 02:33:48,661
Please continue.

3220
02:33:49,261 --> 02:33:50,421
Oh no!

3221
02:33:50,781 --> 02:33:51,941
Azam Khan!

3222
02:33:52,181 --> 02:33:53,380
Everybody run!

3223
02:33:53,381 --> 02:33:56,181
Did you think I would not recognise
you in that coat, you scoundrel?

3224
02:33:57,941 --> 02:34:00,101
- Oh no! My clothes!
- Don't look there, you scoundrel!

3225
02:34:00,941 --> 02:34:02,021
Jump!

3226
02:34:04,621 --> 02:34:06,301
What kind of crazy,
messy mix-up is this?

3227
02:34:08,901 --> 02:34:10,101
Has everyone left?

3228
02:34:11,101 --> 02:34:12,301
Who is this Azam Khan?

3229
02:34:13,061 --> 02:34:14,101
Where is he now?

3230
02:34:16,821 --> 02:34:19,501
That fellow who just ran off
looked exactly like the Sarbath-maker!

3231
02:34:20,261 --> 02:34:22,581
But why did he run away?
Shouldn't I be the one running?

3232
02:34:25,461 --> 02:34:26,541
Dragon!

3233
02:34:27,381 --> 02:34:28,501
Dragon!

3234
02:34:29,581 --> 02:34:32,501
I don't see a single scoundrel here.
All the ones I saw have run away.

3235
02:34:36,341 --> 02:34:37,741
Something is fishy.

3236
02:34:38,461 --> 02:34:39,540
Dear people,

3237
02:34:39,541 --> 02:34:41,581
after a magnificent procession,

3238
02:34:41,901 --> 02:34:46,381
our "Heritage 2025"
now reaches its closing ceremony.

3239
02:34:46,781 --> 02:34:50,220
All those who have preserved
our land's heritage

3240
02:34:50,221 --> 02:34:51,821
are here with us on
this stage today.

3241
02:34:52,061 --> 02:34:53,301
Except for one person.

3242
02:34:53,461 --> 02:34:56,300
The king of tug-of-war,
Shaji Paappan!

3243
02:34:56,301 --> 02:34:58,341
He will be arriving shortly.

3244
02:34:59,181 --> 02:35:01,821
If he says he'll show up,
he'll definitely show up!

3245
02:35:02,021 --> 02:35:04,181
O Goddess!!!

3246
02:35:05,261 --> 02:35:07,620
♪ Grandmaster of the duel,
sovereign of the land ♪

3247
02:35:07,621 --> 02:35:09,980
♪ War-dance titan none may ever withstand ♪
He... Huh?

3248
02:35:09,981 --> 02:35:12,220
♪ Lord of the realm,
great master of valour ♪

3249
02:35:12,221 --> 02:35:14,420
♪ O fearless guardian,
protector of the order ♪

3250
02:35:14,421 --> 02:35:16,820
♪ The Infinite One,
Scion of the royal bloodstream ♪

3251
02:35:16,821 --> 02:35:18,981
♪ Despot of Empires,
Autocrat Supreme ♪

3252
02:35:19,101 --> 02:35:21,380
♪ Monarch of the blade,
king of every crown ♪

3253
02:35:21,381 --> 02:35:24,221
♪ Behold the mighty Padmanabha,
great king of renown ♪

3254
02:35:25,781 --> 02:35:28,220
Don't just stand there staring,
say something on the mic!

3255
02:35:28,221 --> 02:35:30,580
No one needs to be afraid.
Shaji Paappan has lost his mind!

3256
02:35:30,581 --> 02:35:31,820
Everyone, please come back.

3257
02:35:31,821 --> 02:35:32,981
What kingdom is this?

3258
02:35:35,301 --> 02:35:36,461
Rohini!

3259
02:35:38,341 --> 02:35:39,900
O Goddess!
My back!

3260
02:35:39,901 --> 02:35:41,181
I'm going to kill him today!

3261
02:35:42,421 --> 02:35:44,460
Release my hand!
Who are you people?

3262
02:35:44,461 --> 02:35:45,581
- Shaji!
- Huh?

3263
02:35:46,181 --> 02:35:49,100
Drowning yourself in cheap liquor
and dressing like a clown,

3264
02:35:49,101 --> 02:35:51,660
are you trying to disgrace me in front
of all these people, you son of a gun?

3265
02:35:51,661 --> 02:35:53,221
- Who are you, lady?
- Your worst nightmare!

3266
02:35:54,781 --> 02:35:56,861
Shaji Paappan, cut out
this nonsense!

3267
02:35:57,021 --> 02:36:00,020
How did you grow
such a thick beard so quickly, man?

3268
02:36:00,021 --> 02:36:02,340
Lift him up
and prop him up on that stage.

3269
02:36:02,341 --> 02:36:03,100
- Prop me up?
- Yeah, lift him!

3270
02:36:03,101 --> 02:36:04,540
- Lift him, lift him.
- Hey, stop!

3271
02:36:04,541 --> 02:36:05,580
I am the King.

3272
02:36:05,581 --> 02:36:07,300
We all feel like kings
after a couple of drinks.

3273
02:36:07,301 --> 02:36:07,980
You grab him. Lift!

3274
02:36:07,981 --> 02:36:10,260
What are you doing?
Hey, do not touch me there!

3275
02:36:10,261 --> 02:36:11,780
Let's honour him royally today!

3276
02:36:11,781 --> 02:36:13,140
My back is grievously hurt!

3277
02:36:13,141 --> 02:36:14,460
The whole world
knows that, Paappan.

3278
02:36:14,461 --> 02:36:16,220
What is this?
Are you trying to devour me?

3279
02:36:16,221 --> 02:36:18,180
Stop making lame jokes, Paappan!

3280
02:36:18,181 --> 02:36:20,421
I am not Paappan.
I am Padmanabhan!

3281
02:36:21,061 --> 02:36:23,340
♪ Grandmaster of the duel,
sovereign of the land ♪

3282
02:36:23,341 --> 02:36:25,700
♪ War-dance titan
none may ever withstand ♪

3283
02:36:25,701 --> 02:36:27,940
♪ Lord of the realm,
great master of valour ♪

3284
02:36:27,941 --> 02:36:30,340
♪ O fearless guardian,
protector of the order ♪

3285
02:36:30,341 --> 02:36:31,541
What happens now, Baba?

3286
02:36:32,421 --> 02:36:34,101
Chaos, confusion.

3287
02:36:35,421 --> 02:36:37,301
And in every timeline,

3288
02:36:38,941 --> 02:36:39,941
war awaits!

3289
02:37:09,301 --> 02:37:10,501
Paappan!

3290
02:37:18,341 --> 02:37:19,741
♪ Paappan, Paappan ♪

3291
02:37:20,061 --> 02:37:21,541
♪ O Paappan, Paappan ♪

3292
02:37:21,821 --> 02:37:23,341
♪ O Paappan, Paappan ♪

3293
02:37:23,701 --> 02:37:25,141
♪ O Paappan, Paappan ♪

3294
02:37:25,541 --> 02:37:29,100
♪ Even Haji Mastan would salute the man,
The brave and mighty Shaji Paappan ♪

3295
02:37:29,101 --> 02:37:32,381
♪ Even an atom bomb would surely fizzle,
Before Shaji Paappan's lethal sizzle ♪

3296
02:37:32,821 --> 02:37:36,380
♪ Even Haji Mastan would salute the man,
The brave and mighty Shaji Paappan ♪

3297
02:37:36,381 --> 02:37:39,700
♪ Even an atom bomb would surely fizzle,
Before Shaji Paappan's lethal sizzle ♪

3298
02:37:39,701 --> 02:37:46,581
♪ O precious Paappan,
O priceless Paappan ♪

3299
02:38:14,101 --> 02:38:16,900
♪ The festival bursts with joy in the air,
Cheers and euphoria everywhere ♪

3300
02:38:16,901 --> 02:38:19,660
♪ Rope in hand for the tug-of-war,
Here comes the little army with a roar ♪

3301
02:38:19,661 --> 02:38:25,060
♪ Drums roll loud, storm-clouds proclaim,
Sirens and war-cries hail their fame ♪

3302
02:38:25,061 --> 02:38:27,860
♪ The world shall bow
to their blazing palms ♪

3303
02:38:27,861 --> 02:38:30,740
♪ Like pearls that fall
from shattered dreams ♪

3304
02:38:30,741 --> 02:38:36,260
♪ Like lightning racing for the sky,
Their daring hearts find paths to try ♪

3305
02:38:36,261 --> 02:38:41,740
♪ Where firework rebels gather bold,
Defy the sun that burns the road ♪

3306
02:38:41,741 --> 02:38:47,221
♪ O fearless legends brave and free,
Swimming across the roaring, raging sea ♪

3307
02:38:58,181 --> 02:39:03,341
♪ To the clash where lion warriors fight,
Come forth, O heroes of might ♪

3308
02:39:03,661 --> 02:39:08,620
♪ All brave hearts gather as one,
Make the raging battle begun ♪

3309
02:39:08,621 --> 02:39:14,501
♪ They swing on a rogue elephant's tusk,
Daredevils bold, fierce and brusque ♪

3310
02:39:14,701 --> 02:39:21,261
♪ Who dares to stand against their flame,
And halt their blazing charge to fame? ♪

3311
02:39:22,661 --> 02:39:25,420
♪ The festival bursts with joy in the air,
Cheers and euphoria everywhere ♪

